title: turkey and vegetables
directions: In
10-inch
skillet
combine
cabbage,
cauliflower, carrots and broth.
Cover and cook over medium-high heat until vegetables are tender-crisp, 8 to 10 minutes.
Add sausage and stir to combine.
Cook until sausages are heated through, 3 to 4 minutes longer.

title: buffalo chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter, brown sugar, sugar, vanilla and eggs. Add flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Mix.
Add chocolate chips, oatmeal, cereal, coconut and walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes a lot of cookies.

title: easy ranch vegetables
directions: Combine the dressing mix with the oil in a large bowl.
Mix with the vegetables and toss.
Bake in casserole dish at 375° for 30 minutes. Stir every 10 minutes.

title: carol's b&b blueberry muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Stir in blueberries. Add milk, egg and butter. Mix just until dry ingredients are moistened. The batter will be lumpy. Do not over beat. Spoon batter into twelve muffin cups. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes. Serve warm.

title: wrapped hot dogs
directions: Wrap the dough for one bread stick in a spiral around each hot dog.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 15 or 20 minutes until golden brown.
You can also use frozen hot dogs without taking any additional time.
Freeze any uneaten hot dogs.
Each can be reheated on High in a microwave for 2 minutes. Serves 4 to 8.

title: broccoli and rotelle macaroni
directions: Place oil in skillet.
Add onion and garlic.
Saute. When cloves are brown, remove. Add oleo.
Mix well. Cook broccoli according to box (don't overcook). Add broccoli to skillet.
Cook macaroni. Drain and add to skillet. Simmer over low heat. If needed, add more oleo. Add grated cheese and stir.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat slowly; spoon off excess fat.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles in boiling salt water until tender. Drain and rinse in cold water.
Combine cottage cheese, eggs, parsley, salt and pepper.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mix and freeze in 9 x 11-inch dish.
Thaw about 15 minutes before serving.

title: caramel pear pudding cake
directions: In large bowl, stir together first six ingredients.
Add milk, beating until smooth.
Stir in pears and pecans.
Turn into ungreased, 2-quart casserole.

title: pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Combine ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour, then turn oven to 300° and bake for another hour.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Melt margarine over medium heat.
Saute onions until clear and tender.
Grease a 2-quart casserole (8 x 11 x 2-inch).
Line dish with crushed cracker crumbs, reserving 3 tablespoons.
Alternately add undiluted cream of mushroom soup and onions.
Pour beaten eggs on top.
Pour milk on top of the eggs.
Sprinkle grated cheese next, then sprinkle the reserved cracker crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: plum good cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well with mixer, about 2 minutes.
Bake in Bundt pan in oven at 325° for 1 hour.
Check after 50 minutes.
Let cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Can also frost with Cream Cheese Frosting, if desired.

title: deep dutch oven catfish
directions: Melt margarine in a 10 to 12-inch frying pan; saute onion. Layer fish over onion; sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste. Cover with tomato sauce; add hot pepper if desired.
Cover and simmer for 10 to 20 minutes until catfish is desired texture.

title: prize-winning meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
Place in large baking dish.
Cover and bake 1 hour.
Spread ketchup or barbecue sauce evenly over top and bake additional 15 minutes.

title: streusel coffee cake
directions: Stir together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Combine egg, milk and oil.
Add to flour mixture and mix well.
Turn into a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine brown sugar, 2 tablespoons flour, butter and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over batter. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: lemon pepper chicken
directions: Grate peel from lemons. Set aside. Cut lemons in half and squeeze to make 1/4 cup juice. In a large resealable plastic bag, combine 1 Tbsp. of the lemon peel, lemon juice, olive oil, garlic, pepper, oregano, rosemary, thyme and salt. Score chicken. Add chicken to bag and squeeze to coat chicken completely. Refrigerate for 1 hour, turning bag occasionally.

title: no-bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix corn syrup and sugar in a saucepan; bring to a boil, stirring frequently, and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, vanilla and cereal.
Blend well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper and let cool until firm.

title: hot wings
directions: Soak wings overnight.
Bake 40 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: tiramisu
directions: Start 3 hours before serving.
In large bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat cream cheese with 3 tablespoons milk until smooth and fluffy.
Add confectioners sugar and beat in with 3 tablespoons coffee flavored liqueur and 1 teaspoon vanilla extract.
Stir 2/3 grated chocolate.
Set aside remaining chocolate for top of dessert.

title: tropical salad
directions: Peel and dice bananas and oranges; mix lightly with meat, pineapple and celery.
Combine mustard with mayonnaise and blend with banana mixture.
Serve on lettuce.
Garnish with olives and walnuts.
Serves 6.

title: candied nuts
directions: Beat egg white and water together until frothy.
Add rest of ingredients and put flat side down on buttered cookie sheet.
Bake in 250° oven for 1 hour.
Remove from pan immediately or they'll stick.

title: french fudge
directions: In
top of double boiler, melt chocolate chips.
Remove from heat; add Eagle Brand milk, vanilla, salt and nuts.
Stir until smooth.
Turn into waxed paper lined 8-inch square pan. Chill. Cut and store in airtight container.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix ingredients in order given. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Sprinkle top with coconut.

title: chocolate heaven cake
directions: Mix together 2 minutes; pour in Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool for 15 minutes.
Take out of pan.

title: "old virginia" scrapple
directions: Brown onions in fat. Add meat.
Fry out somewhat. Add tomatoes, mushrooms, corn meal and 1 teaspoon salt and pepper to taste. Simmer 2 hours over low heat.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Melt butterscotch in a double boiler until in liquid form. Add string potatoes and peanuts and mix together thoroughly. Spoon out on wax paper.
Let cool until hardened.

title: rouladen(spicy stuffed beef rolls)
directions: Trim fat off top round slices and pound to 1/4 inch thick.
Cut out 6 rectangles, about 4 x 8-inches each.
Spread a teaspoon of mustard on each piece and sprinkle with 2 teaspoons of chopped onion.
Place a slice of bacon along center of each strip.
Place pickle halves along narrow ends of each strip and roll meat around pickle jelly roll style.
Tie ends of each roll with kitchen cord and fry in oil in heavy skillet or pot quickly until brown on all sides.
Add celery, water and salt.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour, turning rolls once or twice.
Serves 6.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash potatoes.
Add milk, nutmeg and raisins.
Pour into large greased casserole dish.
Top with butter, brown sugar and marshmallows.
Bake for 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: dad's easy goulash casserole
directions: Start water boiling for 2 cups of macaroni.
Start frying ground beef and turkey.
Add a small onion or dried crushed onion, if desired.
Start these cooking.
Put a can of cream-style corn in a large casserole.
Add paprika and red pepper.
Stir the pepper well into the corn to avoid hot lumps.
Add tomato soup; stir again.
Stir in Parmesan cheese.
(Cheese can be sprinkled on top if the oven is used.)
Add Worcestershire sauce.
Combine all ingredients and heat in oven for 20 minutes at 350° or microwave until hot.

title: smothered steak
directions: Place layer of onions in bottom of crock-pot.
Mix flour, salt, pepper and paprika together and dredge steak pieces until lightly coated with flour mixture.
Place 1/2 of meat pieces on onions.
Add another layer of onions and drained mushrooms.
Add remaining meat and onions.
Mix beef broth, Worcestershire and Kitchen Bouquet.
Pour over entire meat mixture.
Cover and cook on low for 8 hours.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Cook until thick and clear.
Pour over oatmeal mixture. Sprinkle with rest of the crumbly mix.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: spanish stuffed peppers
directions: Cut green peppers in half lengthwise.
Steam peppers with 1-inch water in pan for 5 minutes.
Cool quickly.
Brown beef and onion; drain fat.
Stir in rice and ketchup.
Spoon ingredients into green pepper halves.
Place peppers in baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan and Mozzarella cheeses.

title: oriental beef strips
directions: Cut meat into strips; brown in oil.
Add water, soy sauce and garlic.
Cook and simmer for 45 minutes.
Add vegetables.
Cover and continue cooking 20 minutes.
Combine cornstarch and 1/4 cup water.
Add gradually to the meat mixture, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Stir in Parmesan cheese.
Serve over rice.

title: cheesy garlic bread
directions: Slice loaf lengthwise.
Spread butter evenly over each half. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, garlic and oregano to taste.
Broil until bread is golden brown and topping is melted.
Slice into small sections.
Serve immediately.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Make roux using small amount of cooking oil and flour.
Let brown well. Add green peppers, onions and celery.
Add water and cook approximately 15 minutes. Add hot sausage, tomatoes, tomato paste and bay leaves. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Add okra, gumbo file, shrimp and crabs.
Cook for 30 minutes until done.

title: wacky cake
directions: Use ungreased 10 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Sift the following ingredients into pan:
flour, soda, salt, white sugar and cocoa. Make a well in the dry ingredients and pour in the following: vinegar, vanilla, oleo and cold water.
Mix thoroughly with spoon or fork.
Drop pan sharply on table and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cream puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In saucepan, heat water and margarine to boiling.
Stir in flour and salt briskly.
Beat until mixture forms a ball and leaves sides of pan.
Remove from heat.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, beating hard after each addition.
Drop by teaspoons onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake 30 minutes.
Split and fill with chicken or crab salad.
Also good with chocolate or vanilla pudding.
Makes 35 puffs.

title: stuffed mushroom caps
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms.
Rinse in colander.
Finely chop stems.
In skillet, heat margarine.
Combine all ingredients except mushroom caps.
Fry 4 to 5 minutes, stirring frequently. Remove from heat.

title: apple pie cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pa dutch pepper and onions
directions: Slice onions and peppers; sprinkle with salt (easy on the salt).
Bring the rest of the ingredients to a boil, then add peppers and onions.
Cook until tender.
Cold pack can.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Dry Mix:
Sift together the flour, sugar, cinnamon, baking soda and salt into a large bowl.
Add the fruit, carrots and nuts and stir to combine.

title: dirty rice
directions: Spray 1 qt. casserole dish and place ingredients in dish, cover. Bake 1 hour at 350°. ENJOY!

title: potato salad
directions: Combine Miracle Whip, vinegar, sugar, salt/pepper, milk and food coloring. Add potatoes, eggs and onions; mix well. Refrigerate.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs until frothy.
Beat in sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat mixture until thickened and lemon colored.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Fold in zucchini and nuts.
Pour into 2 oiled and floured loaf pans.
Bake 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Put on rack.
Freezes well.

title: date cake
directions: Good for holidays and to bake in small tins to share with friends.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cook fettuccine in a large pot per directions on package. Drain well and return to pot.
Melt margarine in a saucepan and add garlic powder.
Add to fettuccine.
Gradually add whipping cream, 1/2 cup of Parmesan cheese, sugar and sour cream.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thoroughly heated.
Be careful as this scorches and sticks easy!
Remove from heat and serve immediately.
Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper to taste.
This is a good basic white cream sauce pasta dish that you can experiment with.
Add cooked and diced clams, shrimp, crab meat, etc.

title: cream puffs
directions: Melt margarine in water.
Add flour and salt all at once. Stir vigorously.
Cook and stir until mixture forms a ball that doesn't separate.
Remove from heat.
Cool slightly.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each until smooth.
Drop on greased sheet.
Bake at 400° until brown and puffy, about 30 minutes. Remove from oven; split.
Cool on racks.

title: mexican corn-on-the-cob
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (180°C) or prepare barbecue.
Mix together butter, chili powder, paprika, salt and pepper.
Spread on corn; wrap in heavy foil and seal well.
Place in baking dish and bake or barbecue for 1 hour, or until corn is tender.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Bake 45 minutes at 400°.
The last 2 or 3 minutes cooking, put cheese on top.

title: yeast dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Scald milk and cool. Add water, cooled shortening, sugar, salt and the yeast.
Mix well and add enough flour to make a slightly firm dough, about 6 cups. Let rise until double in bulk.
Then make into desired roll shapes and let rise until double. Bake at 400° until golden brown.
Brush with melted butter.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix jello and cottage cheese together.
Add pineapple and Cool Whip.
Mix and chill.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into baking dish. Crumble Ritz crackers over top of mixture.
Melt butter and pour over crackers. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: twenty-four hour layered salad
directions: Fill a large rectangular ovenproof glass dish 2/3 full of lettuce.
Layer green pepper, celery, water chestnuts and peas. Spread mayonnaise over top layer.
Sprinkle sugar and Cheddar cheese over mayonnaise.
Press down into cheese the bacon bits. Cover tightly with plastic wrap and foil.
Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.

title: breakfast drink
directions: Blend all of the ingredients in a blender.
Pour into 3 (10 ounce) glasses.
Garnish with fresh mint, if available.

title: golden cheese bake
directions: Toss together all ingredients, except 1/2 cup of cheese.
Pour in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top. Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove cover and bake for 30 minutes longer.

title: cheese log(club member: keisha hudson)
directions: Allow cheese to reach room temperature. Mix together and sprinkle with garlic salt. Roll into log. Roll log in chopped pecans and sprinkle with paprika.

title: peanut butter munchies
directions: Bring syrup and sugar to boil; remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter.
Mix well.
Add coconut and corn flakes.
Mix well. Roll in small balls and press flat (with bottom of a glass). Place on wax paper.
Put wax paper between layers of cookies.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Steam carrots until tender.
Drain in a pan; mix butter, sugar and nutmeg.
Stir in carrots and heat until glazed.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Combine sugar, paprika, salt and vinegar.
Add oil, celery seed and honey.
Beat well.
Add Miracle Whip; stir until well blended.
Refrigerate.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix all ingredients well and store in an airtight container.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine ingredients and pour over tortillas.
Top with 1 to 2 tablespoons chopped jalapeno peppers, chopped tomatoes and 1/2 cup shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cappuccino
directions: Prepare coffee in automatic coffeemaker using amounts of coffee and water given.

title: pea soup
directions: Cover ham bone with water and add the peas, celery and parsley.
Simmer until peas are soft enough to put through sieve. Fry the onion in butter until slightly burned; add to soup and continue to simmer for half hour.
Brown the flour lightly in butter and add to soup.
Serve with grated cheese or croutons.

title: orange cream crush
directions: Combine juice, water, sugar, milk and vanilla in blender.
Add ice and blend until slush consistency.
Serves 4 or 5.

title: guacamole
directions: Scoop out inside of avocados; mash.
Add lemon juice to keep from browning and add rest of ingredients.
Serve with tortilla chips and melted cheese for your favorite Mexican foods!

title: filled cookie tarts
directions: Mix Crisco and dry ingredients.
Make a well in the center and add beaten eggs and orange juice.
Mix well.
Place small balls of dough in tea cake pans.
Flatten out the dough in tins to form small tarts.
Fill with pie filling (cherry or blueberry).
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.
Makes 48 to 50 tarts.

title: strawberry mousse
directions: Reserve several strawberries for garnish.
Press the remaining berries through fine sieve.
Add sugar and white wine.
Stir well and chill.
Soften gelatin in the cold water.
Add boiling water and stir to dissolve.
Cool.
Combine gelatin and chilled strawberry mixture.
Beat with rotary beater until fluffy and slightly thickened.
Fold in whipped cream.
Turn into a 2-quart oiled mold.
Chill for 3 hours or longer.
Unmold onto a chilled serving platter.
Garnish with reserved whole strawberries.

title: slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, onion, carrot and green pepper.
Set aside. Mix vinegar and eggs together and beat.
Add sugar and cook until thick and let mixture cool.
Pour over chopped cabbage mixture.

title: french breakfast puffs
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of muffin cups or use paper liners.
Mix shortening, 1/2 cup sugar and egg thoroughly. Measure flour by dip-level-pour method or by sifting.
Blend flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Stir in alternately with milk.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Immediately roll in melted butter, then in sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Serve hot.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: brown rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix
all ingredients and pour into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan. Melt
stick
margarine
and
pour
over pumpkin mixture. Sprinkle on that 1 cup chopped nuts.
Sprinkle 1/2 box yellow cake
mix (dry)
over next.
Bake at 300° for approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: satsuma age
directions: Grind
fish meat in suribachi or food processor.
While grinding,
add
sugar
and	mix
well.
Combine cornstarch and water.
Add to fish mixture and mix to make it soft.
Add salt and mix until it becomes firmer.
Add egg and mix well before adding the
shredded gobo and carrots.
Make patties and deep fry in hot cooking oil until golden brown.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Melt chocolate over low heat.
Add peanut butter, then add nuts.
Pour over marshmallows that are in a 9 x 9-inch pan lined with wax paper.

title: chicken lucy
directions: Cut chicken into bite-size pieces and soak in eggs for 1/2 hour.
Bread chicken and fry in oil until golden brown.
Drain and set aside.
In large casserole, add mushrooms, sliced onions, cheese and tomatoes.
Mix well, then add chicken.
Bake at 350° until onions are soft and serve with vegetables, rice or potatoes.

title: old fashion tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together; add eggs.
Beat until creamy.
Add 2 cups flour and milk to mixture; beat well.
Add flour and beat.
Roll to 1/4-inch thickness, then bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 36 cookies.

title: corn relish
directions: Cut corn from cob but do not scrape cob.
Mix with onions, peppers and cabbage.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Cook slowly for 1 hour; stir occasionally.
Turn into sterilized jars and seal at once.
Makes 5 (1/2 pint) jars.

title: mother goose popcorn
directions: Bring ingredients (except popcorn) to a full boil.
Add several drops of food coloring of your choice and vanilla.
Pour over popped corn.
Serves 12.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Use only real mayonnaise, not Miracle Whip.

title: ice cream punch
directions: Spoon ice cream by tablespoon into a large lunch bowl.
Add water and lemonade concentrate; stir.
Slowly pour carbonated beverage down side of bowl.
Stir gently.

title: weight watchers skillet lasagna
directions: You can make this in a skillet with a cover or a casserole dish.

title: apple oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg, vanilla and milk.
Add flour, cinnamon, and soda.
Stir in oatmeal, raisins, nuts, and apples.

title: ham 'n biscuit appetizers
directions: Split entire package of Tatum rolls in half.
Put layer of cheese, layer of ham, another layer of cheese on bottom half of rolls.
Put top layer of rolls on.
Melt butter and stir in Worcestershire, mustard, onions and poppy seed.
Pour on top. Cover with foil and bake in 350° oven until cheese melts.
Cut into individual servings.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Melt oleo, cocoa and milk.
Add confectioners sugar, vanilla and nuts.
Pour over cake while cake is still hot.

title: seven-layer salad
directions: Arrange the first 6 ingredients in layers in a glass 9 x13-inch pan.

title: orange salad
directions: Drain juice from oranges and mix with water to make 1 cup. Add to Jell-O mixture and add cream cheese and Dream Whip to Jell-O.
Add mandarin oranges.

title: goldenrod eggs (breakfast)
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add flour slowly, stirring to keep it smooth, over low heat.
Add milk slowly, also stirring to keep smooth.
Cook to a low boil and until it starts to thicken. Separate the egg yolks from the whites.
Chop up the whites and add to the sauce mixture.
Cook until bubbly.
Add the salt and pepper. Serve over toast.
Sprinkle the egg yolks "goldenrod" over the sauce.

title: lentil soup
directions: Soak lentils overnight in 2 cups water.
Saute onion, garlic, celery and carrots in oil.
Add drained lentils, 6 cups of water, salt, pepper, tomato paste, bay leaves and oregano.
Bring to a boil.
Cook until lentils are soft.
Remove bay leaves.
Add vinegar.

title: prune bread
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well.
Sift together flour, cinnamon, cloves, allspice and soda; add to sugar, oil and eggs along with buttermilk.
Fold in nuts, vanilla and prunes.
Cook in one large loaf pan for 1 hour or 3 medium pans for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: jackpot drop cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix ingredients and form into balls.
Broil in oven until brown; drain off grease.
Mix sauce ingredients and pour over meatballs.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Combine sugar, brown sugar, butter, cream and syrup; bring to boil, then to soft ball.
Pour into mixer.
Combine with marshmallow cream and peanut butter; mix until candy begins to cake.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottoms only of 2 loaf pans.
Mix sugar and shortening in 2 1/2-quart bowl.
Stir in pumpkin, water and eggs.
Mix together flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, cloves and baking powder.
Stir into wet ingredients.
Pour into pans evenly.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, about 70 minutes.
Loosen sides of loaves after five minutes, then remove from pans.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Combine hot water, salt, sugar and oil.
Cool to lukewarm. Add beaten eggs.
Dissolve yeast in the 2 tablespoons warm water and add to the first mixture.
Stir in enough flour to mix well; beat well and then add enough flour until dough is easy to handle. Turn on floured board and knead.
Place in a bowl; allow to rise until dough has doubled in bulk.
Make into rolls.
Brush with melted butter.
Let rise in a warm place.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 400°.

title: unbaked fruit cake
directions: Crush 1/2 package graham crackers with your rolling pin into small pieces. The rest of the crackers are to be crushed into fine powder. Mix the coarsely crushed crackers in a bowl together with the chopped prunes, marshmallows, chopped walnuts and condensed milk. Mix well and roll up one handful and shape like a jumbo hot dog and roll it into the finely crushed crackers. Then wrap it in aluminum foil and store in your freezer.

title: banana crush
directions: Boil sugar and water for 3 minutes.
Mix orange juice, lemon juice, pineapple juice and bananas until smooth.
Stir in syrup. Freeze.

title: spanish rice with beef
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and green pepper in Dutch oven. Drain off fat; pat meat with paper towel.
Return meat to Dutch oven; stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes, or until rice is tender, stirring occasionally.

title: green vegetable salad
directions: In large bowl, mix together green beans, peas, corn, celery, green pepper, onions and pimentos.
In saucepan, mix together sugar, oil, vinegar, salt, black pepper and water; cook over heat until mixture boils.
Cool completely before pouring over vegetable mixture.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: date and nut dream squares
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine cake mix, pudding mix and butter.
Add first egg.
Mix well until crumbly, about 1 minute. Save 1/2 cup of crumbs for top.
Put remaining crumbs in a cake tin, 13 x 9 x 2-inch (greased).
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes; press in pan.

title: whipped cream pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream the sugar with softened butter. Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour and add alternately with whipping cream.
When combined, add extracts.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan and bake for 1 hour and 25 minutes. Cool on rack for 10 minutes while in the pan.
Ideal for freezing.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cook the juice of the pineapple with the orange juice and cornstarch until the mixture thickens.
Cool.
Add the pineapple chunks and the other favorite fruits.
When ready to serve, add bananas, marshmallows and pecans.
Serves many.

title: crab gumbo
directions: Boil crabs in approximately 3 quarts water for about 15 minutes.
Make dark roux by browning flour in 2 tablespoons oil; set aside.
Smother okra in 2 tablespoons oil, adding tomatoes when okra is nearly cooked.
Add all ingredients to boiling crabs. Cover and cook slowly 30 minutes.
Add liquid crab boil to taste.

title: garlic tomatoes
directions: Quarter the tomatoes.
Mix the remaining ingredients.
Cover tomatoes with ingredients and let stand at least 2 hours.

title: grilled skewered marinated shrimp
directions: Remove shell to tail.
Remove black vein and wash shrimp. Combine butter, oil, garlic, wine, beer and cognac in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Skewer shrimp and lay flat in a shallow pan. Pour hot marinade over shrimp.
Add parsley, cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Grill 4 minutes per side over hot coals. Heat marinade left in pan and serve with shrimp.
Serves 6.

title: potato supreme
directions: Bake potatoes; peel and slice.
Place in bottom of baking dish.
Saute onion and green pepper.
Pour over potatoes. Sprinkle tomato over top.
Cover with white sauce.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake until cheese bubbles at 350° (about 20 minutes).

title: country breakfast
directions: Cook bacon until crisp and remove from skillet.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons bacon fat.
Add potatoes, season with salt and pepper and cook according to directions on potato package. Carefully break 6 eggs over potatoes.
Cover and cook until egg whites are firm.
Garnish with bacon strips and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Cover and heat a moment longer until cheese just begins to melt.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Melt the margarine.
Stir in brown sugar and white syrup (or honey).
Stirring constantly, bring to a boil.
Then remove from heat and add soda and vanilla.
Stir well and pour over popcorn. Stir until all syrup has coated the corn.
Then pour into 2 large cake pans.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Take out and cool.
Then break apart.

title: sunday morning brunch dish
directions: Mix together eggs, milk, salt, mustard and soup.
Layer bread, sausage, cheese and egg mix in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° (covered) for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crust on a cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°. Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and Italian dressing mix.
Spread over cooled crust.
Sprinkle chopped vegetables over cream cheese mixture.
Press down into mixture.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Before serving, place under broiler until cheese begins to melt. Cool and slice in serving strips.

title: rum cake
directions: Combine and beat for two minutes.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan and bake at 325° for 55 minutes.
Remove from oven.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Pour milk over bread crumbs or bread slices.
Add meat, salt and pepper and shape into balls or a loaf and put in a shallow pan.
Combine other ingredients and pour over the meatballs or loaf.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Baste occasionally.

title: round rye dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Hollow out center of bread and cut into bite size pieces (put aside).
Put dip into bread and wrap with foil.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cut second rye into pieces for additional bread.
Serve warm or cold.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown together bacon, ground beef and onions.
(Drain excess fat.)
Add sugar, catsup, vinegar, mustard, salt and the beans. Mix well.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift
flour,
sugar,
salt
and
soda together.
Cut in shortening; add yeast and buttermilk.
Combine and knead well. Let chill 1 hour.
Roll out dough on lightly floured surface. Cut out biscuits and let rise in warm place for 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Dough may be covered and refrigerated for a week.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream shortening; sift in dry ingredients.
Add bananas and half the buttermilk; mix until flour is dampened.
Then beat with mixer on high speed for 2 minutes.
Add remaining buttermilk and eggs; beat 2 minutes more.
Fold in nuts.
Bake in greased 9-inch pans at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove and cool.
Spread one layer with 1/3 cup of Cocoa Whipped Cream and top with banana slices.
Add second layer; frost tops and sides with remainder of whipped topping.

title: wine biscuits
directions: Mix wine, sugar, oil, baking powder and salt together. Gradually add flour to make a moist dough.
Roll and shape.
Bake at 375° about 20 minutes.
Do not open oven door for the first 15 minutes.

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind peppers in food grinder or food processor.
Pour boiling water over this and let stand 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Bring to boil sugar, vinegar and salt.
Add peppers and boil 5 minutes. Put into pint jars and seal.
Process in boiling water bath 10 minutes.

title: cherry scones
directions: Preheat oven to 375°; grease cookie sheet.
Combine egg, buttermilk, vanilla and cherries in bowl; let stand 5 minutes. Stir flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt in large bowl.
With pastry blender or 2 knives, cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in cherry mixture until moistened.
On lightly floured surface, knead dough 6 to 8 turns. With lightly floured rolling pin, roll dough 1 inch thick.
Cut scones with lightly floured 2 inch biscuit cutter and transfer to prepared cookie sheet.
Reroll scraps and repeat.
Brush tops lightly with egg glaze.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes, until golden. Cool on wire racks.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: peanut butter fudge(in electric skillet)
directions: Set electric skillet on 325°.
Add sugar, evaporated milk and margarine.	Stir until mixture comes to a boil.
Let boil 5 minutes stirring constantly.
Turn skillet to off and add marshmallows, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until marshmallows have melted and all ingredients have blended together.
Pour into a buttered 8-inch or 9-inch square baking pan or dish.
Cool and cut into squares.
It is necessary to work quickly so have pan buttered and peanut butter and marshmallows measured and ready to add.

title: punch
directions: Mix all liquids together in a punch bowl.
Put large spoonful of sherbet in at last minute.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers in pickling salt for 2 hours and drain.
Heat vinegar, sugar, onion, celery salt and mustard seed to boil; pour over cucumbers.
Freeze.

title: milky way cake
directions: Combine Milky War bars and butter.
Melt over low heat and set aside to cool.
Combine Crisco and sugar.
Cream together, then add 4 eggs one at a time, buttermilk, flour, soda and chopped pecans.
Pour in 10-inch tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°. Sprinkle with powdered sugar when done.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain green beans and mix all the ingredients, saving 1/2 of the French fried onions.
Put green bean mixture in casserole dish and sprinkle rest of onions on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grate zucchini and set aside to drain.
Sift dry ingredients together and set aside.
Beat eggs until light and fluffy; add sugar, oil and vanilla to eggs.
Mix well.
Blend in sifted ingredients; add nuts.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Use 2 greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans or one long loaf pan.

title: tuna cakes
directions: Drain and flake tuna in bowl.
Add onion, egg whites, pepper and crushed crackers; mix well.
Shape into patties.
Cook in a small amount of oil in skillet over medium heat until light brown.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix berries, orange and sugar together.
Dissolve Jell-O in 3 cups hot water.
When cool, add berries mixture, pineapple and nuts.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: texas barbecue
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add black pepper.
Simmer 5 minutes. Add brown sugar, garlic, salt and vinegar; stir.
Add half of bottle of Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer a few minutes.
Add lemon and rest of Worcestershire sauce; heat.
Add butter at end. (Omit butter with pork.)

title: faye spiers' delight
directions: Put all cans in refrigerator to cool.
Let strawberries thaw. Mix all fruits together, except pudding mix.
Sprinkle pudding mix over fruit and stir.
Chill about 3 hours.

title: almond coconut bars
directions: Mix until crumbly, using hands, the coconut, crackers, 2/3 cup sugar, flour and margarine.
Put 1/2 of mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the almond filling, 1 cup sugar, eggs and the lemon and almond extract; spoon carefully over the crust.
Top the filling with the rest of the crumbs and press down gently.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: taters
directions: Melt margarine in
oven
in a 13 x 9-inch pan.	Mix all other ingredients
well and roll potatoes in mixture.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour and turn in pan about 30 minutes.

title: pizza crust
directions: In large bowl dissolve together water, sugar and yeast, then add salt, oil and flour.
Knead for 5 minutes.
Set oven at 375°. Bake for 25 minutes.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix the meats, juice, milk, eggs, crackers and spices and shape into a loaf; place into a greased pan.
Make mixture of drained crushed pineapple, mustard and brown sugar and spread across top of loaf.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes and 45 minutes at 375°.

title: sausage upside-down cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook sausage, onion and bell pepper until brown and crumbly.
Stir in flour.
Mix in tomato paste, salt, chili powder and black pepper.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cheese and spread evenly in 9-inch baking pan.

title: date-nut meringue cookies
directions: Add sugar 1 tablespoon at a time to egg whites and salt.
Fold in chopped dates and pecans.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° approximately 20 to 30 minutes.

title: quesadillas
directions: Heat tortillas, one at a time, in ungreased hot skillet until softened, about 30 seconds.
(Cover hot tortillas to prevent drying.)
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons each Cheddar and Monterey Jack cheese over half of each tortilla.
Sprinkle with tomato, green onion, chilies and salt and top with taco sauce.
Moisten edge of tortilla with water.
Fold tortilla over filling.
Pinch to seal. Secure with wooden picks.
Heat shortening (1/4-inch) until hot. Fry tortillas until golden brown, about 4 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.
Remove wooden toothpicks.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pat's easy chicken casserole
directions: Combine in large baking dish.
Sprinkle top with cheese and onion rings (can use French fried onions).
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: shrimp with lime sauce
directions: Heat olive oil in large skillet; add mushrooms and saute 1 minute. Stir in green onions, garlic and ginger.
Add chicken broth, lime juice, Worcestershire sauce and shrimp.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes or until shrimp are pink.
Meanwhile, heat evaporated milk in glass measuring cup in microwave just until bubbles appear around edge (30 seconds).
Stir milk into shrimp mixture and serve immediately over rice or noodles.
Yields 4 servings.

title: tapioca pudding
directions: Mix tapioca, sugar, salt, beaten egg and milk.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Bring to full boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.

title: easy oatmeal cake
directions: Save egg yolks for icing.
Mix dry ingredients in smaller bowl.
Add shortening, sugars, egg whites, and whole egg and add to oatmeal mixture.
Add dry ingredients.
Add vanilla and mix thoroughly.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Top with Oatmeal Cake Icing (recipe follows).

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Cool, then chill until syrupy.
Add thawed strawberries, pineapple and banana.
Spoon half of the mixture into an 8 x 8-inch dish.
Spread with sour cream and top with the rest of the gelatin mixture.
Chill until set.
Makes 12 servings.

title: crabbies(appetizer)
directions: Blend butter, cheese spread, mayonnaise, garlic salt, seasoned salt and crab.
Spread on muffin halves.
Freeze until ready to use (freeze on cookie sheet, then cut into 6 to 8 wedges and pop into plastic bag).

title: the very best peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook milk, sugars and butter together to soft ball stage (234° to 238°, use candy thermometer).
Remove from heat, add peanut butter and beat well.
Add vanilla when temperature drops.
Pour into large, buttered cake pan.
Cut when cool.
This makes a lot, about 3 pounds or more.

title: cauliflower with herb butter
directions: Remove large outer leaves of cauliflower.
Break cauliflower into flowerets.
Cook, covered, in a small amount of boiling water 8 to 10 minutes or until tender; drain.
Arrange flowerets in serving dish and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine butter, parsley, salt and basil; pour evenly over flowerets.
Garnish with lemon twists and parsley sprigs.

title: mystery salad
directions: Slice bananas in bottom of bowl.
Drain fruit; set juice aside.
Layer fruit and marshmallows over bananas.
Mix pudding with pineapple juice and juice from 1 can of the orange slices. Pour over fruit and spread evenly.
When ready to serve, toss lightly.
(Nuts or coconut can be added for variety.)

title: e. z. apple pie
directions: Mix 1/2 cup sugar, 1 tablespoon flour and cinnamon. Roll apples and place in unbaked pie shell. Cover with 1/2 cup sugar, 1/2 cup flour and butter, sliced over pie. Bake on cookie sheet at 375° until brown.

title: cherry yum-yum
directions: Will need a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.

title: corn relish
directions: In large pan add corn, grind other vegetables and add to corn. Then add other ingredients.
Cook for about 25 to 30 minutes. Pour into sterilized jars and seal.

title: black pepper steak(wok cooking)
directions: Prepare rice as directed.
Brown meat in butter.
Add the water in wok.
Cook onions until opaque. Spread rice in dish. Add onions, green pepper and meat when gravy thickens.
Pour over rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spiced orange tea
directions: Place tea bags in a big bowl.
Add cloves and cinnamon stick. Peel the oranges thinly.
With a very sharp knife, cut away all the white membrane from the peel.
Cut peel in very thin strips.
Add to bowl.
Squeeze the juice.
Heat water to boiling point.
Pour the hot water over the spices and tea bags.
Let steep for a few minutes.
Remove the tea bags; discard.
Add reserved orange juice. Strain liquid into glasses or cups and serve.
Serves 10.

title: lemon fluff
directions: For crust, combine oats, flour, brown sugar and salt in a shallow pan.
Add melted butter and mix thoroughly.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Soften gelatin in cold water.
Combine egg yolks, sugar, lemon rind and lemon juice in saucepan.
Cook over low heat until mixture boils.
Remove from heat, add softened gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Cool thoroughly.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add sugar, then beat until mixture stands in peaks.
Fold cooled gelatin mixture into beaten egg whites.
Put half of crumbs in pan, add filling and top with rest of filling.
Chill until set.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour and 1/2 teaspoon salt. Cut in 1/3 cup butter until mixture resembles coarse meal. Gradually stir in ice water until mixture forms a ball.
Roll dough out on lightly floured board to fit 10-inch pie plate. Transfer to plate and shape edges.
Saute onion in 1 tablespoon butter until tender.
Set aside to cool.
Line crust with bacon and cheese.
Combine eggs, cream, remaining salt and spices and sauteed onion.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 375° about 35 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve hot!

title: vidalia onion relish
directions: Let onions come to a boil.
Put into sterilized jars and seal.

title: raspberry jam
directions: Stir altogether and bring to boil.
Add 8 1/2 cups sugar.
Boil 8 to 9 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Skim and bottle.

title: grandma hostetter's pumpkin pie
directions: Baking Temperature: 400° and 350°.
Baking Time: 20 minutes each temperature.

title: diane's pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta as directed and let cool. Slice zucchini, mushrooms, olives and cherry tomatoes.
Add to pasta.
Stir in artichoke hearts, Parmesan cheese and Italian dressing.
Place in refrigerator.
Serve when chilled.

title: baked crab and shrimp casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except bread crumbs and butter. Pour into an ungreased 1-quart casserole dish.
Toss bread crumbs in butter; sprinkle over seafood mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients well; pour into an unbaked 9-inch pastry pie shell and bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool and top with whipped cream or ice cream.
Even served plain, nothing tops this.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Pour lukewarm milk over sugar, salt and shortening.
Soften yeast in lukewarm water and add to first mixture.
Add beaten eggs.
Beat in flour to make a soft dough.
Knead in any remaining flour.
Place in greased bowl, cover and store in refrigerator until ready to use.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in greased and floured loaf pan and bake for 30 or 40 minutes.

title: beefy spaghetti soup
directions: In large casserole combine ground beef, onion, garlic and oil. Microwave at High until meat is no longer pink, stirring once during cooking.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover. Microwave at High until spaghetti is done (around 20 to 25 minutes).
Stir occasionally.
Yields 4 servings.

title: browned butter noodles
directions: Cook noodles in water until tender; drain.
In small skillet melt butter over medium heat.
Stir and cook until light medium brown (be careful not to burn).
Pour over noodles; salt and pepper to taste.
This is a delicious Amish recipe.
Enjoy.

title: smoked salmon spread
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a medium bowl; stir well. Transfer mixture to a serving bowl; cover and chill thoroughly. Sprinkle with chopped parsley before serving.
Serve spread on Melba rounds.
Yields 16 appetizer servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and debone.
Do not add salt.
Put 1/3 crumbs in bottom of dish; add 1/2 chicken.
Mix 1 can soup and 1 cup broth and pour over.
Add 1/3 crumbs, then rest of chicken.
Mix 1 can soup and 1 1/4 cups broth and pour over.
Add remaining 1/3 crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.
This recipe freezes well.
Very good warmed over.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Chop artichokes.
Mix with mayonnaise, garlic powder and Parmesan cheese.
Put in glass baking dish.
Put in a 350° oven for 20 minutes, until brown on top.
Serve with warmed wedges of pita bread, or crackers.

title: baked beef stew
directions: Place all ingredients in roaster with lid.
Bake in 250° oven for 4 hours.
Gravy will be thick and brown when done.
Can be cooked in crock-pot all day.
Serves 6.

title: hamburg soup
directions: Brown hamburg. Add juice, water, vegetables, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook slow for 2 hours.

title: cheese soup
directions: Put the first 5 ingredients in a crock-pot.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Simmer in crock-pot for 6 hours.

title: my favorite candy
directions: Pour 3 cups melted chocolate into Rice Krispies.
Mix; add more Krispies until all of the chocolate is used up.
Spread into a square baking dish.
Spread marshmallows on top until covered. Melt white chocolate and pour 3 cups over the marshmallows. Cover well.
Let harden and cut into squares.

title: pork meatballs
directions: Can use Italian seasoning.
Meatballs can be browned in chicken fat.

title: flaky pastry
directions: With fork, mix first 4 ingredients.
In small bowl, beat 1/2 cup water and remaining ingredients together.

Add to first mixture and blend with fork until dry ingredients are moistened. With hands, mold dough into balls and chill at least 15 minutes. Dough can be stored in refrigerator up to 3 days or frozen until ready to use.
Makes 2 double crusts for 9-inch pies and one 9-inch shell.

title: quick inexpensive punch(serves 40)
directions: Dissolve sugar in boiling water.
Let cool.
Mix all ingredients except strawberries.
Pour over ice cubes.
Add frozen berries.
Serve when chilled.

title: cheese dip
directions: Line pan with cream cheese.
Top with chili, Jack cheese and olives.
Heat in oven until cheese melts.
Serve with corn chips.

title: cabbage and cheese casserole
directions: I use lo-cal cheese (white).

title: pecan squares
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar.
Add the flour and salt.
Press firmly into greased 10 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes or until golden brown.
While this is cooking, prepare filling.

title: baked nuts
directions: Add dry ingredients to beaten egg.
Beat together until light and cream.
Add nuts and mix well.
Spread into buttered pan. Bake in oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Bake at 350°.

title: hot squash casserole
directions: Combine squash, chiles, salt, black pepper, and cheese, mixing lightly but thoroughly.
Pour squash mixture into 2 quart casserole prepared with non stick vegetable spray.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for
30 minutes or until cheese is melted and bubbly.
Yield: 10 to 12 servings.

title: gooey caramel brownies
directions: Unwrap caramels and melt in top of double boiler with 1/3 cup of evaporated milk; set aside.
Mix together the cake mix, remaining 1/3 cup evaporated milk, 1 cup chocolate chips, nuts and melted butter.
Mix dough until it holds together.
Press 1/2 of dough into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Spread caramel mixture over the top.
Sprinkle with remaining chocolate chips.
Put remaining half of dough on top.
(You have to do this in "pinches".)
Return to oven and bake an additional 15 to 18 minutes.
Cool; refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Cut into bars.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: chicken-mushroom-wild rice casserole
directions: Simmer chicken breasts in onion, celery, wine and water until tender.
Strain broth and bone chicken.
Cool chicken and broth.

title: catsup
directions: Boil 20 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 quarts.

title: bean dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Mozzarella cheese.
Put in baking dish and bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.
Top with Mozzarella cheese. Bake a few minutes more, until cheese melts.
Dip tortilla chips in this, then sour cream and taco sauce.

title: pork-chop-sauerkraut
directions: Salt and pepper pork chops to taste. Brown in skillet in a small amount of oil. In covered baking dish, arrange 1 layer of pork chops. Put a thin layer of sauerkraut and sprinkle brown sugar. Arrange another layer until you fill to top. Put a thin layer of sauerkraut on top. Cover and bake 30 minutes or until pork chops are tender.

title: rice pudding
directions: Slowly heat milk in heavy pan. Add rice and butter.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt half of margarine in casserole dish.
Mix in croutons on bottom of casserole dish.
Cook squash and drain well.
Mix all other ingredients.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over croutons and sprinkle reserved crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Can be prepared ahead of time.
Very good reheated (microwaved).
Can also be frozen.

title: broccoli and baby carrots with pecan-crumb topping
directions: In a 4-quart saucepan over high heat, bring 2 inches water to a boil.
Add broccoli and carrots.
Return to boil.
Cook 5 to 7 minutes until veggies are crisp-tender.
Meanwhile, in a 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat, melt butter (1/4 cup only).
Add bread crumbs; cook 5 minutes, stirring frequently, until golden and toasted.
Stir in pecans, 1/2 teaspoon salt, thyme and pepper; cook, stirring, about 1 minute longer.
Drain veggies; return to saucepan.
Toss with remaining butter.
Transfer to a serving dish. Sprinkle with crumb mixture.

title: ginger salad dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients together until smooth.

title: quick chicken pie
directions: Cook and bone chicken. Reserve 2 cups broth. Cut chicken into pieces. Place in bottom of dish. Melt butter and pour over chicken. Sift together dry ingredients and mix well with milk. Pour over chicken. Heat soup and broth to boiling and pour over all. Bake 45 minutes at 350°. (Makes own crust.)

title: onion patties
directions: In mixing bowl, combine the dry ingredients.
Stir in milk. Add a little more if needed to make a thick batter.
Mix in onions.
Heat oil to 375°.
Drop batter by tablespoonfuls into hot oil and fry to a golden brown.
Turn and brown other side.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve warm.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add other ingredients.
Stir.
Pour in pie shell. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool and serve.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until fluffy.
Add powdered sugar and peanut butter.
Add milk slowly.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in graham cracker or chocolate pie crust.
Freeze until 20 minutes before serving.

title: bread in a bag
directions: Mix 1 cup flour, yeast and 1 tablespoon sugar; add 3/4 cup water to 1 freezer-style Ziploc bag; set bag on end.
Mix well; let rest 15 minutes.

title: easy honey-baked chicken
directions: Put chicken pieces in shallow baking pan, skin side up.
Mix other ingredients well.
Pour over chicken and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours, basting every 14 minutes until chicken is tender and nicely browned.
You'll make 4 to 6 friends the easy way!

title: apple brown betty
directions: Slice apples into 1 1/2-quart greased casserole.
In a bowl, mix flour, brown sugar, margarine or butter, cinnamon and granola. Spread the crumbs over the top of apples.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: bacon and swiss dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small casserole dish.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: overnight cucumber pickle
directions: Slice cucumbers 1/2-inch thick (makes about 10 cups); place in a large bowl.
Sprinkle with salt; mix well.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Drain well.
In a large sauce pot combine vinegar, sugar, mustard seed, celery seed, ginger and turmeric; bring to a boil. Add cucumbers; simmer, covered, until crisp-tender, about 10 minutes.
Pour into a container with a tight fitting lid. Refrigerate overnight before serving.
Yield:
3 quarts.

title: lemon layer torte
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well and put into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Cool. Blend powdered sugar and cream cheese. Add Cool Whip. Blend and spread onto cooled crust. Let stand 15 minutes. Blend lemon pudding, cold milk and vanilla. Then beat 2 minutes on low speed. Spread over the cream cheese layer. This makes the third layer. Spread 8 ounces of Cool Whip over the top for the fourth layer. Sprinkle with nuts. Refrigerate.

title: "let's have a little fun" possum plank steak
directions: Place vegetables around the possum on an oak board about 1-inch thick.
Place in oven and bake for 3 hours at 350°.
After thoroughly cooking, remove the possum and allow to cool.
Then, throw the possum away.
Add catsup; salt and pepper to taste.
Eat the plank.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Add ingredients to onion and butter. Mix together. Put into casserole dish. Top with cracker crumbs and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken.
Layer casserole dish with boned chicken.
Heat together celery soup, milk and mushroom soup.
Pour over chicken. Mix stuffing mix as directed on package.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 400° until brown, approximately 15 to 20 minutes.

title: navaho-blue-corn-pancakes
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine and mix the first 5 dry ingredients. Add butter, eggs and milk and stir well. Let batter sit for a few minutes.
Spoon batter onto a medium-hot oiled skillet.
Cook until lightly brown, or about 2 minutes on each side.
Serve with honey or syrup.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate-cheesecake brownies
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease an 8-inch square baking pan.
Melt margarine in saucepan.
Remove from heat and add chocolate.
Let stand, stirring several times to melt.
Beat eggs and salt with electric mixer until frothy.
Gradually add sugar, beating about 2 minutes until pale yellow and thick.
Stir in chocolate and then flour, mixing to blend.
Spread batter evenly into prepared pan.

title: beef stew
directions: Mix all together in roaster; cover and put in oven at 275° for 4 to 5 hours.
Serves 8.

title: homecoming pound cake
directions: Cream
butter, sugar and Crisco.
Beat in eggs one at a time. Sift
flour and baking powder together.
Add to creamed mixture alternately
with
milk.
Add
vanilla.
Bake
in
2 greased and floured tube pans at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or when done.

title: honey oatmeal chews
directions: Cream butter, honey and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt. Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in oatmeal, coconut and nuts.
Spread in a greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
When cool, cut into bars about 1 1/2 x 2 1/2-inches.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Drain broccoli between paper towels.
Combine uncooked broccoli and next 5 ingredients, mixing well.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake by directions on box.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake as directed.
When done, poke holes in cake with wooden spoon handle all over cake.
Set aside.

title: brie torte
directions: Freeze cheese for 30 minutes or until very firm.
Cut in half horizontally and set aside.
Cream butter and garlic.
Mix walnuts, olives and basil and blend thoroughly.
Spread mixture evenly on 1/2 of cut side of cheese.
Top this cheese with the other half, cut side down.
Press together.
Wrap and chill. Bring to room temperature.
Makes 12 appetizers.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix together oil and sugar, then add eggs, flour, salt, soda, milk, vanilla, bananas and pecans. Pour into floured and greased loaf pan. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: collards
directions: For healthier recipe, substitute smoked turkey wings for salt pork.
Cut off and discard tough stems and discolored leaves.
Wash thoroughly.
Combine pork and water in heavy pot; bring to a boil and cook 15 to 30 minutes.
Add collards; cover and cook at low boil for 1 1/2 hours.
Add potatoes and cook 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: cookie brittle
directions: Mix butter, sugar, salt and flour.
Stir in vanilla and chocolate chips.
Pat into large cookie sheet or pizza pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes, until beginning to brown.

title: crock-pot cubed steak
directions: Pour 1 can cream of mushroom soup and cream of chicken soup in crock-pot. Put steak in pot and pour remaining cans of soup over cubed steak.
Start cooking on high until boiling, then turn temperature down to low.
Cook until steak is done.
(Can cook on low all day while you're at work!)
Delicious served with mashed potatoes.

title: dump pie
directions: Melt butter in a shallow baking pan.
In a small bowl mix flour, sugar and milk.
Pour over melted butter.
Empty cherries over this.
Then pour 1 cup sugar (another) over this.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
The flour mixture will come to the top.

title: brownies deluxe
directions: Melt butter with chocolate over warm water using a double boiler.
Beat eggs; add sugar, then flour sifted with baking powder.
Add vanilla and then nuts.
Stir well.
Then add to chocolate-butter mixture.
Pour into a greased and floured 11 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: easy 7-layer salad
directions: Assemble the salad in order in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Refrigerate.

title: best play dough
directions: Mix dry ingredients thoroughly.
Add food coloring to water and oil.
Stir into dry ingredients.
Stir over medium heat several minutes until mixture forms a ball.
Let cool in bowl and knead.
Store in airtight container.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Mix until creamy and smooth.

title: chicken pan pie
directions: Pour soup, vegetables and chunks of chicken in the unbaked pie shell.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with other pie shell. Close edges together.
Punch a few holes in top shell.
Cook in oven at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: chocolate cherry bars
directions: Mix
cake
mix, pudding, eggs and almond extract.
Fold in cherry
pie filling and milk.
(Makes a heavy batter.) Turn batter onto a
greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until cake springs back.
Cool.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots in a medium saucepan until tender.
This will take 6 to 20 minutes, depending on age of carrots.
Drain.
Mix the orange juice, sugar, cloves, salt and cheese spread.
Pour over the carrots; cook over low heat, stirring all the time, until the cheese melts and the mixture thickens.
Do not let it boil.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine together; add eggs one at a time. Sift and measure flour. Add salt and baking powder; re-sift. Add flavoring with milk. Bake in tube pan at 350° for about 1 hour (depends on your oven heat).

title: butternut cake
directions: Mix Crisco, sugar and eggs together at high speed for 5 minutes.
Add flour 1
cup at a time.
Beat one minute on high and add remainder
of
flour,
then
milk.
Beat one minute on high, add flavoring and
mix.
Bake
in 3 layers at 350° until cake begins leaving sides of pan, about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Stir together in order given.
Pour into two well-greased bread pans.

title: squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil squash in salted water in saucepan until tender; drain.
Fry bacon in skillet; crumble and add with drippings to squash.
Add onion and bell pepper; mix well. Reserve small amount of cracker crumbs for topping.
Add remaining crumbs and eggs to squash mixture; mix well.
Pour into greased 3-quart casserole.
Top with reserved crumbs.
Dot with butter; sprinkle paprika and cheese over top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes, or until done.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain beans.
Place in bowl.
Add green pepper and onion.
Mix oil and vinegar with sugar, salt and pepper.
Pour over mixture and toss well.
Refrigerate.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: In a large bowl, mix first 10 ingredients together.
Shape into balls, about 1-inch in diameter.
Brown in shortening.
Remove meat balls.
Stir flour into drippings and cook until brown.
Add water and bouillon cubes.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Reduce heat; add meat balls.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: strawberry cake no. 2
directions: In a large bowl, add the boiling water to the jello and dissolve
well.
Add
frozen
strawberries, stirring gently to separate
berries.
Put
in
freezer.
In
a bowl, break angel food
cake
into small pieces. Combine one Cool Whip, powdered sugar and
vanilla.
Mix
well.
Add nuts to jello mixture and pour over
cake.
Make
sure
each
piece
of cake is covered. Pour mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Leave in refrigerator 8 to 10 hours.
Ice with Cool Whip.

title: barley muffins with dates and walnuts
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Combine orange juice and next 3 ingredients; stir well.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened. Gently fold in dates and walnuts.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, 1 stick melted oleo and 2 teaspoons white sugar for the crust.
Cream 2 sticks (room temperature) oleo and powdered sugar.
Add vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Pour over crust.
Layer on sliced bananas.
Layer on crushed pineapple.
Layer on Cool Whip.
Top with cherries that are sliced in half.
Sprinkle on chopped fine walnuts in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: fast and fit potato chowder
directions: In microwave, melt butter in 2 1/2 to 3-quart microwave-safe dish on High 1 minute.
Add leeks and bell peppers; microwave on High 3 minutes.
Stir in potatoes, broth, thyme and bay leaves. Remove 4 cups cooked potatoes with a slotted spoon; put into electric blender.
Add milk and puree until smooth.
Return mixture to dish.
Stir in corn, parsley and cayenne season with salt and pepper.
Heat on High 3 minutes.
If desired, pass bowls of shredded Cheddar cheese, crumbled cooked bacon, drained canned clams and/or cubed cooked chicken or ham, to stir into soup.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cornish hens mandarin
directions: Combine the ingredients and marinate hens overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Bring marinade to boil, then baste hens while baking.

title: macadamia nut crunch torte
directions: Note: This is best done the night before serving.

title: original kentucky whiskey cake(a cissy gregg recipe)
directions: Soak cherries and raisins in bourbon overnight.
After flouring nuts, sift rest of flour with baking powder and nutmeg 3 times.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Add soaked fruit and remaining liquid and flour to butter, sugar, egg mixture.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Add floured pecans.
Bake in large greased tube pan (lined with brown paper, greased and floured).
Bake at 250° to 275° for 3 to 4 hours.
Watch baking time.
Cool completely and place in tightly covered container.
Stuff center hole with cheesecloth soaked in bourbon.
Wrap in heavy waxed paper.
Keep very cool.
Refrigerate if necessary.

title: pea salad
directions: Defrost the peas and combine the celery, nuts, onion and bacon bits with the peas. Prepare the dressing of sour cream and mayonnaise and add to the pea mixture. Let salad stand several hours or overnight in refrigerator.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Mix ingredients and form into balls (about 16 to 20).
Brown and drain well.
Put in casserole.
Cover with tomato sauce and water.
Put on lid and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: dilly casserole bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Combine in bowl the remaining ingredients, except flour, with yeast.
Add flour.
Cover.
Let rise in warm place 1 hour or until doubled.
Knead with a little flour and turn into well-greased 8-inch round casserole.
Let rise 30 to 40 minutes.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes and golden brown. Brush with soft butter and sprinkle with a little salt.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: garlic mashed potatoes
directions: Quarter potatoes.
Cook, covered in boiling water 20 to 25 minutes.
Peel garlic cloves and add to potatoes last 15 minutes of cooking.
Cook onion in butter until tender.
Drain potatoes and garlic.
Mash.
Add onion mixture, cheese and pepper.
Beat in enough milk to make potatoes light and fluffy (1/3 to 1/2 cup).

title: date nut fingers
directions: Melt butter, add sugar, beaten egg and dates. Cook for a few minutes until dates soften.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla,
nuts and rice cereal.
Cool slightly.
Shape into fingers and roll into coconut.
Yield: 3 to 4 dozen.

title: ice cream wafers
directions: Blend butter and sugar until creamy. Beat in egg and vanilla. Stir in flour gradually. Drop by small teaspoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet (not too close together as cookies will spread). Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Remove from cookie sheet immediately.

title: cold pizza dip
directions: Spread soft cream cheese on medium pizza pan.
Empty chili sauce on top of cream cheese and spread evenly.
Sprinkle with toppings and top with cheese.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Serve with plain tortilla chips.
Serves 4 to 8.

title: party reubens
directions: Layer by order onto cocktail rye bread.
Place in broiler until cheese melts.
Serve immediately.

title: chunk pickles
directions: Cut cucumbers in chunks or slice.
Soak in salt water 5 hours or overnight 7
tablespoons
salt to 2 1/2 quarts water. Covers about same
amount
as
vinegar
mixture.
Boil
water, vinegar, sugar and
spices.
After
liquid
boils, add drained pickles and heat.
Do not boil.
Seal in hot jars.

title: easy brownies
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes in an 8-inch square pan.
(One-half cup of chopped nuts may be added but these brownies are delicious without nuts.)

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Lightly brown chicken in oil.
In same oil, saute onion, celery, green pepper and carrot until tender.
Stir in tomatoes. Season with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Return chicken pieces to sauce.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve sauce over hot cooked fettuccini.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate milk shake
directions: Put cold milk and chocolate syrup in mixing cup.
Add 2 to 4 scoops vanilla ice cream, depending on thickness you like best. Mix just enough to blend.

title: zucchini jam
directions: Cook first
4 ingredients, boil for 8 minutes. Add jello, seal and store in cool place. Can be frozen also.

title: tea time toast
directions: Combine yeast in warm water with pinch of sugar; set aside. In a large bowl, mix corn meal, hot water, milk, sugar, salt, butter, egg and yeast.
Mix well.
Add flour and soda; knead for 5 minutes.
Place dough in greased bowl and let rise 2 hours. Repeat; let rise second time for 1 hour.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
I use pie pans.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread in ungreased loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Cook, uncovered, in a 350° oven until done, about 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: souper scalloped potatoes
directions: Stir soup blend in milk and pepper.
Arrange alternate layers of potatoes, onion and sauce in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Dot top with butter.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Uncover; bake 15 more minutes.
Makes about 3 1/2 cups.

title: 60-minute yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and 1/2 teaspoon sugar in water.
Beat egg; add to milk.
Combine yeast and milk.
Add butter and dry ingredients. Allow to stand for 15 minutes.
Shape in half the size you want the finished roll to be.
Let rise in pan to double in size.
Bake for 15 minutes at 375° or until golden brown.

title: "thrive on five" bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients; set aside.
Mix oil, egg and molasses. Add vegetables.
Gradually add dry ingredients into egg mixture. Pour into a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan, lightly oiled.

title: greek wedding cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar, egg and vanilla thoroughly.
Blend in flour, baking powder and nuts.
Heat oven to 300°; shape dough in a round ball about the size of a large cherry or a crescent shape and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Press clove into the center of each. Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until set, but do not brown.
Cool.
Dust confectioners sugar over all.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: chicken reuben
directions: Place chicken in greased 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Cover with sauerkraut.
Layer cheese on top.
Pour Russian dressing on and sprinkle with parsley.
Bake, uncovered, 90 minutes at 325° or until chicken is tender and cooked through.

title: crab quiche
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
In a separate bowl combine remaining ingredients.
Mix together.
Spoon into the 2 pie shells. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: marinated turkey
directions: Slice turkey breast in slices 1/2 to 3/4-inch thick.
Mix marinade.
Marinate turkey for at least two hours.
Turn turkey a time or two or put in container with tight-sealing lid and turn over.
Place turkey on grill; baste occasionally.
Turn once. (Grill about 8 to 10 minutes per side, depending on thickness of slices.)
Fresh turkey may be sliced and frozen (put on cookie sheet with wax paper between layers until frozen).
To fix quantity desired, mix a proportional amount of marinade.

title: angel rolls
directions: Mix flour and sugar together, then cut in shortening. Dissolve yeast in warm water; add to mixture with buttermilk.
Mix together, then knead.
Store in refrigerator in covered bowl. Shape into rolls or biscuits.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Blend dry ingredients with shortening; add egg and liquids. Form into a roll.
Wrap in wax paper.
Store in refrigerator.
Take off as much as you need.
Warm to room temperature.
Roll on heavily floured board.
Bake as usual for pie crust.
This is enough for 3 pie crusts.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into small bite size pieces. This should take about 2 months. Add enough brown gravy to cover.
Cook over charcoal fire for 4 weeks at 465°.
This will serve 3,300 people. If more are expected, 2 rabbits may be added.
Do this only as necessary as most people do not like to find hare in their stew.

title: salvation army doughnuts
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and lard; mix rest of the dry ingredients
Combine the two mixtures with the milk.
Knead slightly.
Pat and roll into 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut or shape into form.
Fry in deep hot oil.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: glazed fruit(peaches, pears, apricots, etc.)
directions: Drain fruit.
Put fruit into a large skillet or saucepan with juice, brown sugar and butter.
Heat slowly at a simmer, turning fruit often until glazed all over.
Drain.
Stick whole cloves in end and use to garnish poultry or pork.
Is good just as a fruit dish, especially in the winter.

title: glazed ham with sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat broiler. Place oven rack about 4 inches from heat source. Place ham in shallow pan, surrounded with peaches and sweet potatoes. Drizzle peaches and sweet potatoes with 1 tablespoon syrup. Broil 5 minutes until browned.

title: helene white's imperial crab
directions: Mix all ingredients together except for crab meat.
If mixture is too dry, add more mayonnaise and a little milk to make moist. Mixture must be moist.
Add crab, but do not overmix.
Keep crab as whole as possible.
Bake in greased casserole dish, uncovered. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, until brown.

title: napoleon creams candy
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in top of double boiler.
Cook over hot water until butter melts.
Add egg, cook and stir until thick, 3 minutes.
Add crumbs and coconut.
Press into buttered 9-inch square pan.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Blend sugar and Crisco.
Add egg, milk with baking soda and vanilla.
Beat well.
Mix in flour, a little at a time, making dough pretty stiff.
Roll out and cut.
Sprinkle dough with sugar. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: orange pecans
directions: In large Teflon coated skillet, mix orange juice, sugar, and orange rind together over medium heat.
Continually stir until mixture begins to boil.
Add pecans and continue stirring until nuts absorb all the liquid.
Remove from heat and stir until sugar coating crystallizes.
Spread on cookie sheets to cool.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: In skillet, brown chicken in oil.
Remove the chicken.
In same skillet, cook the onions and garlic until tender.
Return chicken to skillet.
Combine undrained tomatoes and rest of ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes. Stir in wine and cook, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Turn often. Remove bay leaves before serving.

title: quick caramel rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Place butter in a 9 x 13 pan. Heat in oven until melted. Sprinkle with pecans; add caramel topping and stir together. Remove dough from tubes (DO NOT UNROLL). Cut each section into 6 rolls. Arrange rolls in prepared pan with cut side down. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown. Immediately invert onto serving plate.

title: surprise steaks in oil
directions: Take steaks, cut them to smithe-reens.
Put them in a pot. Pour oil in the pot.
Cook for 3 hours.
Take out; pour dip stuff on top.
Then you are ready to eat them.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Combine 1/2 cup sugar, milk and peanut butter in bowl; mix well.
Shape into balls.
Roll in 1/2 cup sugar, coating well. Store in airtight container.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Brown onion and pepper in the butter.
Mix ingredients; add to onion, pepper and butter.
Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: malfatti
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients and roll into fingers, then into flour.
Place on a cookie sheet and chill until very cold.
In a skillet bring several inches of water to a rolling boil.
Place fingers into water and leave until they come to the top.
With a slotted spoon, remove from water.
Serve them with meat sauce covering.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onions and garlic in butter until tender.
Add the remaining ingredients for sauce and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: virginia chunk sweet pickles
directions: *Use 75 cucumbers, 4 or 5 inches long, or 2 gallons small cucumbers.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Mix water, pudding and milk; let stand 5 minutes.
Whip whipping cream to stiff peaks and fold into pudding mixture. Layer sliced bananas, vanilla wafers and pudding mixture, alternately, in serving dish.
Refrigerate at least an hour before serving.

title: hand cubed steak
directions: Brown steaks in a skillet.
Put in a slow cooker and cover with mushroom soup.
Cook for 8 hours on low.
More soup can be added for gravy.
Quick and easy for a fast dinner.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni and onion; drain.
Add other ingredients, especially cheese, while noodles are hot.

title: chipped beef log
directions: Mix all ingredients well and form into a log.
Serve with crackers.
Can be formed into a ball or to make finger sandwiches.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Fold together whipped topping and condensed milk.
Add pineapple, strawberries and bananas.
Pour into serving dish and freeze until firm.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt chips in microwave. Stir in peanuts and chow mein noodles. Drop by tablespoon onto waxed paper. Refrigerate until firm. Makes 2 dozen.

title: mocoa mix
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Store in airtight jar.
To use, place 2 rounded teaspoon fulls in a cup of boiling water.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain
pineapple
and
reserve 3 tablespoons juice. Mix sugar, flour,
juice
and
margarine.
Heat
until
bubbles. Remove from
heat	and
stir
in cheese. Stir until dissolved. Pour over pineapple
in baking dish and top with 1/2 cup Ritz cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Place zucchini in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with onion and cheese.
Beat eggs; add oil.
Mix dry ingredients and add egg mixture. Stir well.
Pour over zucchini.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: basic pesto sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender and whirl smooth.
Toss well over hot cooked pasta.
Add additional cheese, if desired. Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: breakfast ring
directions: Grease Bundt pan. Sprinkle bottom with pecans. Line rolls close together. Mix sugar, cinnamon and pudding together and sprinkle over rolls. Dot with butter. Cover with foil. Let stand overnight. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: superior meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
In a large shallow baking pan, shape into a loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Butter can turn boiled carrots into delicious glazed carrots.

title: cranberry fluff salad
directions: Combine cranberry sauce, marshmallows, pineapple, lemon juice and salt;
fold in whipped cream.
Chill overnight.
I usually double this for it is very popular (and so easy).

title: eye of round roast and gravy
directions: Brown roast on all sides after rubbing with salt, pepper and bouillon.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes per pound for well done meat.
For gravy, add water in desired amount.
Bring to a boil and make a paste using 1 1/2 teaspoons cornstarch and small amount of water.
Cook to desired thickness.

title: tomato macaroni bake
directions: In saucepan lightly brown onion in butter.
Stir in soup, water and 1/4 cup cheese.
Heat until cheese melts.
Blend sauce with macaroni.
Pour into a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole. Sprinkle remaining cheese and crumbs on top.
Bake in a 350° oven about 20 minutes or until nicely browned and bubbling.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add egg, vanilla and milk.
Make a paste of cocoa and hot water.
Add to sugar mixture, then beat. Add flour, baking powder, soda and salt to sugar mixture to make a stiff mixture.
Drop on cookie sheet for 7 minutes at 375°.

title: easy chocolate cherry cake
directions: Mix the ingredients and bake until cake turns loose at sides at 350°.
Can be served plain or with ice cream.
May be frosted with chocolate Cool Whip.

title: pineapple beets
directions: Drain pineapple and beets, saving juices.
Mix cornstarch with a little pineapple juice.
Add this to 1/2 cup pineapple juice and all of beet juice.
Heat, stirring constantly, until it begins to thicken.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer until heated through.

title: flower bed and beach dessert
directions: For the low-fat version of this recipe, use skim milk instead of whole milk.
