It's really very difficult to tell the difference anywhere but on your waist line.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix all together in cake pan and refrigerate overnight.
The next day, cut into pieces; roll in flour.
Brown and put in roaster.
Pour mushroom soup over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix altogether in crumbs.
Add 2 eggs alternately with 1 cup buttermilk with 1 teaspoon baking soda in it.
Add one 6 ounce package chocolate chips.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: baked chicken supreme
directions: Mix all together and marinate chicken overnight. Roll marinated chicken in Pepperidge Farm herb crumb. Place in baking dish. Pour 1/4 cup of butter over chicken. Cover and bake 45 minutes. Pour another 1/4 cup butter over chicken. Uncover and bake another 15 minutes.

title: bran muffins
directions: Let All-Bran and boiling water set for 5 minutes.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Bake in oven at 400° for 20 minutes.
You can keep batter in refrigerator for 3 to 4 weeks and bake as needed.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix together all the ingredients.
Pour into crust; bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: junk salad
directions: Drain pineapple and mix with cherry pie filling, milk and pecans.
Fold in Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: martha's lemon supreme salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, mix well and refrigerate.

title: refrigerator pickle
directions: Layer
cucumbers
and
onions
in
a
gallon glass jar. Bring remaining
ingredients to a boil.
Let ingredients boil until sugar
is dissolved good.
Then pour over the cucumbers and onions that are layered in the glass jar.
Refrigerate!

title: jambalaya
directions: You can substitute sausage or chicken instead of shrimp.

title: diet gelatin
directions: Take 2 tablespoons of the soft drink and mix with the gelatin. Pour remaining soft drink in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Add gelatin mixture to saucepan and stir until dissolved.
Chill until set.

title: lime punch
directions: Dilute the frozen juices with 6 cans of cold water.
Add lime sherbet and ginger ale.
Stir well.
Garnish with lemons or limes.

title: christmas salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except whipping cream.
Whip cream and sugar, then fold into salad.
Chill overnight.
Serves 14.

title: one dish chicken
directions: Mix stuffing, 1/2 cup boiling water and 1 tablespoon margarine. Spoon stuffing across center of 3-quart baking dish.
Place chicken on each side of stuffing and sprinkle with paprika.
Mix soup, milk and parsley; pour over chicken.
Bake covered at 400° for 15 minutes.
Bake uncovered for 15 minutes at 400°.

title: pineapple chicken
directions: Blend sugar, vinegar, garlic salt, shoyu (soy sauce) and ginger together.
Add cornstarch and water.
Blend well and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven.
Add garnish of onion, bell pepper and 1 can pineapple chunks.
Bake an additional 1/2 hour.

title: cough syrup
directions: Boil flax seed in water, then strain out seed.
Add lemon juice and honey (mix well).
Keep in a cool place.
Take 1 tablespoon every 2 or 3 hours.

title: applesauce meatballs
directions: Thoroughly, but lightly mix together all ingredients, except flour, shortening and consomme.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Roll in flour to coat lightly and brown in hot fat.
Place in baking dish, using all drippings and add consomme.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Thicken gravy; serve over noodles. Serves 8.

title: taco pie
directions: Preheat cookie sheet in oven to 400°.
Thaw pie crust 10 minutes.
Prick bottom and sides of pie crust.
Bake 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350°.
Brown meat and onion; drain fat.
Add taco seasoning mix to meat according to package directions.
Mix beans and 1/3 cup taco sauce; mix well.
Layer half of refried beans mixture in bottom of pie crust.
Top with seasoned meat, 1/2 cheese and tortilla chips.
Repeat layers.
Bake on preheated cookie sheet 20 to 25 minutes.
Top with lettuce, tomatoes, sour cream, olives, etc.

title: cherry sauce
directions: Put cherry juice, Sugar Twin and cornstarch into a 1-quart saucepan; stir to dissolve cornstarch.
Add butter; bring to boiling and boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in cherries.
Serve warm or cooled.

title: tortilla casserole
directions: Cook ground beef
and onion until meat is browned; drain.
Add enchilada sauce.
Layer in casserole dish 1 tortilla, then meat sauce.
Spread with sour cream and top with layer of Cheddar cheese.
Layer with another tortilla and repeat ending with Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan bars
directions: In medium bowl, beat together butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg, cinnamon and vanilla.
Continue beating until well blended.
Stir in flour to form soft dough.

title: spicy cranberry orange mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water in large bowl.
Stir in cranberry sauce, cold water, lemon juice, cinnamon and cloves. Refrigerate until thickened.
Stir in orange and walnuts.
Spoon into a 5-cup mold.
Refrigerate 4 hours or until firm.

title: pretzel wreath
directions: Form a circle of pretzels, using 6 on a sheet of waxed paper;1 single hole on outsides and OB on insides.
Place wax paper on plate.
Using three pretzels, dip inner sections halfway into melted chocolate.
Then place back in circle formation.
Use remaining 6 pretzels for the top layer.
Dip top half of pretzels in chocolate, then lay top of bottom section, overlapping 1 pretzel over 2 pretzels.
Put in refrigerator to set.
Weave licorice in between to form bow.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in large casserole or baking dish that has been sprayed with Pam or greased.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: general tso's chicken
directions: Cut chicken into bite-size chunks.
Mix egg and 2 tablespoons cornstarch.
Add chicken; stir until well coated.
Fry chicken in hot oil until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Do not cover. Mix together 2 tablespoons cornstarch in cool water and set aside.
Combine the soy sauce, rice vinegar, sugar, dark soy and sesaame oil.
Add 1 tablespoon oil to hot pan.
Quickly fry red pepper, onions, garlic and ginger until they become hot.
Add soy sauce mixture and bring to a boil.
Add just enough cornstarch mixture to thicken.
Stir in chicken pieces.
Serve with steamed rice.
Experiment with amounts of ingredients to get it the way you like it.

title: fresh frozen sweet corn
directions: Cut kernels from ears.
Melt butter and mix all ingredients in large roaster pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 250° for 1 hour, while stirring often.
Pour into several pans and set in ice water to cool quickly.
When cool, place in freezer bags or containers. Place in deep freeze.
To serve, just heat and ready to eat.

title: pancakes
directions: Combine dry ingredients in one bowl, the rest in another. Combine all together; stir by hand until wet.
Don't overstir. You don't have to get lumps out.
Ladle onto hot griddle at 425°, fry 1 minute and turn.

title: oreo cookie surprise
directions: Crush the Oreo cookies.
It's easiest to put them in a Ziploc bag and crush with a rolling pin.
Melt the butter and pour over cookies.
Mix well.
Place 2/3 of crushed cookies on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan; press firmly into pan.
In separate bowl, whip instant pudding and milk together.
Mix in softened cream cheese until well blended.
Add Cool Whip and blend well again.
Pour filling over cookies.
Top with remaining cookies.
Chill and enjoy.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Trim soiled leaves off cabbage and remove core.
Cover with boiling water and let stand for five minutes or until cabbage leaves are limp.
Separate leaves carefully.
Preserve five of the largest leaves for rolls.

title: clam chowder
directions: Dice salt pork and cook until crisp in saucepan; remove pork scraps.
Saute onion in pork fat or butter until golden.
Add potatoes and just enough water to be seen.
Season with salt and pepper to taste, then cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and simmer until potatoes are tender.
Add clams; let simmer for 2 minutes on low heat.
Add hot milk and serve.

title: garlic cheese grits
directions: Cook grits in boiling water about 30 minutes.
Crumble in cheese and butter.
Blend eggs and milk and mix with grits.
Pour in greased 2 quart casserole and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with additional 1/2 cup Cheddar and bake 15 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine and simmer in a large saucepan until an oatmeal like consistency (about 45 minutes).
Do not overcook.
Stir frequently so the pudding does not stick to the pan.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt 3 or 4 times (important). Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, beating good. Add vanilla.
Fold in flour, alternating with sour cream.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 300°.

title: cherry salad
directions: Thaw Cool Whip and add small amounts of ingredients, folding after each addition.
May add nuts, if desired.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans and place in casserole.
Stir in mushroom soup. Put 1/2 can of onion rings in beans and mix well.
Cut up half of cheese and mix in beans.
Then put remaining cheese, sliced thin, on top of beans.
Bake at 350° until it starts to bubble.
Remove and add remaining onion rings and return to oven until top is brown.

title: congo squares
directions: Melt shortening and stir in brown sugar.
Cool slightly.
Add the eggs, beaten one at a time.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt and add to egg mixture.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into greased and wax paper lined pan, 10 x 1-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheese 'n' crab appetizers
directions: In medium bowl, combine soup, green onion, pimento and hot sauce.
Fold in crab meat.
Spread this mixture evenly over the 12 muffin halves. Place on baking sheets.

title: patio potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water to cover, about 30 minutes. Drain and cool slightly.
Peel and cut into 1/2-inch cubes. Combine potatoes, chopped eggs, pickles and salad dressing which follows.
Toss gently.
Cover and chill. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Layer in order given in casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: frost for cake
directions: Combine milk, sugar, margarine, egg yolks and vanilla in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat about 12 minutes or until mixture thickens; remove from heat and add coconut.
Beat until cool.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Mix the flour, sugar and milk. Melt butter in pan. Pour in batter. Pour peaches over batter. Bake at 375° until brown.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream margarine.
Add sugar and continue to cream.
Add eggs and mix.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to sugar mixture along with the mashed bananas and sour milk.
Add vanilla.
When mixed thoroughly, pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake for 45 minutes or until done at 350°.
Test with a toothpick.

title: pancit canton
directions: Peel shrimp, leaving tails.
Devein.
Coat with cornstarch and egg white.
Set aside.
Slice chicken breast; coat with cornstarch.
Saute garlic, onion, pork, shrimp and chicken meat. Season with salt, aji-no-moto and soy sauce.
Pour broth and bring to boil.
Add all the vegetables.
Thicken with dispersed cornstarch.
Stir canton in and cook 10 minutes.
Serve hot.
Best cooked in a wok.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots in boiling water, salted to taste, until still a little crisp.
Drain well and place in a shallow baking dish.

title: water chestnuts
directions: Soak water chestnuts in soy sauce overnight.
Drain and roll water chestnuts in sugar; wrap small strip of bacon around water chestnut and secure with toothpick.
Bake in oven at 350° for 25 minutes or microwave on High for about 10 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: good salad
directions: Heat can of fruit cocktail.
Add dry jello; dissolve.
Let mixture cool.
Mix buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Fold into jello mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: holiday scent
directions: Put ingredients in large saucepan and bring to a boil; simmer 30 minutes.
Refrigerate in a nonaluminum container.
When you want a festive holiday smell, simmer with a cover on stove.

title: beets with orange sauce
directions: Melt butter. Mix sugar and cornstarch together.
Blend into butter.
Stir in orange juice and cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add salt, pepper and beets.
Cook until beets are heated.
Sprinkle with grated orange rind.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Cover bottom of jelly roll pan with crescent rolls and bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, Miracle Whip and dressing mix together.
Spread over rolls.
Sprinkle mixed vegetables over cheese mixture and press down.
Chill for 1 to 2 hours.
Cut into squares.

title: st. paul's rice
directions: Brown hamburger, sausage, onion and pepper in a saucepan. Cook 1 cup of rice in 4 1/2 cups water for seven minutes.
Then add chicken soup mix and mix well.
Mix rice and meat mixtures together in a casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: coconut sheet cake
directions: Mix and bake as directed on box.
When done, take toothpick or fork and punch holes in cake.
Mix together Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk and pour over cake.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Refrigerate until cool.

title: golden cheese wheel
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Beat in 1 cup of flour, oil, 1/2 teaspoon sugar and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Stir in enough of remaining flour to make a moderately stiff dough.

Turn out onto lightly floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic, 5 to 8 minutes. Place in lightly greased bowl, turning once to grease surface. Cover; let rise in warm place until double (about 1 hour).
Punch down; divide into 2 portions.
Cover; let rest 10 minutes.
Roll out each portion to 13-inch circle.
Place 1 circle on greased round pan.
Combine 1 egg, cheese, parsley, garlic salt and pepper; spread over dough in pan.
Place second dough over cheese filling.
Trim and flute.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Brush top with mixture of beaten egg and water.
Sprinkle with sesame seed. Bake for 12 minutes.
Cut into wedges; serve hot.
Makes 16 to 20 servings.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix flour and butter until texture of crumbs.
Spread into a buttered 7 x 9-inch
pan.
Press until firm.
Bake for ten minutes in a preheated 350° oven.

title: rice salad(from liechtenstein)
directions: Cook the rice in the liquid and cool. Add corn and peppers. Make a dressing of the remaining ingredients; mix thoroughly with the rice and vegetables. May be served at room temperature or chilled. Excellent with grilled steak, grilled or fried chicken and fish.

title: fruit balls
directions: In food processor chop prunes and dates for 35 to 40 seconds or until finely chopped.
Place in a large mixing bowl.
Repeat process with raisins and coconut.
Add raisin mixture to prune mixture and mix well.
Stir in wheat germ, orange rind, orange juice, honey and 1/2 cup pecans.
Mix well.
Shape into 1 inch balls and roll in remaining pecans.
Store in airtight container with waxed paper between each layer.

title: strawberry divinity
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water in a 3-quart saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Cook to the hard ball stage (252°).
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Blend in jello.
When syrup reaches 252°, pour in a thin stream over egg whites, beating constantly with electric mixer on medium speed.
Beat as long as possible using wooden spoon if too stiff for mixer.
Add nuts and pour into lightly buttered 9-inch square pan.
Cool.
Cut into pieces.

title: french fudge cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Bake in 2 (9 x 13-inch) pans for 12 minutes.
Mix pudding with milk, then add Cool Whip. Spread between the 2 layers.
Add icing to top layer.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: my famous broccoli-fried rice
directions: *I know you will be tempted to use Minute rice or some substitution, but you will be sorry. It turns to mush and you will have mashed fried rice!

title: lucille's pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter until fluffy. Add eggs 1 at a time. Beat well in between. Add flour 1/2 cup at a time, mixing well between. Beat about 5 good minutes until batter is fluffy. Do not overbeat. Add vanilla and lemon extract. Mix well. Pour into well-greased large tube or Bundt pan. Cook in preheated 350° oven for an hour until golden
brown.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together.
Put in large Tupperware bowl and freeze.
When ready to take to picnic, it will be thawed.

title: cut-out cookies
directions: Mix sugar and butter until creamy, add slightly beaten eggs. Add just a little flour and mix before adding the soda and coffee. Add rest of flour and mix well.
Chill a few hours or overnight before rolling out or roll into rolls or squares and freeze.
Then cut and bake.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken and shred into pieces.
Add mixed vegetables, cream of mushroom soup; mix well and put in one pie shell and put other pie shell on top.
Cook 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken coriander
directions: Stir all seasonings into melted margarine, roll chicken in mix and arrange in casserole in single layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, turn and baste.
Bake until tender about 15 minutes.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients well.
You can roll out the dough and cut the biscuits or pinch off and place in pan.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: rhubarb
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1/2 amount of red pop.
Cook rhubarb in remaining half of red pop until tender.
Mix all together and cool.

title: strawberry cobbler
directions: Combine flour, sugar and milk.
Put over 1 stick melted butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine strawberries, sugar and water; pour over batter.
Don't mix.
Bake until done.
Use toothpick test.

title: quiche
directions: Sprinkle cheese and bacon into crust.
Beat remaining ingredients all together; pour over cheese.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Cook cabbage in salted water a few minutes to soften; drain. Mix 2 tablespoons soup with remaining ingredients.
Divide meat mixture among cabbage leaves.
Fold in sides and roll up.
In skillet, place rolls, seam side down.
Pour remaining soup over. Cover and cook over low heat for 40 minutes.
Stir occasionally, spooning sauce over rolls.

title: coke salad
directions: Drain pineapple and cherry juices into saucepan. Bring liquid to a boil and dissolve Jell-O in it.
Whip cream cheese until soft and fluffy.
Add Jell-O solution and whip to thoroughly combine. Add pitted cherries (cut up), pineapple, nuts and Coke. Pour into Pyrex dish and chill until firm.

title: one minute cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Boil, stirring constantly, for 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour over oats.
Add vanilla.
Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: tostito dip
directions: Use a pizza pan and layer each of above ingredients.
Use Tostitos chips to dip.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding mix with milk.
Add Eagle Brand milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer with bananas and wafer.

title: earthcake dessert
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions.
Flour and grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put coconut and nuts in bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix and pour over nuts and coconut. Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and oleo; spoon over cake mix.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Combine cream cheese and sugar until well blended. Spread mixture over top of cookie. Finish by garnishing with a variety of your favorite fruit. Makes a great summertime treat.

title: doctor bird cake plus
directions: Measure dry ingredients and sift together. Dice bananas to equal 2 cups. Add bananas to dry ingredients along with oil, pineapple and

juice, vanilla, and eggs. Stir to blend---DO NOT BEAT. Gently stir in chocolate chips, cherries, and nuts. Blend well. Pour into a greased 9 inch tube pan or bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour 20 minutes. Set aside to cool on a rack without removing from pan.

title: chicken and dumplings(4 servings)
directions: Cook all ingredients slowly until tender.

title: mushroom rice
directions: Combine rice, mushrooms, peas, butter, seasonings and pimiento. Heat until vegetables are hot, about 3 or 4 minutes.
Toss lightly. Makes 6 servings.

title: ray's meringue
directions: Mix cornstarch with 1 tablespoon cold water and pour into 1/4 cup boiling water, along with the salt.
Cook until clear.
Cool. Beat 4 egg whites until peaks form.
Gradually add sugar.
Put mixer on low and add cold starch mixture.
Put mixer on high and beat until stiff.
Add vanilla.

title: salmon wiggle
directions: Place salmon in bottom of casserole.
Add half of the white sauce, covering the salmon well.
Add the peas, spreading well over the sauce.
Sprinkle diced eggs and pimiento over peas. Cover with remaining white sauce and sprinkle cheese over top. Bake slowly about half an hour or 45 minutes in fairly slow oven. Serve hot.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pecan karo pie
directions: Brown butter in iron skillet.
Remove from heat and add the sugar, stirring until well blended.
Mix eggs and corn syrup with sugar and butter.
Beat thoroughly.
Add vanilla, salt and chopped nuts.
Mix well.
Place in unbaked pie shell.
Cook for 10 minutes at 425°.
Reduce heat to 350° and cook until a silver knife inserted in center of filling comes out clean.
Good.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into 1/4's and coat with sugar and cinnamon. Drop into Bundt pan.
Mix together margarine, cinnamon, milk and sugars.
Pour sauce over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bacon horseradish dip
directions: Stir all ingredients until well mixed.
Cover; chill.

title: cantaloupe soup
directions: Put all ingredients into food processor or blender and mix well.
Chill, covered, in refrigerator.
Blend again before serving to mix altogether.
Makes 6 servings.

directions: Dissolve

title: sparkling punch
directions: Mix all ingredients, except ginger ale and strawberries.
Mix well to dissolve sugar.
Chill.
Just before serving, pour mixture in punch bowl.
Add ginger ale.
Garnish with strawberry slices. Use ice ring in punch.

title: date nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a loaf pan.
Bring 3/4 cup of water to a boil.
Mix it in with dates, sugar and butter in a large bowl.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Stir in the egg, baking soda, flour, salt and walnuts.
Please blend well.
Spoon into a loaf pan and bake 50 minutes.
Remove pan and cool slowly.

title: coconut bundt cake
directions: Separate
egg

in

End with flour. Add coconut.
Beat in egg whites in peaks and fold in. Bake 2 hours at 300°.
Cool 15 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions very thin.
Let stand in salt water (1 cup salt to each gallon of water) for 2 hours or longer. Drain.
Boil in vinegar mixture until tender.
Pack in jars. Seal.
(Makes about 13 pints for the doubled recipe.)

title: lentil soup(greek)
directions: Simmer lentils in stock with salt and pepper to taste for 1 hour. Add remaining ingredients, except vinegar.
Cook until vegetables are tender, about 1/2 hour. Add a teaspoon of vinegar to each bowl as it is served, if desired.
Cooking time:
1 1/2 hours.

title: spicy clam dip
directions: Simmer chopped clams and lemon juice for 10 to 15 minutes (medium in microwave).
Mix all ingredients together and gradually add Italian style bread crumbs to thicken consistency.
Pour into large casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese (suggestion Muenster).
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika.

title: lazy day turkey
directions: Combine butter flavored mix and water, stirring until mix dissolves.
Pour into a large skillet; add chopped onions, green pepper, mushrooms and garlic.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until vegetables are tender.
Stir in cubed turkey, cream of chicken soup, skim milk and next 5 ingredients.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat and simmer uncovered, 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve over rice or pasta. Yields 4 servings (386 calories, 2.6 g fat), per 3/4 cup meat mixture and 1 cup rice.

title: mom's baked barbecue green beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in covered casserole at 275° for 4 hours.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Cook onion, celery, butter and water until tender.
Add other ingredients and simmer
30 minutes.
Delicious added to browned hamburger to make Sloppy Joes or use it as you would any barbecue sauce.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and vanilla.
Mix applesauce and soda and add to mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: hanukkah fruit balls
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Wet hands and shape balls.
Put 1-inch apart on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 or 20 minutes.

title: sausage and pepper braid
directions: Brown sausage and cook pepper until done, stirring to break up meat.
Drain and cool.
Measure warm water into a large warm bowl. Stir in yeast until dissolved.
Add sugar, salt, seasoning, margarine, 1 egg and 2 cups flour; beat until smooth.
Stir in enough more flour to make a soft dough.
Knead 8 to 10 minutes. Place in a greased bowl; turn to grease top.

title: cowboy coffee cake
directions: Cut in flour, salt, sugar and fat.
Remove 1/3 cup crumb mixture for topping.
Nuts may be added.
Add baking powder, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix buttermilk and eggs; add to dry ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: marshmellow cake
directions: Put it in the cake, then cook it.
Bake it at 5° for 3 minutes.

title: mexican stuffed shells
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, brown beef and drain. In medium saucepan, saute peppers and onion in margarine.
Stir half of sauteed vegetables into beef. Add spinach, 1 cup salsa, 4 ounces tomato sauce, 1/2 cup cheese, garlic powder and Creole seasoning.
Mix well.

title: carrot casserole(a great "second" vegetable for a hungry family during winter.)
directions: Mix all ingredients in casserole; pour carrot juice on top and heat in oven for 20 minutes at 375°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: gourmet peas
directions: Cook peas according to package instructions (do not overcook; peas should be bright green).
Drain.
Melt margarine; add chopped onion and celery.
Cook slightly (celery should be crunchy).
Add mushrooms, pimento and water chestnuts and heat thoroughly.
Pour into drained peas.
Mix and serve.

title: beef garden casserole
directions: Cook onion in a small amount of shortening until tender, but not brown.
Add ground chuck and seasonings.
Brown lightly.
Add green peppers, corn and tomato soup.
Pour into casserole.
Top with Cheese Spins (recipe follows).

title: lemon fluff
directions: Mix flour, margarine and pecans together and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Cool.

title: cream of chicken soup
directions: Cook chicken, salt and pepper, celery, onion, carrots and butter until all is tender; shred chicken and put back into broth. Then add flour and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: heath bar chocolate cake
directions: Bake chocolate cake as directed on box.
Mix chocolate pudding as directed.
In a clear dish (salad bowl), crumble chocolate cake.
Top with chocolate pudding.
Top with Cool Whip.
Top with Heath candy bars.
(Continue to layer until all ingredients are used.)
Makes a lot, an excellent potluck dessert.

title: pheasant in sour cream
directions: Coat pheasant with flour, salt and pepper.
Brown in hot fat. Combine cream, soup mix and milk.
Pour over browned meat. Cover.
Bake at 350 F for 1 hour or until tender.

title: turner's fried chicken
directions: Cut and wash chicken, drain on paper towel.
Mix all of the ingredients (except Crisco) in a plastic bag.
Shake parts of chicken in a bag until covered with flour.
Preheat frying pan before putting in Crisco.
When Crisco oil is very hot, place chicken in pan to fry.
Turn chicken often to brown evenly on both sides.
Cook until golden brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Melt butter in large frypan.
Saute onions over medium heat until clear.
Reserve 3 tablespoons of cracker crumbs for topping and place remaining crumbs in the bottom of a lightly greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Remove onions from pan with slotted spoon.
Add soup and onions in alternating layers until full. Combine eggs and milk; pour over onions.
Top with cheese and remaining cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugars, butter and oil.
Add egg.
Mix well.
Sift flour, salt, soda and cream of tartar together.
Add to sugar mixture gradually.
Add vanilla.
Drop by spoonful on oiled cookie sheet. Flatten.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon and salt. In a small bowl, beat eggs gently, not much with a fork.
In a medium bowl, combine oil, sugar and eggs from small bowl, carrots and pecans; stir together by hand.
Combine medium bowl with ingredients in large bowl; stir well by hand. Pour into three 8-inch greased cake pans.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes, or until done.
Let cool before frosting.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Blend margarine until soft.
Add sugar and eggs, mixing well. Mix in remaining ingredients, adding coconut last.
Bake in a tube pan 1 hour at 350°.

title: pork chop suey
directions: Mix together.
Stir slightly and cook 5 minutes more.
Serve over hot rice with Chinese noodles.
A nice change!

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Chop as many potatoes as desired in bite-size pieces.
Put in well-buttered casserole.
Add onions.
Dab with rest of butter. Sprinkle with seasonings and Parmesan cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° until tender, usually 30 to 45 minutes.
Stir and add more Parmesan cheese during cooking.

title: no bake banana pudding
directions: Mix together 1 large box instant French vanilla pudding, directions on box.
Fold in Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk.
In 13 x 9-inch pan, layer bottom with vanilla wafers.
Then layer bananas.
Pour some of mixture on this.
Repeat with vanilla wafers, bananas and mixture until all used up.
Refrigerate 2 hours before serving.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Peel and slice eggplant.
Dip into egg and breadcrumbs.
Fry in oil until browned lightly.
Use a long, low baking pan and pour enough tomato sauce to cover the bottom.
Put one layer of fried eggplant slices and enough Mozzarella cheese to cover.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and cover with a layer of tomato sauce. Repeat process until all the ingredients are used, ending with cheese and sauce layer.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves four.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add onion, bell pepper and remaining ingredients. Stir well.
Cook until onion and bell pepper are done.

title: special k bars
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in saucepan and bring to a complete boil. Turn off heat and stir in cereal and peanut butter until well combined. Turn out into a bowl. Form into balls immediately. May also be dropped by spoonfuls onto wax paper or pressed lightly into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan. Let cool and cut into squares.

title: candied apples
directions: Have apples at room temperature.
Wipe apples with clean, damp cloth.
Insert stick 3/4 deep into apples.
Combine all ingredients, except apples, in saucepan, sides of which have been buttered.
Stir until it comes to a boil.
Let cook without stirring until it reaches a hard crack stage (300°).
Remove from fire.
Dip apple in syrup and twist.
Lift apple out and let excess syrup drip off.
Place on buttered aluminum foil or cookie sheet. When cool, wrap with Saran Wrap or Baggies.

title: sinful salad
directions: Mix together (ready to serve).

title: chili
directions: Brown beef with onion.
Mix other ingredients together and when it boils, add meat mixture. Salt to taste.
You may add uncooked spaghetti. Simmer about 1 hour.

title: chicken surprise
directions: Boil chicken and pick off bone; boil broccoli until tender. Mix water (2 cans) with soup and stir until creamy.
In a casserole dish (approximately 9 x 13-inch), layer chicken, then uncooked stuffing.
Sprinkle seasoning, then soup, then broccoli. Continue to layer until ingredients are all used.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese bubbles.

title: broccoli corn bread casserole
directions: Cut broccoli fine.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on package.
Pour half of batter into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan and bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Melt together the caramels, evaporated milk and butter.
Take cake out of oven, pour caramel mixture over cake, then sprinkle chocolate chips and chopped pecans.
Pour the last half of cake batter on top and bake another 20 minutes or until done.
Serve with whip cream.

title: christmas stollen(3 loaves)
directions: Soak raisins in rum for 3 days.
Stir once to make sure it is completely soaked.
In small bowl, place yeast and warm water.
Mix until yeast dissolves.
Add warm milk and 1 cup flour, mixing well. Cover and place in warm area until light and bubbly.
In large bowl, cream soft butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Mix in salt, lemon rind and yeast mixture.
Stir in nutmeg, vanilla and flour, 1 cup at a time.
Stir well after each addition.
Turn dough out onto a floured board and knead until smooth, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Add drained, rum soaked raisins to dough and knead until evenly distributed.
Place dough on greased bowl.
Turn it over so it is greased on all sides and cover with a towel.
Allow to rise in warm spot until doubled in bulk, about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: carrot bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease bottom only of loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inches. Mix all ingredients; beat vigorously 30 seconds. Pour into pan. Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 50 to 55 minutes. Cool 10 minutes.
Loosen sides of loaf with knife or metal spatula. Remove from pan. Makes 1 loaf.

title: banana muffins
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and shortening.
Add bananas, flour and cinnamon.
Pour into greased muffin pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix 2 cups sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa in saucepan; add 1/2 can milk and equal amount of whole milk.
Cook on medium heat to boil. Once it begins to boil, boil for 4 to 5 minutes, stirring the whole time.
Before you remove from stove, stir in 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter, then place in cold water until it begins to harden.
Spread on greased plate.

title: chili-shrimp with bacon
directions: Mix chili sauce and garlic; pour over shrimp in glass bowl. Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.
Fry bacon until done, but bendable. Drain.
Wrap bacon piece around each shrimp; secure with wooden pick.
Arrange shrimp on broiler pan; broil until bacon is crispy and shrimp is done.
Serve with guacamole.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown stew beef in margarine.
Add 2 to 3 teaspoons soy sauce. Add bell peppers and onion, sliced.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes until onion and peppers are tender.
Serve over rice.
Pineapple chunks may be added just before serving.

title: french onion soup
directions: In a large bowl, combine beans, celery and green onion.

title: chile con queso
directions: Mix in a bowl and put in microwave for 3 or 4 minutes, then mix with a spoon until cheese is melted.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter.
When soft, add sugar gradually.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat well after each.
Add flavoring and beat in. Stir baking soda into sour cream and then beat into mixture.
Sift flour and measure 3 cups.
Beat into sour cream mixture.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pan.
(Can also use 2 regular size loaf pans.)

title: banana split pie
directions: Simmer the pineapple, flour and sugar in small pan until thick.
Cool.
Line crust with sliced bananas.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Pour mixture over.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Chill several hours.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine eggs and corn syrup; mix well.
Add sugar; mix thoroughly.
Stir in salt and vanilla.
Let stand about 5 minutes.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix jello and boiling water together and chill, just until it starts to jell.
Add mayonnaise, pineapple, cottage cheese and horseradish; mix.
Turn into a mold; let set.
Serve on lettuce.

title: cheese pie
directions: Mix well and line pie plate and bake 5 minutes.

title: sausage and rice supreme
directions: Cook rice according to package.
Fry sausage and crumble it. Remove meat.
In drippings, add onion and celery and saute.
Add mushrooms, chestnuts, soup, water, rice and meat.
Mix.
Bake, covered, 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: perfect biscuits
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients and add Crisco; mix with a pastry cutter as you would a pie crust.
Add milk; stir only until moistened.
Turn out onto a floured surface and knead 8 to 10 times.
Roll out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Place on cookie sheet and bake 10 to 12 minutes at 475°.
Serve hot with butter and honey.

title: fudge topped chocolate chip cookies
directions: Go to grocery store.
Buy a package of Chips Ahoy chocolate chip cookies and a jar of Hershey's hot fudge sauce.
Use a spoon to put some fudge on top of each cookie as you eat it.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Bring pineapple and sugar to a boil; add gelatin.
Cool.
Add grated cheese, whipped cream, mayonnaise and nuts.
Chill overnight before serving.

title: strawberry yogurt pie
directions: Fold yogurt into Cool Whip, blending well.
Spoon into graham cracker pie crust.
Freeze until firm.
Top with fresh or frozen strawberries, if desired.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Arrange mushrooms in a shallow baking dish, hollow side up. Combine all remaining ingredients except cream; heap into mushroom umbrellas. Pour cream over mushrooms; bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Baste once or twice with sauce in baking dish. Serves 6 to 8.

title: hearty home-style chili
directions: In a large saucepan or Dutch oven, brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add all remaining ingredients except kidney beans. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Add kidney beans; simmer until thoroughly heated.
Makes seven 1 1/2-cup servings.

title: hearty macaroni salad
directions: Combine macaroni, celery, cheese and ham.
Mix mayonnaise and remaining ingredients.
Pour over salad, toss and chill.
Makes 8 cups.

title: christmas sparkler
directions: In a bowl, press strawberries through a sieve.
Stir lime or lemon juice into pulp.
Cover; chill.
Place strawberry pulp in a large punch bowl.
Carefully pour grape juice and lemon-lime carbonated beverage into chilled pulp, stirring with an up and down motion.
When serving punch, garnish each serving with a lime or lemon slice, if desired.
Makes 18 (4 ounce) servings.

title: parched pecans
directions: Melt oleo in long cake pan.
Put pecans in and toss real good, then salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Cook 10 minutes at 350°.
Take out and repeat: salt, pepper and garlic salt again and bake 10 more minutes.
Real good.

title: pumpkin bread with chocolate chips
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients.
Blend remaining ingredients except pumpkin and chocolate chips
in a bowl.
Add powdered ingredients and pumpkin alternately to the creamed mixture; add chips last.

title: banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Oil an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan lightly. Combine first 5 ingredients in a medium bowl.
Add bananas, milk, Puritan oil and egg whites. Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Spread batter in pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pan for 10 minutes. Remove from pan. Cool completely before slicing.

title: original irish cream
directions: In a blender, combine all ingredients. Blend on high speed for 20 to 30 seconds. Store in a tightly sealed container in the refrigerator. Shake well before serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken with chopped onion in salted water.
Cool, bone and cut up chicken in bite-size pieces.
Boil noodles in broth. Add sour cream and soups and mix.
Add chicken and pour in casserole dish.
Top with five pieces of bread, coarsely broken and buttered.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes, uncovered, at 350° until bubbly and browned.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Combine Jell-O and pineapple. Heat until dissolved. Let cool. Add buttermilk, Cool Whip and pecans. Mix well and refrigerate until congealed.

title: banana-pecan bread
directions: Cream the sugar and cream cheese in a bowl until light and fluffy.
Beat in bananas and eggs.
Stir in baking mix and pecans until just moistened.
Pour into greased 5 x 9-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until bread tests done.

title: crumb cake
directions: Mix butter or margarine, flour and 1 1/2 cups sugar together as a pie crust (use hands).
Take 1/2 cup of the mixture and add cinnamon and a little sugar.
Mix and set aside.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, peanut butter and sugars together.
Add egg, milk and vanilla.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes in one of the following ways:

title: parmesan chicken breasts
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Dip chicken in margarine or spread.
Mix remaining ingredients and coat chicken with mixture.
Place in prepared pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until cooked through. Makes lace in 6 servings.

title: pumpkin dip
directions: Blend.
Serve in small cleaned pumpkin.
Surround with vanilla wafers.

title: dinner-in-a-dish
directions: Crumble beef and cook until it loses color with onion and bell pepper.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place in casserole dish, pushing to the sides to form a ring.
Fill the center with Veg-All.
Pour soup over top.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add soups, sauces and peppers. Mix well.
Place layer of Doritos in bottom of a large casserole dish.
Put hamburger mixture over Doritos; top with shredded cheese.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: burgundy beef stew
directions: In Dutch oven over medium flame, fry bacon until crisp; remove bacon and reserve.
Turn flame to low.
Coat beef pieces with flour.
Cook and stir beef in hot bacon fat until brown.
Drain excess fat from Dutch oven.
Add wine and just enough water to cover beef.
Stir in garlic, bayleaf, bouillon, thyme and pepper. Heat to boiling over medium flame; reduce flame to low.
Cover and simmer until beef is tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
About fifteen minutes before serving, melt margarine in skillet over low flame. Add mushrooms and onions; turn flame to medium.
Cook and stir until onions are tender.
Stir mushrooms, onions and reserved bacon into stew.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Remove bay leaf. Garnish with parsley.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: turnips and collard greens
directions: Combine ham hocks and water in a large Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Cut turnips from greens.
Reserve for other uses.
Remove stems from turnip greens.
Wash turnips and collards.
Drain and tear into bite size pieces.
Add greens, salt, sugar and red pepper to ham hocks.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until greens are tender.

title: peach trifle
directions: Combine pudding mix and milk in a saucepan; bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; let cool. Fold in half of the whipped topping.
Sprinkle sugar over peaches. Toss gently and set aside.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix shortening, margarine, brown sugar, egg yolk and vanilla.
Blend flour and salt.
Stir in little at a time.
Roll 1 teaspoon dough into balls.
Dip in slightly beaten egg whites.
Roll in nuts.
Place 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press thumb gently into center.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes. Cool.
Fill holes with strawberry jam.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: garden vegetable pasta
directions: Melt the butter in a large frying pan.
Saute the garlic and onion for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add the vegetables and the tomato juice, cover and simmer about 15 minutes.
(Start boiling water for noodles during this time.)
While the vegetables are simmering, cook the noodles according to package directions.
Pour vegetables on top of noodles and serve.

title: jane's chicken and dressing
directions: Mix chicken with soup and sour cream.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread dressing mix on top.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: black forest cherry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Stir by hand until smooth.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350°
for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pork and apple stew with rosemary
directions: Mix together the flour, salt and pepper in a bag or a large bowl.
Add cubed pork a few pieces at a time and coat lightly; set aside.
In a large Dutch oven or casserole dish, heat 1 tablespoon of vegetable oil.
Add garlic and onions and saute until onions are clear.
Remove and set aside.
Add a little oil to same pan and, over medium heat, brown meat; set aside.
Raise temperature under pan.
Add cider and stir to get up bits at the bottom.
Put all ingredients into pan.
Stir.
Bring to boiling.
Cover and cook in oven for about 1 hour or until meat is tender.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Prepare pie crust shell.
Cool.
Stir together sugar and flour in saucepan.
Add 1/4 of milk to mix.
Separate eggs, using only the yolks.
Beat into mixture in saucepan.
Add vanilla.
When all is blended well, slowly add remainder of milk.
Heat on medium heat until thickened; stir constantly.
Cool slightly, then stir in peanut butter and fill pie shell.
Garnish slices with Cool Whip and chopped peanuts.

title: angel food supreme(son's favorite cake)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Have ready tube pan, 10 x 4-inch.
Do not grease.
Sift flour, then measure.
Stir flour and first amount of sugar together to blend.
Measure egg whites, cream of tartar and salt into large mixing bowl.
Beat until foamy.
Gradually add second amount of sugar, two tablespoons at a time.
Continue beating until meringue holds stiff peaks; fold in flavoring. Sprinkle flour and sugar mixture over meringue.
Fold in gently, just until the flour-sugar mixture disappears.
Push batter into ungreased tube pan.
Gently cut through batter.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Invert on funnel.
Hang to cool.

title: lasagne roll
directions: Brown together first 4 ingredients.
Mix together next 6 ingredients.
Pour over meat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients together in a separate bowl.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown the ground beef and onion in a frypan. Spoon off grease. Add the remaining ingredients and stir until blended. Simmer over low-medium heat for approximately 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serve on hamburger buns.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and pour into 9 x 12-inch cake pan. Top with brown sugar and nuts.
Bake at 350° until done, 30 to 40 minutes.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients thoroughly.
Add syrup and bourbon; mix well.
Form into one-inch balls, then roll in powdered sugar. Makes approximately 30 balls.

title: pie crust
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and work in chilled shortening. Lightly add ice water slowly and roll on lightly floured board. Line pie tin.
Have dough well over edge of pan.
Roll dough outwards from center.
Keep circular form.

title: green bean salad
directions: Mix veggies and let drain.
Put oil, sugar, vinegar and salt in a saucepan.
Bring to the boiling point, but don't boil.
Pour over veggies and let stand for 2 hours before you refrigerate. Serves 8 to 10.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Add each ingredient, as listed.
Add a dash of salt and pepper to each layer.
Place in oven and bake at 350° for one hour and 30 minutes.

title: meatballs and sauerkraut
directions: Mix and form small meatballs.
Brown in oven.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix well in order given.
Chill overnight or for several hours, covered, in refrigerator.

title: beef and bean stew
directions: Fry beef and onion.
Drain fat away.
Add soup, water and beans.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: strawberry fig preserves
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bring to a rolling boil for 6 minutes.

title: gay's unbaked chocolate cookies
directions: Put sugar, cocoa, milk and butter in a pan and boil for 1 1/2 minutes. Add peanut butter, vanilla and oats. Boil for 2 or 3 minutes longer (until blended), stirring frequently. Drop on waxed paper.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Sprinkle bottom of crust with bacon.
Saute mushrooms, 1/2 teaspoon salt and onion in butter.
Spread on top of bacon. Sprinkle grated cheese over mushrooms.
Cook spinach according to directions with 3/4 teaspoon salt.
Beat eggs and sour cream.
Add milk, 1/4 teaspoon salt and spinach.
Pour over cheese and bake at 350° until set.
Serves 6.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in a greased pan 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.

title: red pepper relish or jam
directions: Remove seeds and mid ribs from thick walled peppers; run through food chopper.
Use smallest knife; measure.
Sprinkle with salt.
Let stand 3 to 4 hours.
Add sugar and vinegar.
Cook until set.
Pour into hot jars and seal at once.

title: pumpkin pie layer cake
directions: Mix until crumbly and sprinkle over top of pumpkin. Bake at 350° about 1 hour (test with knife).

title: carrots and zucchini julienne
directions: Pare carrots and zucchini and cut into lengthwise slices, approximately 1/4-inch thick.
In hot oil in medium skillet, saute, stirring two minutes.
Add 2 teaspoons of water.
Cook, covered, over high heat, stirring occasionally for three minutes. Toss with butter and serve.
Yields 4 servings.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan.
Mix ketchup, Worcestershire sauce and A.1. sauce together.
Add butter and stir well, then add vinegar, salt and pepper.
You may want to add more or less of the ingredients to suit your taste.
Makes approximately 10 ounces.

title: steak marinate sauce
directions: Mix red wine vinegar, soy sauce, oil, garlic powder, onion and brown sugar. Marinate steak 3 to 4 days in the refrigerator. Grill.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into crust and bake at 300° for about 1 hour.

title: red lobster cheese biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients with ice water until mixture can be pushed off end of spoon (about biscuit size lumps).
Bake 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pink peppermint frosting
directions: Combine sugar, water, egg whites, syrup and salt in top of double boiler.
Before placing over boiling water, beat mixture at low speed for 1 minute or just until blended.
Place over boiling water.
Beat at high speed for 7 minutes or until stiff peaks form.
Remove from heat.
Add extract and coloring.
Beat at high speed for 2 minutes or until thick enough to spread. Yields 7 cups.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook spinach and squeeze out water.
Mix all ingredients, except bread.
Pull out the bread center into bite-size pieces. Fill center with dip.
Arrange bits of bread around loaf.

title: easy rice-cooker sausage jambalaya
directions: Drain mushrooms, black-eyed peas and string beans.
Mix all into rice
cooker.	Cover
and
turn on; cooks in 30 to 35 minutes.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Combine sweetened condensed milk and margarine.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Place in refrigerator until mixture is cool, then form into balls.
Melt caramel morsels and paraffin until melted well; add pecans and coconut.
Drop each ball 1 at a time into paraffin mixture until covered.
Drop onto waxed paper.
Makes 4 pounds.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Combine peaches, honey, egg, tapioca, cinnamon and vanilla. Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease a 9-inch round baking dish.
Spread peach mixture evenly on bottom of baking dish.
Mix flour, soda, butter, milk and buttermilk into dough.
Roll dough to 1/4-inch thickness.
Prick dough with fork and place loosely over peaches. Bake 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with fresh pureed peaches for topping.

title: spicy peanut soup
directions: Reserve 3 tablespoons chopped onion for garnish.
Combine broth, milk and peppers in a bowl; stir until combined.

title: banana-split pie
directions: Mix pudding according to directions on box and pour into pie shell.
Slice bananas into pudding; then, pour pineapple over bananas.
Cover with whipped topping and garnish with pecans or walnuts.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: press 'n bake cream cheese crust
directions: Combine cream cheese and butter; blend well.
Stir in flour. Refrigerate 30 minutes.
Press dough into bottom and up sides of 9-inch pie pan.
Flute edge as desired.
Chill until needed for filling.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Add peanuts just before serving with dressing.

title: new york casserole
directions: Spray a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with Pam.
Layer potatoes, onion, mixed vegetables and Mrs. Dash to taste. Set aside.
In skillet, stir-fry ground chuck until it changes color.
Pour off excess oils. Add cream of whatever soup. Mix well.
Pour over first pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, until potatoes are tender. Sprinkle both cheeses on top.
Bake an additional 5 minutes. Serve hot with salad and French bread.

title: crab dip
directions: Melt cheese in soup in the top of a double boiler.
Add crab and heat through.
Serve with crackers. Keeps nicely in a fondue pot.

title: chinese sausage bites
directions: In a bowl, combine sausage, egg and cubes.
Use a teaspoon for amount to form small balls.
Melt butter in a frying pan.
Cook balls evenly until brown; drain on absorbent paper.
In a pot, mix the remaining ingredients.
Cook slowly for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Place balls in a serving bowl; cover with sauce. Serve with toothpicks.
Yields 20 to 25 appetizers.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: In double boiler, melt paraffin and chocolate chips.
In large bowl, mix butter, sugar and peanut butter.
Roll into small balls. Dip the balls into melted chocolate and place on wax paper.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together and store in airtight containier until ready to serve with vegetable tray.

title: sourdough pancakes
directions: In evening, put water in a large bowl.
Add yeast.
Add flour and beat.
Cover with a plate and leave in a warm place overnight. In the morning, add salt, sugar, eggs and baking soda dissolved in water.
Beat thoroughly.
Bake on hot griddle.
Pancakes are very thin.
Makes 24 to 40 pancakes which also freeze well.

title: cioppino(cha-pee-no)
directions: Thaw shrimp, if frozen.
Remove any skin from fish fillets and cut fillets into 1-inch pieces.
Set aside.
Cut green pepper into 1/2-inch squares.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Pound chicken until thin.
Soak in milk.
Follow directions on spaghetti sauce package.
Mix together the bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese and coat chicken.
Fry in butter or butter-flavored Crisco until browned on both sides.
Place chicken, sauce and cheese in casserole pan and bake at 350° for approximately 15 minutes, until cheese is melted.
Prepare noodles; serve over noodles.

title: layered bean and sausage dip
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Add 1/4 cup of salsa and beans. Spread into large pie plate.
Top with sour cream, remaining salsa (drained) and cheese.
Garnish with green onions and sliced black olives.

title: cherry coke fruit medley salad
directions: Combine sugar, cherries and hot water.
Bring to a boil.
Add Jell-O and let cool.
Add pineapple and Coke.
Add nuts, if desired.
Refrigerate.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients; set aside.
Chop olives, peppers and pimento together.
Spread first mixture on each flour tortilla, then sprinkle olive mixture over top of this.
Roll up jelly roll fashion. Chill several hours or overnight, then slice in slices.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: jambalaya
directions: In a Dutch oven, saute onion, celery, green pepper and garlic in butter until tender.
Add the next nine ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer until rice is tender, about 25 minutes.
Add shrimp and parsley; simmer uncovered, until shrimp are cooked, 7-10 minutes.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: pepper shrimp with rice and beans
directions: Combine rice, drained beans, chilies, pimientos and parsley in microwave container.
Heat 5 minutes on High covered.
Stir and repeat heating for 3 or 4 minutes.
Arrange on platter with shrimp.
Sprinkle with cilantro.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind all ingredients together.
Add sugar.
Let sit 24 hours in the refrigerator.
Add more sugar to taste.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet and drain. Cook spaghetti and drain. Melt butter in 9 x 13 pan. Add garlic. Place cooked spaghetti in pan. Layer beef, mushrooms, sauce, cheeses, pepperoni and olives until gone. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: crock-pot chili
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add onions.
Put in crock-pot and add the ingredients.
Put whole green pepper in for flavor.
Cook on low for 7 to 8 hours.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Combine peanut butter, milk and cream cheese in large mixing bowl on low speed.
Add powdered sugar and whipped topping.
Mix until smooth.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Freeze until firm.

title: artichokes with mustard sauce
directions: Slice 1-inch from top of artichokes.
Trim stem even with base. Cut off sharp tips of outer leaves.
Rinse artichokes under cold water.
Arrange in upright position in square baking dish.
Pour 1/4 cup water into dish.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave for 10 to 16 minutes, rearranging once during cooking time.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Serve with artichokes.

title: quick rolls
directions: Dissolve oleo in warm water.
In large bowl, mix flour, sugar, yeast and salt.
Pour water over dry ingredients.
Mix until half done, then add egg and finish mixing.
Put in refrigerator.
When time to bake, put in muffin tins.
Bake about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: little smokies
directions: Simmer Little Smokies in sweet and sour sauce until smokies look glazed.
Serve hot.

title: hash
directions: Cook pork and chicken.
Take out bone.
Grind pork, chicken, beef, onions and bread.
Add broth, enough to cover.
Put in vinegar, catsup and butter.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until thickened.
Makes about 1 1/2 gallons.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Store in airtight jar.
When ready to serve, mix desired amount (approximately 1 tsp.) in boiling water in cup.

title: hot seafood sandwiches(microwave)
directions: Mix all ingredients, except toast and sprouts.
Arrange sprouts on toast; top with seafood mixture.
Arrange on 12-inch plate.
Microwave, uncovered, on High for 3 to 4 minutes.
Rotate after 2 minutes.
Microwave until cheese begins to melt and mixture is hot.

title: sugar cream cake
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine and egg together.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Press down.

title: salted pecans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in shallow baking pan.
Add pecans and stir well.
Bake 20 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes. Remove from oven, sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Let nuts cool in pan.

title: french onion soup fiesta chicken roll-ups
directions: Saute onions in butter until soft; heat beef broth, water and spices, over medium heat.
Pour onions into broth and simmer for 1 to 2 hours.

title: layer salad
directions: Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: sorry cookies
directions: Cream sugar and eggs together.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Spread into 12 x 14-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool in pan, cut into squares.

title: pennsylvania dutch baked beans with sour cream
directions: Soak beans overnight; add water to cover.
Rinse; cover with water and 1 teaspoon salt.
Cook 30 to 40 minutes; rinse and drain.
Add all ingredients and mix tenderly.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: porcupines
directions: Mix together and make meatballs.
Brown slowly, turning as they fry, then add 2 cans tomato soup or mushroom soup and 2 cans water.
Bake, uncovered, in 400° oven for 35 minutes, then cover for 35 minutes.

title: yeast bread or rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water with small amount of sugar.
Add to flour, plus enough warm water to make medium stiff dough. Knead on floured board for 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in warm greased bowl; turn to grease top.
Cover; let rise until double (1 hour or more).
Shape into rolls or loaves.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 275° for 10 to 15 minutes, then at 325° until done, 25 to 30 minutes.
Grease top when they begin to brown.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Mix yogurt with topping.
Pour into pie crust.
Chill until firm.
Fresh fruit may be used to garnish pie.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Beat eggs in bowl.
Mix mustard in a small amount of milk to blend.
Stir in all ingredients together and pour in 9 x 13-inch greased casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: fresh peach pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased and floured tube cake pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: classic italian crab cioppino
directions: Heat the olive oil in a deep, nonaluminum pot and saute the onion until it starts to soften.
Stir in the chopped tomatoes, oregano, basil, bay leaf, white wine and half the garlic.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Add the remaining garlic, crab, salt and pepper and cook until the crab is hot.
Remove the bay leaf and serve in warmed soup bowls with crusty sourdough bread.
Serves 4.

title: meringue
directions: Dissolve cornstarch; add 1/2 cup water, boil until thick. Cool.
Beat egg whites, cream of tartar and baking powder until soft peaks form.
Slowly add sugar.
Beat until glossy.
Then beat in cooled, thickened mixture.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes high meringue, does not weep.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Dissolve sugar in vinegar, water and oil.
Mix with vegetables.
Marinate for 24 hours in refrigerator before serving. Drain before serving.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine cornstarch, 1 1/2 cups sugar and pinch of salt in pan; stir to blend well.
Gradually stir in hot water until well mixed. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Lower heat and cook 1 minute longer.
Beat egg yolks slightly in small bowl.
Stir in about 1/2 cup of the hot mixture. Stir into cornstarch mixture in pan.
Cook, stirring constantly, 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter and lemon rind until butter is melted.
Gradually stir in lemon juice.
Cool 5 minutes. Pour into pie shell.

title: brown sugar cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Mix ingredients together. Pour into two greased 9 x 13 pans. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: strudels
directions: Prepare day or night before.
Tear buns or bread into small pieces and top with oleo.
Toast in oven at about 300° until light brown and dry.
When cool, put in blender or crush by hand. Divide into 4 portions and set aside.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring sugar, butter, cocoa and milk to a rapid boil.
Boil exactly 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add oats and vanilla. Stir in any optional ingredients.
Drop on wax paper to cool. Store in loosely covered container.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers and onions in brine of salt and water overnight.
Drain and add remaining ingredients.
Bring to rolling boil.
Boil 10 minutes.
Pack in jars.
Seal and process 30 minutes.

title: party snacks
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage; drain well.
Mix in cheese and spices.
Spread mixture over rye.

title: trail mix
directions: Mix all together and store in airtight jar.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar.
Have water boiling in saucepan.
Add cocoa, sugar mixture and salt.
Gradually stir in flour mixture. Remove from burner and stir in vanilla.
Serve hot or cold over hot biscuits.
Good on cake and ice cream, too.

title: vegetable relish salad
directions: Drain beans, corn, peas and chopped pimentos.
Chop green pepper, celery and onion and add to other vegetables.
Mix together salt, pepper, oil, vinegar, sugar and water and pour over vegetables.
Let stand 24 hours and it is ready to serve.
Will keep in refrigerator for at least 2 weeks.

title: baked fish
directions: Heat oven to 450°. Heat butter, water, wine, lemon juice, 1/4 teaspoon salt, pepper and basil in small saucepan until butter melts. Lay out 4 squares of heavy-duty foil. Spread 1/3 cup rice in center of each square. Top with onion, red pepper and peas. Sprinkle with remaining salt. Top with fillets; tuck any rice under. Sprinkle with lemon pepper. Top with tomato. Curl foil up slightly. Divide butter mixture among packets. Seal packets completely. Place on baking sheet. Bake in heated 450° oven 20 to 25 minutes. Open packets carefully, as steam may escape. Serve with lemon wedges if desired. Delicious!!!!!!

title: turkey-pasta primavera
directions: Cook broccoli, onion, garlic and carrot in oil in 10-inch nonstick skillet over medium heat about 10 minutes, stirring frequently, until broccoli is crisp-tender.
Stir in turkey, salt and tomatoes.
Heat about 3 minutes or just until turkey is hot. Spoon turkey mixture over spaghetti.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 6 servings.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix together vinegar, sugar, Wesson oil, salt and pepper and pour over wax beans, green cut beans, red kidney beans, chopped green peppers and chopped scallions. Marinate at least 1 day. Serves 4 to 6.

title: cheese soup
directions: Cook vegetables in chicken stock on medium heat until tender. (approx. 15 minutes) Melt butter, blend in flour, reduce heat to low.
Add cream.
Add all of this to chicken broth and vegetable. Bring to boil slowly stirring constantly.
Add grated cheese and oregano.
Stir until cheese melts.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Crush pretzels and mix with margarine and 2 tablespoons sugar. Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes.
Blend together cream cheese, Cool Whip and 1 cup of sugar and spread over cooled crust.
Dissolve jello in boiling water (2 cups).
Add strawberries and drained pineapple.
Chill until slightly thick. Pour over cream cheese mixture.
Chill until firm.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Combine berries, sugar, flour, salt and lemon juice.
Fill 8-inch pie pan.
Dot with butter; cover with top crust.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: barbecue beef
directions: In crock-pot, cook roast until tender and breaks apart.
Drain. Juice can be saved for flavoring a soup.
Add 1 bottle barbecue sauce and cook slowly until beef is flavored.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine whole kernel corn and 3/4 cup milk or cream-style corn and 1/2 cup milk.
Add crumbs, onion, green pepper and seasonings. Pour into greased baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mississippi spuds
directions: Toss spuds with mayonnaise and salt, pepper, cheese and onion. Place mixture in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with crumbled bacon and olives.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Serves 8 to 10 people.
Can be prepared ahead and frozen.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream the shortening.
Gradually add 1 cup sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer. Add egg and vanilla. Beat well. Combine flour and baking powder. Add to creamed mixture alternating with milk.
Cover and chill.
Work with half of the dough at a time.
Store remainder in refrigerator. Roll dough to 1/4-inch thickness. Cut and place cookies on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Drain potatoes and place in a greased baking dish.
On top of potatoes, dot with 1/2 cup margarine.
Place topping ingredients over potatoes.
Combine the remainder of ingredients and pour over potatoes.
This may be refrigerated overnight or may bake at once in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Use a shallow pan covered with foil or a Corning Ware dish. (Salt and pepper both sides of chicken.)
Turn bony side up.
Put some butter on each piece.
Pour some lemon juice on each piece. Brown on the bony side on broil.
Turn breasts over.
Put lemon juice on each piece.
Let brown on broil.
Turn back to bony side. Put Worcestershire sauce over each piece.
Pour 1 cup of water over all and cover with foil tightly.
Cook 45 to 60 minutes, until water is gone, at 450°.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender and blend for 10 seconds, pulsing 3 or 4 times.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes, until top is golden brown.

title: frosty cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple and sauces; reserve liquid.
Add enough water to make 2 cups.
Bring this liquid to a boil.
Dissolve Jell-O in it.
Chill Jell-O until almost set.
Beat softened cream cheese and mayonnaise together.
Gradually beat in Jell-O and Cool Whip. Stir in remaining ingredients and refrigerate until set.
Need a 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish.

title: lou's salad
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients until thick.
Cook mixed vegetables. Cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour vinegar mixture over vegetables and serve.

title: banana puddin
directions: Place a layer of vanilla wafers in the bottom of a flat glass dish. Add layer of sliced bananas. Prepare one box of pudding and pour on as the next layer. Then another layer of wafers, then bananas, then 1/2 the pineapple, the other box of pudding. One more layer of wafers, bananas and top with the rest of pineapple and its juice. Let sit until cool, but not cold. Served at room temp is best.

title: caramel corn(microwave)
directions: Melt butter.
Add brown sugar, dark corn syrup and salt. Microwave 1 minute and 50 seconds on High.
Add baking soda and stir well.
Put popped corn in brown bag.
Pour mixture over popcorn and shake well.
Microwave 1 minute and 50 seconds; shake well.
Pour into bowl and stir often.

title: tanuki meat lump
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into loaf and place in loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: jogging in a jug
directions: Mix honey and vinegar. Then mix with both juices. Take 2 ounces per day.

title: buckeyes(candy)
directions: Cream together the butter and peanut butter; add confectioners sugar.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin wax over low heat until melted.
Dip balls using a toothpick in the chocolate until almost emerged.

title: arroz con pollo
directions: Boil chicken in water until chicken falls off bone.
Strain chicken from broth.
Save broth.
Strip chicken from bone into pieces.
Set aside.
In large pot or frypan, saute green peppers and onions in oil until tender.

Add chicken pieces, rice, 3 cups chicken broth (water can be added to saved broth to equal 3 cups), salt and pepper, 1/4 teaspoon saffron, tomatoes and pimentos. Cover and simmer slowly for about 30 minutes or until rice is done. Add baby peas just before serving.

title: snap bean casserole
directions: Put in baking dish and cook about 1 hour at 350°.

title: bacalhau a bras number 1
directions: Shred codfish, after removing skin and bones.
Codfish should be soaked prior to this for about 1/2 hour so it loses its salt. Remove from water and press until dry.
For best results, water should be changed several times.
Cut the potatoes into long thin strips and fry until transparent and lightly browned.
Do not allow potatoes to crisp.
Remove from pan.
Cut onion into crescent shape slices (thin) and saute until lightly browned.
Add shredded codfish and cook for 5 minutes.
Add salt, pepper, garlic and bay leaf.
Mix well then add the parsley and potatoes.
Add beaten eggs and stir until eggs are cooked.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Combine ingredients in mixing bowl.
Dump into 2 1/2-quart casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until bubbling.
It may take longer if hash browns are completely frozen.

title: pineapple cheesecake
directions: Mixture 1
- Cream together cream cheese, margarine and sugar.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Put syrup, sugar and peanuts in skillet.
Cook until peanuts pop and syrup turns a little brown, about 12 to 15 minutes.
Then stir in soda.
Pour into buttered pan to cook.

title: cucumber spread
directions: Grate peeled cucumber and onion into mixing bowl.
Drain well to remove juice.
In separate bowl, beat cream cheese, mayonnaise and flavorings together until smooth.
Blend in cucumber and onion.
Taste for seasoning.
Chill.
Spread on party bread.

title: chipped beef cheese ball
directions: Defrost cream cheese until room temperature.
Add rest of ingredients.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: brownie mixmaster mix
directions: Mix well.
Place in sealed container.
Makes 12 single recipes.

title: chocolate brownie cake
directions: Mix in mixing bowl, sugar and flour; set aside.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In 3-quart oblong baking dish, combine milk, thyme and pepper. Stir in vegetables and chicken. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until mixture begins to bubble. Meanwhile, cut each biscuit into quarters.
tags: cream of broccoli soup with Cheddar

title: mexican chowder
directions: Brown meat and onions in fat in skillet.
Add chopped garlic, olives, mushrooms, pimento, corn, spaghetti and tomatoes.
Add juice from pimento and mushrooms and 1/2 cup tap water.
Cook slowly for 45 minutes, covered.
Serve while hot.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Put skim milk in boiler.
Add gelatin.
Stir to dissolve.
Add eggs that have been beaten and rest of ingredients.
Cook long enough to cook eggs, if using them.
Cool 8 to 12 hours, then freeze as usual.

title: broccoli stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until tender.
Cook broccoli and drain well. Halve potatoes lengthwise, leaving 1/4-inch thick shell.
Scoop out flesh into bowl.
Add milk and butter and mash until smooth. Spoon into shells.
Mix broccoli, cheese, onion, salt and pepper until blended.
Spoon 1/4 cupful onto each potato.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend cheese, milk, sugar and peanut butter together.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Serve with additional Cool Whip.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, milk and sugar in a large bowl with a wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped cream.
Spread on bottom of crust.

title: swiss cashew tossed salad
directions: In a blender, combine the vinegar, sugar, mustard, onion and salt. Cover and process until well blended. While processing, gradually add oil in a steady stream. Stir in poppy seeds. In a salad bowl, combine the romaine, cashews and Swiss cheese. Serve with dressing. Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Combine ground beef, oatmeal, green pepper, onion, celery, egg, parsley, garlic, tomato juice, salt and pepper. Put in greased loaf pan. Cook in microwave on High 6 minutes. Frost with ketchup and cook 5 more minutes.

title: pistachio nut torte
directions: Mix like pie dough the first 4 ingredients.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Whip with mixer the cream cheese and sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread on crust.
Mix pudding and milk until thickened.
Spread over creamed mixture.
Top with other half of Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts. Chill.

title: cheesy crumb tomatoes(serves 6)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In small bowl, combine bread crumbs, cheese, salt and pepper; mix well.
Sprinkle several tablespoons crumb mixture over each tomato half.
Dot each half with 1 teaspoon butter (or drizzle with melted butter).
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: Sort and wash peas; place in Dutch oven.
Add 2 slices bacon and next 4 ingredients.
Bring to a boil; cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 40 minutes or until peas are tender; drain and discard bacon, onion and garlic.

title: creamed brussels sprouts
directions: Place the Brussels sprouts in a baking dish.
Pour enough cream over them to cover the bottom of the dish, 1/2-inch. Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste. Cover and bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix together ground chuck, garlic powder, salt, bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, rice, pepper and 1/2 cup sauce.
Cook cabbage until tender.
Cut off leaves; mix filling ingredients and roll in fist size balls.
Wrap each ball in cabbage leaf.
Place in casserole and cover with tomato sauce.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: royal rice
directions: Prepare Minute rice, using beef bouillon instead of plain water.
Saute green onions in butter until tender.
Add mushrooms, salt and cooked rice.
Mix all together.
Heat thoroughly; fluff lightly with a fork before serving.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine in dish.
Spread uncooked rice over margarine. Pour water over rice; place chicken on rice and spoon soup over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: dirt
directions: You will need an 8-inch flowerpot (plug hole).

title: pork chop dinner
directions: Place chops in casserole dish.
Combine all remaining ingredients.
Pour mixture over pork chops.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana blizzard(diabetic recipe)
directions: Put bananas in blender. Add lemon juice and blend to mix.
Put in all remaining ingredients and blend at high speed until frothy. Serve in chilled glasses. Serves 6.
Each serving contains 1 fruit portion, 1/2 milk portion and 80 calories.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown ground beef and pork sausage with onion.
Crumble meat with fork.
Add tomatoes, kidney beans, chili powder and salt. Simmer 1 hour.
Makes 4 servings.

title: meat-za pie
directions: Place beef, salt, garlic salt, onion and bread crumbs in a 9-inch pan.
Add evaporated milk and mix together with a fork. Spread mixture evenly over the bottom of pan, raising a rim about a half-inch high around edge.
Spread catsup or tomato paste over meat to the rim.
Arrange drained mushrooms on catsup.
Place cheese strips in crisscross pattern over top.
Sprinkle with oregano.
Sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in a preheated oven at 400° for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted and lightly browned.
Cut in wedges.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar together.
Add eggs at room temperature. Add 2 cups of cake flour, then 1/2 cup of White Lily flour.
Cook at 200° until done.

title: six or seven layer dinner
directions: Put ingredients in baking dish as given.
If using cabbage, add after ground turkey.
Season with salt and pepper.
May add hot pepper seeds and oregano.
Bake at 375° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain cans; mix all ingredients together.
