Bring to a boil the sugar, oil, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Pour over vegetables.

title: six flavor pound cake
directions: Cream together margarine, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 2 minutes after each egg.
Mix together and set aside salt, flour and baking powder.
Mix together the flavorings and milk.
Add dry and liquid ingredients to creamed mixture alternately.
Bake in a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.
Do not open oven door while cake is baking.

title: broccoli ham bake casserole
directions: Preheat over to 350 degrees.
Cook broccoli by package directions.
Do not overcook.
Drain.
Cook rice in water until tender.
Saute onion in butter until tender.
Combine milk and soup.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into casserole dish. Reserve some cheese for top.
Cook until cheese has melted and ingredients well blended.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° until done.

title: corn casserole(as close to judy mckay's as i'll ever get!)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake 20 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle the 1 cup grated cheese on top.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes longer.
Makes 1 large or 2 small casseroles.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in warm water and add to flour mixture along with buttermilk.
Mix well; turn out on lightly floured board.
If necessary, add additional flour to make soft dough.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick.
Dip in melted butter and fold over to make pocket-book rolls.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Store unused dough in plastic bowl in refrigerator.
Use within a week.

title: mexican taco spread
directions: Layer ingredients in a 9 1/2-inch pie plate in the order given.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar together.
In another bowl mix milk, pudding and whipped topping.
Combine mixtures.
Put 1/3 of crushed cookies in bottom of plastic sand pail or flowerpot.
Add 1/2 of pudding mixture.
Top with 1/3 of cookies, then remaining pudding mixture.
Top with rest of cookie crumbs before serving.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Cook onions, celery and bell pepper in oleo until soft.
Add English peas, chestnuts, pimento and mushroom soup.
Pour into a buttered casserole and cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until brown and bubbly.

title: hamburger hot dish
directions: Mix all together in casserole dish and sprinkle top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 325 degrees (slow oven) until done and browned, about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Chow mein noodles may be substituted with elbow noodles.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cut up and stew potatoes to fill 9 x 13-inch pan, drained. Mix remaining ingredients. Spoon over potatoes. Top with cracker crumbs. Melt 1/2 stick margarine and pour on top.
Bake at 375° approximately 40 minutes, until brown and bubbly.

title: rhubarb-cherry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix together the first 4 ingredients until crumbly.
Press 1/2 into bottom of square pan.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Pour over crust.
Sprinkle remaining crust on top.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: mezzela pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; add baking powder, sugar and vanilla.
Beat again.
Fold in pecans and graham crackers. Butter a 9-inch pie plate and pour mixture in.
Bake at 300° for 35 minutes or until lightly golden brown.
Cool.
Top with a medium tub Cool Whip and chopped pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream 3 sticks margarine and softened cream cheese.
Add sugar a little at a time.
Add eggs, one at
a time, beating mixture after each addition.

title: everyday cookies
directions: Combine sugar, margarine, oil, vanilla and eggs.
Beat well so oil doesn't separate.
Add dry ingredients.
Chill.
Form into balls, flatten with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: beef and bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain off fat.
Add beans, tomato sauce and cheese.
Let simmer until cheese melts.
Pour into casserole dish.

title: brown sugar christmas cookies
directions: Melt lard and butter in small pan.
Pour into large bowl; add sugars, baking powder, salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Blend in eggs and milk.
Stir in flour a little at a time until stiff enough to roll out.
Roll 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick and cut into desired shapes. Place 1/2-inch apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool and decorate with colored icing.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: sarah chase's scalloped tomatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place 2 tablespoons olive oil in a large nonstick skillet.
Add the bread cubes and stir to coat. Saute over medium heat for 5 to 7 minutes, or until the bread is lightly browned.

title: mini quicki quiches
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Generously grease 24 miniature muffin cups.
Separate dough into 12 pieces.
Divide each roll in half. Press dough in muffin cups, covering bottom and sides.
Divide shrimp or ham evenly among shells.

title: doodle cake
directions: Pour over cake while cake is still hot.
Eat 2 pieces at a time.

title: one hour turkey from margaret's kitchen
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Wash turkey; season inside and out with salt and pepper.
Place a flat lid in bottom of roaster so the turkey won't stick.
Place turkey in roaster and baste with butter.
Pour water in roaster and add giblets if you have any. Cover and bake 1 hour.
Do not open oven while cooking and do not open oven until it is completely cooled.

title: bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Melt butter over low heat.
Crumble bread into a big bowl.
Add milk and mix thoroughly.
Add sugar, salt and vanilla and mix. Beat eggs lightly; add and mix.
Add melted butter; mix and pour into baking dish.
Bake 1 1/2 hours on middle rack in oven.
Place pan underneath to catch drippings, then cool on wire rack.

title: peanut butter cornflake cookies
directions: Cook sugar and syrup until sugar dissolves.
Add peanut butter and cornflakes and mix well.
Mix with buttered hands to make sure it is well mixed, then with buttered hands press firmly into a 13 x 9 baking pan. Cut with a buttered knife while still warm.
Cool until firm and eat.

title: oven apple butter
directions: Mix well.
Bake in oven 3 to 4 hours at 350°.
Stir occasionally.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan, mix rice and 3 cans soup.
Put chicken on top of rice mixture and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: pear chiffon pie
directions: Drain pear halves, reserving 1/4 cup syrup and 1 pear half. Mash remaining pear halves; drain. Combine the first 1/3 cup sugar, gelatin and salt.
Stir in reserved pear syrup, egg yolks, lemon peel and lemon juice.
Cook and stir until slightly thickened.
Add mashed pears. Cool until mixture mounds.
Beat egg whites to soft peaks.
Gradually add remaining sugar, beating until stiff.
Fold in pear mixture.
Turn into pie shell. Chill. Garnish with whipped cream and reserved pear half, sliced.

title: whipped cream cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add flour alternating with whipping cream.
Beat well.
Add vanilla. Pour in tube pan.
Place in cold oven and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: spicy seasoning mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store, covered, in airtight container.
Shake before using to blend.
Yields about 1/3 cup.

title: frozen orange juice jelly
directions: Thoroughly mix orange juice concentrate with water and powdered pectin in a large pan.
Stir constantly over high heat until bubbles form around edge.
Immediately add sugar and stir well. Bring to a full rolling boil and boil hard for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from the heat.
Skim and pour into sterilized jars. Fill to within 1/2-inch of top.
Put on caps; screw bands firmly tight!
Process in boiling water bath 5 minutes.
Yields 6 (8 ounce) jars.

title: cheese fondue
directions: Crumble sausage and fry until done; drain.
Put in casserole dish.
Grate cheese and spread 1/2 on top.
Spread bread crumbs on top of cheese.
Beat the eggs, add milk and mix well.
Pour over casserole dish.
Spread the remainder of the cheese over all. Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes until browned.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Add peanut butter to melted butter in large bowl; stir until peanut butter melts.
Stir in sugar and vanilla.
Beat in eggs. Add flour, baking powder and salt; beat well.
Remove 1 3/4 cup batter; stir cocoa into this part.
Spread cocoa batter in prepared pan; spread remaining peanut butter batter over top. Bake 30 minutes or until brownies begin to pull away from sides of pan.
Cool completely in pan.
Cut into bars.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients with mixer.
Add pecans; mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sauerkraut pork
directions: Brown pork roast, then bake.
Use drippings and mix with brown sugar.
Add sauerkraut.
Place on roast.
Cover and bake.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Whip potatoes until soft.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add milk and eggs; mix well.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into well-greased square glass dish; mix remaining ingredients for topping in order given.
Sprinkle on top of potatoes.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350° until bubbly and slightly browned.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Place croutons in well greased baking dish. Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over croutons. Soak overnight. Bake at 325° for 55-60 minutes.

title: white fudge
directions: Combine sugar, sour cream, milk, butter, corn syrup and salt in heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until sugar is dissolved and mixture reaches a boil.
Boil 9 to 10 minutes at 238°, softball stage.
Remove from heat and allow to stand until lukewarm (110°), about 1 hour.
Add vanilla and beat until mix just begins to lose its glaze and hold its shape.
(Requires very little beating.)
Quickly stir in nuts and cherries and turn into oiled pan.
Let stand in pan until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: chicken cilantro
directions: Cut chicken into 1/4-inch pieces.
In large skillet, melt butter.
Add onions, garlic, cilantro and lemon.
Saute until tender.
Add cut chicken, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook 5 minutes until chicken is cooked.
Pour over 6 cups steamed rice. Serves 12.

title: cocoa-nut pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Mix sugar and cocoa.
Add to eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour mixture into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Thaw and drain spinach.
Stir in can of cream of potato soup. Add Parmesan cheese.
Blend all together and place in square baking dish.
Prepare Stove Top by box instructions and spread on top of spinach mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
When cheese appears through dressing, it should be done.

title: quick potatoes au gratin
directions: Prick potatoes with fork.
Bake in a 375° oven for 45 to 50 minutes or until tender.
Cool slightly.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise.
Gently scoop out each potato half, leaving a thin shell.
Set shells aside.

title: hash brown cheese bake
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Spoon onto a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: german crumb ball
directions: Mix above ingredients.
Roll into small balls.
Melt chocolate chips.
Dip balls into chocolate.
Let set overnight.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix well the flour, sugar and cinnamon in a large bowl. Combine in saucepan the oleo, oil, cocoa and water and bring to a boil.
Pour over flour, sugar and cinnamon.
Add eggs, buttermilk, soda and vanilla.
Mix well and pour onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: russian dressing
directions: In a screw-top jar, combine all ingredients.
Cover and shake. Chill.
Shake before serving. Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Layer pineapple chunks with juice and cherry pie filling.
Sprinkle on yellow cake mix (dry).
Slice butter stick and drop squares across top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese topped pork chops
directions: You will also need Pam spray.

title: frozen fruit champagne punch
directions: Mix rinds of lemons and oranges, corn syrup and brandy and let mellow in refrigerator for a week.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Cut cauliflower into florets.
Place in bowl, pour on dressing, mix and serve.

title: peanut brittle candy
directions: Boil until spins a thread off spoon, then add raw peanuts (10 ounce jar).
Cook until light brown.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla, then take off heat and stir in 2 teaspoons baking soda.
Pour on greased cookie sheet.

title: cranberry jello
directions: Mix as listed and chill.

title: chicken breast veronique
directions: Remove the
skin from the chicken breasts.
Cut them in half. Combine cracker crumbs and seasonings.
Coat chicken in this mixture.

title: eggplant with shrimp
directions: Cook eggplant in 1-quart boiling water with 1 teaspoon salt 10 minutes or until tender.
Drain and mash.
Cook shrimp in boiling water (shrimp boil may be added) and 1 teaspoon salt for 5 minutes. Cool, peel and chop.
Saute celery, onions, parsley and garlic in 2 tablespoons butter or margarine.
Add mashed eggplant to onion mixture and mix well.
Add eggs, salt (if now needed), pepper and all of bread crumbs except 2 tablespoons and mix well.
Stir in chopped shrimp.
Place in casserole dish and sprinkle reserved bread crumbs on top.
Drizzle remaining 2 tablespoons melted margarine over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until browned.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind or chop fruit into small pieces.
Add remaining ingredients, mix well.
Add a small amount of pineapple juice.
If relish is to dry, add sugar to taste.
May be stored airtight in refrigerator for a month.

title: freezer beef squares
directions: Mix well.
Pat into 15 x 9-inch ungreased jelly roll pan.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Separate slightly.
Cook uncovered at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cover. Label and freeze (no longer than 2 months).

title: wassail
directions: Place all the ingredients in a large pot.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Reduce the heat.
Partially cover the pot and simmer for 1 hour.
Serve hot.
Makes 12 servings.

title: chocolate-caramel layer squares
directions: Combine caramels and 1/3 cup of the milk in top of double boiler.
Melt, stirring constantly, until completely melted. Remove from heat (keep warm so it will not harden).

title: pineapple alaska
directions: In a small electric mixing bowl, combine egg white, water and nonfat dry milk powder.
Beat at high speed until stiff enough to hold shape.
Reduce to low speed and gradually add granulated sugar and lemon juice.
Return to high speed and continue beating about 5 minutes or until stiff.
Blend in egg yolk.
Fold in crushed pineapple.
Spoon into ice cube tray.
Place in freezer for about 2 hours or until thoroughly chilled.
Makes 6 servings. Has 110 calories each serving.

title: chicken loaf
directions: Mix together and bake in microwave-safe casserole dish at High power for 15 minutes.

title: hearty lasagne soup
directions: In a large skillet, cook beef with garlic powder until browned; drain.
Add broth, tomatoes and Italian seasoning.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in pasta.
Cook over medium heat for 10 minutes or until pasta is tender.
Stir in 1/4 cup Parmesan.
Serve with additional cheese, if desired.

title: prune cake
directions: Cream together the sugar, eggs and oil.
Add the prunes.
Sift together the flour and the spices.
Add this to the sugar/egg mixture.
Add nuts.
Grease or line a 1/2 pound cake pan.
Start cake in cold oven, then bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: the world's easiest pickles
directions: Put cucumbers, onions and peppers into a large container.
Mix marinade
well and pour over cucumbers.
Refrigerate for 2 weeks. Transfer to clean jars and refrigerate.

title: green chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute onions and chilies in skillet.
Add cream of chicken and cream of mushroom soup, 2 cans chicken broth from deboned chicken and simmer 5 to 10 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine meal, flour and onion.
Add egg.
Gradually beat in milk.
Drop from a spoon into hot fat; fry until golden brown. Drain on absorbent paper.
Makes 16 hush puppies.

title: meat roll
directions: Combine ground beef, egg, cracker crumbs, onion, 1/3 cup tomato sauce, salt, oregano and pepper.
Mix well and form into a flat rectangle, about 10 x 12-inches, on waxed paper.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese evenly over meat mixture.
Roll up like a jelly roll and press ends of roll to seal.
Place in shallow baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Pour off excess fat.
Pour on remaining tomato sauce and bake an additional 20 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chili
directions: Fry meat in a small amount of grease until pink is gone.
Add onion, green pepper and garlic.
Fry until onion is clear.
Add 1 1/2 or 2 tomato cans of water; let cook for 20 minutes.
Just before serving, add 1 tablespoon of flour to thicken.

title: face paint
directions: Mix Crisco, cornstarch and white flour.
Add glycerin.
Add food coloring.
Apply a thin layer of cold cream to the face.
For 1 child.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Mix jello, sugar, salt and boiling water.
Mix well and chill until thick.
Add cottage cheese, Cool Whip and pineapple.
Mix well and chill until firm.

title: country style chicken kiev
directions: Combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, basil, oregano, garlic salt and salt.
Dip chicken pieces in butter.
(Set remaining butter aside.)
Roll in crumb mixture.
Place in shallow casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.
To leftover butter, add wine, onion and parsley.
Pour over baked chicken.
Bake 2 or 3 minutes more.
Serves 4.

title: barbecue meat balls
directions: Moisten bread crumbs with milk.
Combine with ground meat, salt and pepper.
Shape into eight meat balls.
Pour into baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients to make sauce.
Pour around patties.
Set baking dish in oven.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes. (Any leftover may be frozen.)

title: honey mustard potato salad(low-fat)
directions: In serving bowl, combine yogurt, mustard, lemon juice, parsley, pepper and onion.
Gently stir in potatoes to coat. Cover and chill.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: beans and sausage
directions: Wash beans.
Start in one and a half quarts of water.
Add salt, sugar and ham bone.
Cook slowly until beans are almost done.
Slice sausage in one-fourth inch slices and add to beans. Add one cup of water and continue to cook for half an hour.
Serve in soup bowls with hot corn bread.

title: sugar-free applesauce raisin muffins
directions: Beat together egg, oil and applesauce.
Add flour, soda, baking powder and spices.
Beat well.
Stir in raisins and spoon batter into muffin wells.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until firm to touch.
Delicious with cream cheese.
Serves 12.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix water, sugar and yeast.
When it rises, add flour, salt and oil.
Mix and knead for several minutes.
Knead into a ball. Cover; let rise, then pinch into 18 rolls.
Bake at 325° until nice and brown.
Can be made into 2 loaves.

title: frozen mocha sundae pie
directions: Crush cookies into fine crumbs; combine with melted butter. Press into sides and bottom of 9-inch metal pie plate.
Freeze. Melt chocolate and stir in sugar and butter; add evaporated milk slowly.
Cook mixture until thickened, stirring constantly; chill. Fill crust with slightly softened ice cream.
Freeze again until hard.
Spread cooled chocolate mixture over ice cream.
Sprinkle with walnuts.
Freeze until ready to serve.

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Combine first six ingredients in electric blender.
Cover and blend on low speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased, 9-inch pie pan.
Let stand about 5 minutes, then sprinkle with coconut.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: "philly" bell cheese ball
directions: Combine
cold
pack
cheese
food
and
softened
cream cheese, mixing until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Mold into bell shapes using 2 cold pack containers lined with
plastic wrap.
Chill until firm; unmold.
Garnish with chopped
parsley and pimento strips, if desired.
Yield: 2 bells.

title: dilly casserole bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast over warm water; stir to dissolve.
Heat cottage cheese until warm.
Combine in mixing bowl the sugar, onion, butter, dill seed, salt, baking soda, egg and yeast.
Add flour, a little at a time, to make a stiff batter, beating well after each addition.
Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled (50 to 60 minutes).
Stir down with 25 vigorous strokes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck and large onion; drain.
Add pepper, garlic powder, cumin, chili seasoning and pinto beans; mix well.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with corn tortillas (torn into pieces).
Cover with 1/2 meat mixture and top with Velveeta cheese.
Add other 1/2 meat mixture; top with Velveeta cheese again.
Top with 1 can cream of mushroom soup mixed with Ro-Tel.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 12 to 16 people.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese. Place in 9 x 13 baking pan. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes uncovered.

title: yellow squash muffins
directions: In 2-quart saucepan,

cook chopped squash in 1 cup water until soft and able to mash. Add more squash if necessary or water. Add sugar, eggs and butter to hot mixture. Beat in dry ingredients. The batter should be cake mix consistency. Add more water to batter to make smooth like cake mix consistency.

Pour into 16 greased muffin tins. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes. Cool. Good frozen for weeks. Makes 16 muffins. Can do ahead. Summer squash is always plentiful and finding delicious and nutritious recipes are appreciated. This is good for any meal or snack.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix together and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: seafood salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Chop celery, Italian peppers or green pepper and onions.
Mix together tuna, shrimp and crab meat. Stir in mayonnaise to taste to consistency desired.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together.
Make into small balls.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: fresh vegetable dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well and let age a little in the refrigerator before using.

title: red beans and rice
directions: In skillet, heat oil over med. heat. Saute onion, bell pepper, garlic in oil for 3-4 minutes. Empty kidney beans in large saucepan. Stir cooked vegetables into beans. Add all seasonings. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to simmer for 30 minutes. Slice sausage and add to beans, continue to simmer for 30 minutes more. Prepare rice as directed. Remove bay leaves from beans.
Serve over rice.

title: small easy cheesecakes
directions: You will need 16 baking cups.

title: zucchini rounds
directions: Mix together; drop by tablespoon in hot butter or oil and fry.

title: cheese cake
directions: Cream together sugar and cream cheese.	Set aside.
Mix water and
Jell-O;
cool.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with graham cracker
crumbs.
Reserve some crumbs.
Whip Carnation milk. Slowly
add
cream	cheese mixture, Jell-O and vanilla. Pour into pan
and
sprinkle	top
with cracker crumbs. Chill thoroughly and cut into squares.

title: apricot salad
directions: Heat apricot
nectar
to
a
boil.
Add
jello, crushed pineapple and juice.
Cool	1/2
of
this mixture in a mold or pan.
When set,
spread with a mixture of cream cheese, mayonnaise and walnuts.
Pour remaining liquid over top and let set in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: violet froth
directions: Combine ingredients in a blender until smooth.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies in food processor or blender until mixture resembles dirt.
Set aside.
Cream the cheese, margarine and powdered sugar.
Mix pudding mixes and milk, 1 to 2 minutes until well blended.
Fold pudding mixture into cream cheese mixture with a rubber spatula.
Fold in whipped topping.

title: caramel date cake
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar and butter in bowl. Mix in dates and pecans. Mix egg, buttermilk and baking soda in small bowl and add to flour mixture with vanilla. Spoon into greased and floured 8 x 8-inch cake pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 50 minutes or until cake tests done. Cool for several minutes, then remove and cool completely.

title: easy cherry chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees. Grease and flour 13x9x2

pan. Beat eggs in large bowl. Stir in can mix (dry, cherry pie filling and oil until blended. Spread in pan. Bake 35 to 40 minutes. (the surface of cake will be bumpy). Cool completely. Prepare chocolate pudding as directed on pkg. for pie, Let stand until thickened. Spread over cake. Store covered in refrigerator. Cut into squares. Can top with cool whip and cherries on top of squares.

title: white chocolate haystacks
directions: Place Crisco and white chocolate, in chunks, in microwave, stirring every 30 to 45 seconds.
Add pretzels and peanuts when chocolate is melted and mix until all ingredients are coated. Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper to cool.

title: m & m cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugars, beaten eggs and vanilla together. Sift together remaining ingredients and add to sugar mixture. Stir in 1 cup M&M's and drop by teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes or until light brown.

title: cafe con leche
directions: In a saucepan, bring milk to a boil over medium heat; stir constantly.
When milk begins to boil, turn off heat.
Add coffee and sugar and stir until dissolved.
Serve in 4 clear, heatproof glasses.
Serves 4.

title: frog eye salad
directions: Cook first 5
ingredients until it thickens.
Add lemon juice.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Toss carrots, broccoli and cauliflower.
Mix together celery soup, mayonnaise, Cheddar cheese, diced celery, fresh onion, salt and pepper.
Mix all together.
Spread out into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with 2 tablespoons melted butter mixed with 1/2 cup seasoned bread crumbs.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over this.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until vegetables are just tender.

title: beer bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In mixing bowl, place flour (measuring by spooning it into a cup and leveling the surface; don't shake down).
Add sugar and stir well with the spoon.
Add beer all at once and before stirring break the egg into it.
Mix the egg into the beer and stir the mix with a spoon.
Stir long enough to mix well.
Put batter into a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake 60 to 65 minutes.

title: carrot casserole(lisa's favorite)
directions: Cook carrots sliced crosswise.
Saute onion in margarine.
Add flour, salt and dry mustard, mixed together.
Add milk and cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add celery seed.
Layer carrots, slices of Cheddar cheese and milk mixture into casserole dish.
Cover with milk mixture and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Cover with buttered bread crumbs the last 5 minutes.

title: scalloped spinach
directions: Cook spinach with onion until completely thawed; drain thoroughly.
Add milk and cheese to saucepan; heat just until the cheese is melted.
Mix in beaten eggs.
Stir in spinach to milk mixture.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top; dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: garbanzo beans with cheese
directions: Mix beans, sauce, onion, oil, salt, pepper and oregano in a baking pan; cook on 350° until sauce thickens.
Add top with 1 cup grated cheese, Mozzarella cheese and Muenster cheese.
Cover and return to oven until cheese is melted.

title: sunny scalloped potatoes
directions: Coat potatoes with flour and seasonings.
Place in 11 x 7-inch dish.
Heat cheese and milk over low heat.
Add green peppers, onion and pimiento.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Combine cake mix, eggs, butter, water and cinnamon in large bowl.
Beat at low speed with electric mixer until moistened.
Beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Stir in zucchini.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Sprinkle with walnuts.
Bake in preheated oven 30 to 35 minutes until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Dust with confectioners sugar or drizzle with glaze, if desired.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix oil, vanilla and apples together.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: winter white chili
directions: Soak beans in water overnight.
In the morning, discard water and wash beans.
Put beans and 6 cups water in crock-pot.
Dice onion and garlic and add to crock-pot.
Add salt, pepper and green chili.
Cube turkey breast and put into pot.
(Use jalapenos for extra zip, if you dare.)
Cover and cook on high for six hours, watching to make sure the beans don't dry up.
Add water as needed. Cook beans for as long as it takes for them to get soft.
This is excellent the second day, too.
Serve with hot corn bread.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into 2 pie shells.
Bake at 350° until firm.

title: angel hair with tomatoes, basil and garlic
directions: Cook pasta; drain.
Meanwhile, spray a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray; heat oil.
Add garlic and cook for 1 minute. Add tomatoes, basil, salt and pepper.
Cook for 3 minutes.
Add hot pasta to skillet; toss well.
Add chicken broth and stir. Toss with Parmesan cheese and serve immediately.
Serves 8.

title: tuna quick casserole
directions: In a baking dish, combine noodles, sour cream, onion, cottage cheese, tuna, salt, Tabasco and Worcestershire.
Mix well. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese and paprika on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Mash in oleo.
Add Karo and mix well. Stir in eggs (beaten). Line pie tin with pecans.
Pour mixture over pecans.
Bake at 375°.

title: rotten coconut cake
directions: Mix sugar, sour cream and coconut and let marinate 24 hours in refrigerator.
Mix in 12 ounces of Cool Whip.
Bake cake as directed on box, then split both layers and frost.

title: low-fat stroganoff
directions: Brown ground turkey and onion.
While this cooks, put cream cheese, evaporated milk and soup into another large saucepan.
Stir until melted together; set aside.
Undercook your noodles by a minute or two and drain.
Stir all ingredients together.
Add frozen corn if using.
Pour in a 2 to 3-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Serves four.

title: five flavor pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Combine flour with baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternating with milk.
Add the five flavors.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs and add remaining ingredients.
Bake in unbaked pie shell at 325° for 25 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: green river punch
directions: Combine Kool-Aid, water and sugar in punch bowl. Add half the sherbet and half the ice cream.
Mix well. Add ginger ale, remaining sherbet and ice cream. Stir until frothy.
Serves 24.

title: peanut butter sticks
directions: Trim crusts on bread and cut each slice into 5 strips.
Put in 200° oven for 2 hours.
This will make them crisp.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding mix and milk together with electric mixer.
Add other ingredients in order.
Layer in dish with bananas and wafers.

title: potatoes with sour cream
directions: Place a layer of potatoes in bottom of a greased shallow baking dish.
Add a little onion and sour cream.
Season with salt and pepper.
Repeat layers and finish with a layer of potatoes. Melt 2 tablespoons butter in a saucepan.
Stir in the milk and pour over potatoes.
Dot with remaining butter.
Cover and bake in preheated oven at 375° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 20 minutes longer.
Serves 2 or 3.

title: quick berry parfaits
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; put in blender.
Add juice and water; blend 10 seconds.
Add topping; blend 15 seconds.
Pour half of mixture in a glass.
Let stand 1 minute; top with remaining mixture.

title: oyster cracker snack mix
directions: Place oyster crackers, pretzels and nuts in a large bowl.
Set aside.
Mix oil, garlic salt, dill weed and Ranch dressing well. Pour over snacks and mix well.
Can be kept in container for a long time.
Great for parties and the holidays.

title: chicken noodle soup with vegetables
directions: Heat all ingredients, except noodles and bouillon, to boiling in 4-quart Dutch oven; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until chicken is done, about 45 minutes.
Take chicken out of soup; cool slightly.
Remove bones and cut meat up (I use kitchen scissors).

title: german cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix yeast and warm water.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Blend in Bisquick.
Add cold water.
Mix into balls (4) and roll out into rectangle, 1/4-inch thick.
Melt 1/2 stick butter and brush onto each rolled out rectangle.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Roll as for jelly roll.
Slice into 1-inch pieces.
Lay, cut side down, on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Brush with butter and roll in cinnamon mixture. Serve warm.

title: cucumber spread
directions: Peel and grate 1 medium size cucumber (drain well between paper towels).
Mix with other ingredients, then chill for 30 minutes.
Serve on crackers or for finger sandwiches.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat egg yolks, stir in milk.
Add lime juice slowly.
This mixture will thicken; pour into cool graham cracker pie shell. Make meringue of the four egg whites, beating in powdered sugar. Sprinkle a little grated lime rind on top.
Brown meringue at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions in butter slowly, covered.
Cook 15 minutes on low (not browned).
Add salt, sugar and flour, stir well.
Put all in crock-pot with bouillon.
Cook 6 to 8 hours on low or 3 hours on high.
Place croutons in bowl.
Add soup.
Top with grated cheeses.
Brown a little under broiler.

title: tartar sauce(serve with fried fish.)
directions: Combine above and chill.

title: banana carrot bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 X 5 X 3 inch loaf pan.
In a mixing bowl combine oil and sugar.
Add eggs; mix well.
Combine flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon; gradually add to the creamed mixture alternating with bananas.
Stir in carrots and pecans.
Pour batter into the greased loaf pan.
Bake for 55 to 65 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove to a wire rack to cool completely.
Makes one loaf.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan until done at 400°.

title: banana bread
directions: Grease only the bottom of loaf pan.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix shortening, sugar, eggs and bananas together and beat.
Add dry ingredients all at once and beat with a spoon. Mix until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Cool in pan for 30 minutes and turn out.

title: quick chicken chasseur
directions: Dredge chicken in cornstarch.
In large skillet, brown coated chicken in oil.
Stir in seasonings and scallions.
Cook 2 minutes longer.
Add broth and sherry (wine).
Cover; simmer 10 minutes. Gently stir in mushrooms and tomatoes.
Cover; simmer 5 minutes longer.
Serve over rice.
Sauce may be served separately.
Yields 6 servings.

title: apple raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, combine flour, wheat germ, oats, baking powder, cinnamon and ginger.
In blender, combine juice, oil, egg, raisins and dried apples.
Blend on medium speed until the raisins and apples are chopped.
Stir this with the dry ingredients.
Combine thoroughly.
Drop batter by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Flatten with a fork.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes, until the top springs back when touched.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Let yeast dissolve in water. In a bowl, mix together sugar, oil and eggs. Once yeast is dissolved, add oil mixture to it. Then add flour and salt. Stir just enough to mix. Place covered bowl in refrigerator for at least 4 hours or up to 8 days. Make into desired shapes. Oil tops and let rise 3 hours before baking. Bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: crawfish dip
directions: Saute the green onions in melted margarine. Stir in flour. Add crawfish tails and fat.
Continue to saute. Stir in lemon juice, mushrooms, seasonings and soup.
Keep hot in chafing dish. Serve with Melba rounds.

title: poppy seed loaf delight
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer for 2 minutes.
Pour into 2 loaf pans or 4 small ones.
Lightly grease loaf pans.
Can use Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350° until toothpick comes out clean. Let cook 5 minutes more.
Pour glaze over warm cake.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop and flatten with a glass bottom, dipped in water.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Don't overbake. Make them small!

title: cheesy chicken crescents
directions: Boil chicken; cook and pick from bones.
Mix soups, half cup of cheese and milk in saucepan.
Warm.
Spray loaf pan with Pam, then coat pan bottom with soup mixture.
Put mixed chicken and remaining cheese in crescent rolls.
Place on pan.
Bake at 325° for approximately 20 minutes.
Use remaining soup mixture as gravy.

title: coffee mousse
directions: Heat marshmallows in heavy Dutch oven in 2/3 cup cream until soft and smooth.
Remove from heat and stir in Kahlua.
Whip rest of cream and fold into cooled marshmallow mixture.
Pour into bowl or dessert dishes.
May decorate with chopped walnuts or shaved chocolate.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix jello and boiling water and cool.
Mix ingredients and add jello mixture. Bake in greased and floured 9x12 pan at 350 for 35 minutes.

title: old-fashioned chess pie
directions: Mix ingredients together; pour into your favorite pie crust. Bake at 450° for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 350°.
Bake until firm.

title: sausage bread
directions: Spread dough on cookie sheet.
Saute sausage, onion and peppers.
Sprinkle all ingredients onto center of dough.
Fold closed.
Brush with raw, scrambled egg.
Bake at 350° approximately 20 to 30 minutes.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Drain broccoli thoroughly.
Combine first 6 ingredients.
Stir in corn bread mix.
Pour mixture into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: peanut butter
directions: Shell 4 cups of peanuts and roast.
Remove skins, grind the peanuts through a food chopper or meat grinder, add 1 teaspoon salt.
Remove 1/2 cup of the crushed peanuts, grind the remainder the second or third time using a smaller knife or take up the tension of the plate until the grinder is hard to turn.
Mix coarse butter with the fine.
Fill into clean, sterile jars.
Pack the peanut butter so that all air is expelled to prevent rancidity.
Seal the container air tight.
If the peanut butter is to be stored for several months, process for 10 minutes in a water bath to remove air from top of the jar.
Store in cool, dry, dark place.

title: salmon with brown sugar glaze
directions: Spray rack of broiler pan. Preheat the broiler. Sprinkle salmon with salt and pepper on both sides; place on broiler pan. Combine brown sugar, mustard and chopped dill. Spoon glaze on top of salmon. Broil 7 inches from the heat and broil until lightly browned and just opaque in the center, about 6 minutes.

title: spam hot dish
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Makes 1 large 9 x 13-inch casserole or 2 hot dishes.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: grape-nuts pudding
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients.
Remove from fire.
Add remaining ingredients, stir.
Put in dish and cover with coconut.
Cool.

title: almond stuffing
directions: Put bread crumbs and milk in bowl.
Add salt, pepper and melted shortening; mix well.
Stir in almonds.
Makes 2 cups stuffing.

title: rigatoni with sausage sauce
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions;
drain and set aside.
In a deep, heavy frying pan, melt the margarine and crumbled sausage.
Cook slowly, stirring occasionally, until sausage is lightly browned.
Add cream and wine to skillet with sausage and increase heat to medium-high.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to a gentle boil and cook, stirring occasionally, until sauce is slightly thickened, about 5 minutes.
Mix in the hot pasta and Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle lightly with nutmeg and serve at once with additional grated Parmesan.

title: cornmeal gravy(over 50 years old)
directions: Have some grease or lard in a pan on the stove.
Get it real hot and add the cornmeal.
Stir it until the meal is brown.
Stir in water or milk and stir constantly until it's as thick as you like it.
That should serve about 4 people.

title: broccoli-potato soup
directions: Cook broccoli, potatoes and onions together in a large kettle with a small amount of water until the potatoes and broccoli are tender.
Drain.
In a large saucepan, melt margarine.
Add flour and whisk until smooth.
Add 3 cups water and bouillon.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened.
Add 1 cup milk and continue stirring and cooking until well blended.
Pour mixture into kettle with vegetables.
Add cheese and pepper; heat through, but do not boil.
Serve immediately.
Goes great with sourdough rolls.
Serves 6.

title: orange-raisin sauce
directions: In two-cup measuring cup, combine water and cornstarch; stir in rest of ingredients.
Microwave until thickened.
Delicious served on ham.

title: jumbo raisin cookies
directions: Sift the last 7 ingredients together.
Boil raisins in water for 5 minutes and cool.
Cream together butter and sugar.
Add vanilla, cooled raisins and nuts.
Add sifted flour mixture to other ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet. Cook 10 minutes at 350°.

title: nora's cake
directions: Grease and flour tube pan. Mix ingredients thoroughly; add 1 cup hot water and combine just before you put cake in oven. Bake at 300° for 1 hour without opening oven door.

title: italian stuffed shells
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in 2 cups boiling water and set aside. In a large skillet, brown the ground beef, onion and garlic.
Stir in the tomato paste, oregano leaves and the bouillon liquid with 1 teaspoon sugar and simmer about 20 minutes.

title: cherry dump
directions: In an 8 x 12 or 9 x 9 ungreased pan, dump cherry pie filling and spread evenly. Dump pineapple chunks evenly over cherry pie filling. Sprinkle one single layer white cake mix, dry, on top of pineapple. Combine butter or margarine, coconut and nuts. Sprinkle mixture on top of cake mix. Bake at 350°
for 50 minutes. Serve with whipped topping. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: french silk pie
directions: Cream butter, gradually add sugar, cream together well.
Melt chocolate and blend with butter mixture.
Add vanilla.
Add eggs one at a time beating 5 minutes each time (you can use electric mixer if desired).
Pour into cooled crust.
Chill 1 to 2 hours. Top with whipped topping and walnuts to serve.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix together first 8 ingredients.
Squeeze all juice out of sauerkraut before adding other ingredients.
Sprinkle chopped parsley and crumbled bacon over top before serving.
This can be made several days before using.

title: venison roast
directions: Let venison roast thaw in water.
Wash real good.
Cook in crock-pot or in roasting pan at 350° until done.
Real good.

title: oreo sundae dessert
directions: Put first 5 ingredients into a saucepan.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Cook 4 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: chicken breasts parmesan
directions: Combine the bread crumbs and parsley on a plate.
Place the cheese on another plate.
In a small bowl, lightly beat the egg whites with water.

title: rice meatballs
directions: Mix rice, beef, egg, onion, salt, pepper and 1/2 cup tomato juice.
Form into 18 balls and put in skillet.
Add sugar to remaining juice.
Pour over meatballs.
Bring to a boil, then cover and simmer for 15 to 25 minutes.

title: french toast(stuffed)
directions: Layer 3 layers of bread, cream cheese between layers, lots of cinnamon on cream cheese.

title: ranch dip for vegetables
directions: *Celery sticks, carrot sticks, green pepper, etc., for dipping.

title: cabbage surprise
directions: In large skillet, blend soup, sour cream, and caraway.
Heat. Add cabbage.
Cover and cook over low heat 20 minutes or until cabbage is tender.

title: shoyu chicken wings
directions: Disjoint wings, discarding tips.
Combine ingredients. Marinate at least 2 hours.
Place wings in a single layer in a shallow baking dish. Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes. Best cooked just before serving.
Great for feeding a bunch of hungry kids!

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except potato chips, almonds and cheese.
Place in large casserole dish (usually 9 x 13-inch).
Top with remaining ingredients.
Cover and let set in the refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: creamy squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in salted water until tender. Drain well. In large dish mix rest of ingredients with squash & onion. Bake in 2 qt. casserole dish at 350 degrees for about 30 minutes, or until heated through. Sprinkle a few crackers over top if you desire.

title: punch
directions: Mix together.
Triple it to fill punch bowl; increase 5 times for 100 people.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan or layers until done.

title: chili con queso
directions: In crock-pot, cook 1 large onion in butter until softened. Add all other ingredients.
Cook on high for about 4 hours or until all ingredients are mixed together and piping hot.
Serve with scoop Fritos or tortilla chips.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add to cream mixture.
Place flour in a large bowl.
Add dates, orange slices and nuts.
Stir to coat each piece.
Add flour mixture and coconut to creamed mixture.
Bake in a greased 9 or 10-inch tube pan at 250° for 2 1/2 hours.
Remove from oven.
Pour hot glaze over top of cake.
Let set in pan overnight.

title: mama's chocolate pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, salt and cocoa in heavy saucepan.
Add milk, stirring over heat.
Then add eggs, butter and vanilla while beating with electric beater over medium heat.
Pudding done when mixture bubbles up and has become thick.
Remove from heat.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: Melt margarine; add to graham cracker crumbs.
Press into bottom of greased 7 x 11-inch pan.
Spread coconut over crumb layer, then chocolate chips, then
butterscotch chips, then nuts. Pour Eagle Brand milk evenly over nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Cut into small oblong pieces.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Cook bacon and set aside for garnish.
Bake potatoes until tender.
Remove from oven and cool.
Chop scallions.
When potatoes have cooled, hollow out potato from the top.
Put pulp, scallions, parsley, sour cream, mayonnaise, butter, salt, pepper and Parmesan cheese in a bowl and mix until creamy.
Spoon into potato skins and add cheese and bacon.
Bake in oven at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: forgotten stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into covered casserole and cook for 5 hours at 250°.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
(Mix the soup and water separately and pour over the other ingredients. This makes a rich, brown gravy.)

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on package; set aside. In saucepan, combine soup, milk, chopped onion and pepper.
Place over low heat and add cubed cheese.
Stir occasionally until cheese melts.
Combine macaroni and tuna in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Blend in cheese sauce.
Bake, uncovered, in preheated 325° oven for about 20 minutes.

title: blackened sea scallops (blue cheese sauce)
directions: Cover sea scallops with blackened seasoning and let sit for
a few minutes.
Heat gas grill and put on fish screen or aluminum foil on grill.
Grill until tender.

title: easy casserole
directions: Cut beef, reserve 1/4 cup for topping.
Brown rest of beef and onions in bacon drippings.
Drain, melt oleo, add flour and blend. Gradually add milk.
Cook slowly stirring constantly until thickened.
Add cheese, stir until melted.
Mix with macaroni in 2-quart casserole.
Top with dried beef.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken macaroni casserole
directions: In a large saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in flour until combined.
Add cream and 1 1/2 cups of the broth, all at once. Stir until smooth. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat.
Add the cheese and stir until melted.
Stir in macaroni, chicken, pimentos, salt and pepper.
Add additional broth if needed.
Pour into a 3-quart baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes or until heated through.
Sprinkle with parsley if desired.

title: party spaghetti
directions: Chop onions and brown onions in margarine or butter.
Add garlic and meat.
Cook until meat seems to be done; add tomatoes. Cook slowly.
Cook thin spaghetti
per instructions on package. Drain spaghetti.
Add grated cheese and olives to sauce while hot. Stir in spaghetti and serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Cook rice.
Combine cooked rice, soup and cheese.
Layer broccoli, then rice mixture.
Bake until heated through.
Serve.

title: chili
directions: Cook over low heat for 2 to 3 hours, stirring frequently. Watch the bottom of kettle, chili burns easily.

title: apple and potato fidget(an unusual way to cook chicken and apples.)
directions: Use a 3-pint casserole dish.
Melt the butter and oil; brown the chicken on both sides.
Remove from casserole and place to one side.
Peel and slice the onion, place in the casserole and cook for 2 or 3 minutes until soft.
Peel and slice the potatoes, put into the casserole and stir together with the onion.
Cook for 10 minutes with the lid on.
Peel and slice the apples, add them to the casserole and cook for a further 5 minutes.
Sprinkle the flour over the mixture and stir in.
Add the apple juice and bring to the boil, stirring.

title: grandma miller's dressing
directions: Beat and cook first five ingredients until thickened.
Beat the cream cheese until soft.
Add the grated onion.
Add the cooked ingredients.
Mix well and add pepper to taste.
Great served on sliced cucumbers.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Toss together blueberries, lemon juice and vanilla.
Spoon into buttered 8-inch square pan.
In bowl, combine vanilla, Bisquick, sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Sprinkle over blueberry mixture.
Dot with butter.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes at 350° or until crispy.
You can try canned apples, cherries, etc.

title: layered chocolate pudding dessert
directions: Cream and pat first three ingredients into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes; cool.
Mix next 3 ingredients until creamy and spread on crust.
Beat remaining 3 ingredients until thickened and spread on top.
Spread rest of whipped topping on top and sprinkle with crushed nuts.
Chill for a few hours in refrigerator.

title: salmon ball
directions: Roll thin 1 package pie crust mix and cut with small biscuit cutter.
Place smoked oyster in center of dough round.
Fold; press edges together and bake.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together, hamburger, chicken rice soup, egg, cornflakes and worcestershire sauce.
Top with little butter.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: chocolate cream fruit dip
directions: In a small mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and chocolate syrup. Fold in Marshmallow Creme. Cover and refrigerate until serving. Serve with fruit. Makes about 2 cups.

title: man trapper beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat into narrow strips about 2 inches long and dust with 3 tablespoons flour mixed with salt and pepper.
In a skillet, brown meat and onion in 2 tablespoons Crisco for about 3 minutes, or until meat is browned.
Add remaining Crisco to skillet and stir in remaining 1 tablespoon of flour.
Gradually stir in beef stock and cook, stirring, until sauce is smooth and thickened.
Stir in mustard and sour cream; cover and cook over very low heat for about 1 hour, or until meat is tender.
Do not let sauce boil.
Serve over rice or pasta.

title: poppy seed bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Mix thoroughly for 1 to 2 minutes.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
While warm, glaze with:

title: chimichangas
directions: In medium saucepan, combine meat, water and spices.
Bring to boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer about 2 hours or until meat is very tender.
Uncover and boil rapidly about 15 minutes or until water has almost evaporated.
Remove from heat.
Using 2 forks, shred meat very fine.
Wrap tortillas in foil; heat in 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Spoon about 1/4 cup meat mixture onto each tortilla.
Fold up envelope fashion; fasten with toothpick.

title: simple angel food bars
directions: Combine ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake at 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine in a casserole dish.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Mix cabbage, noodles, onions, almonds and sesame seeds in large bowl.
Combine oil, vinegar, salt and pepper, brown sugar and 1/2 flavor packet together, mix well.
Pour dressing over cabbage mixture and serve chilled.

title: crazy cake
directions: Put ingredients in bowl; mix.
Make 3 holes; into each hole, put one of the following:
2 teaspoons vanilla, 2 tablespoons vinegar, 10 tablespoons melted oleo.
Over this, pour 2 cups cold water.
Stir until smooth.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean, about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring margarine, water and cocoa to a boil in heavy saucepan over medium heat, stirring well.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour into a well-greased and floured jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch).
Bake at 350° in a preheated oven for 30 minutes.
Ice with the following frosting.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: beef 'n beer
directions: Brown meat, onions and garlic in butter.
Add flour.
Mix well to coat beef.
Add consomme and beer.
Season with rest of ingredients.
Bake in 300° oven until meat is tender, about 3 hours.
Serve with noodles or rice.

title: cheese dip
directions: Cook sausage until done.
Drain.
Mix remaining ingredients with sausage and cook in microwave, crock-pot or stove top until Velveeta is melted.
Serve with chips.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with rice.
Mix soups, water, mushrooms, water chestnuts and almonds and pour over rice. Place chicken on top of mixture and season lightly with salt and pepper.
Cover with foil.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Uncover and bake for an additional 1/2 hour.

title: our version of chicken diane
directions: Place chicken breast halves between sheets of waxed paper; pound slightly with mallet.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Heat 1 1/2 tablespoons each of oil and margarine in large skillet. Cook chicken over high heat for 3 minutes on each side; transfer to warm serving platter.
Add green onions, lemon juice, brandy, parsley and the Dijon mustard to pan.
Cook for 20 seconds, whisking constantly.
Whisk in broth.
Stir until sauce is smooth. Whisk in remaining butter and oil.
Pour sauce over chicken. Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit.
Mix fruit.
Sprinkle Jell-O over fruit. Stir thoroughly.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Add pecans, marshmallows and sour cream.
Stir well, fold in Cool Whip. Return to refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Serves 15.

title: sauce for barbecue
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan; bring to a boil, stirring constantly until sugar melts.
Boil, uncovered, until reduced to 1 1/3 cups.
Use for chicken or pork.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Mix and pour into a Pam-sprayed 3-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: glazed peanuts
directions: Mix the peanuts, sugar and water; boil until water is gone. Pour on cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes at 300°.
Remove
from oven; stir and sprinkle salt.
Return to oven for 15 minutes. Stir again; bake 10 minutes more.
Remove and cool.
Makes 6 cups. Great for Christmas gift!

title: corned beef salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water; add vinegar.
Cool until almost set, then add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a ring mold and refrigerate until firm.

title: cabbage and beef soup
directions: Brown meat in heavy 6-quart kettle or pan.
Chop celery and onion.
Cook until onions are transparent.
Add other ingredients. Chop or cut cabbage into bite size pieces.
Bring to a boil for 20 minutes.
Add salt, pepper and sugar.
Reduce heat and let simmer for 2 to 3 hours.
Keep adding extra water as needed.

title: oyster dressing
directions: Boil turkey giblets with celery and onion.
Set aside.
Toast loaf of bread and tear into pieces.

title: orange delight salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate a few hours before serving.
Very easy and tastes great!

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients in mixing bowl except parsley and olives. Divide in half and form into 2 balls.
Coat with parsley by rolling, then decorate with olive slices.
Chill an hour or more before serving with party crackers.
Stores well in refrigerator, tightly covered.

title: easy corn chowder
directions: Peel and cut potatoes into chunks.
Boil about 15 minutes. While potatoes are cooking, saute onion in butter or margarine. Drain potatoes and add onion, cream-style corn, milk and salt and pepper to taste.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix beaten eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Add flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Add apples; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix first five ingredients. Beat 10 minutes with electric mixer.
Fold in grated German chocolate and the chocolate chips. Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: egg rolls
directions: Brown ground beef. Shred vegetables, beef, carrots and cabbage. Squeeze out excess juice after shredding. Add soy sauce, salt and garlic powder to taste.
Roll small amounts into egg roll wrappers.

title: quick muffin rolls
directions: Mix and put into oiled muffin tins.
Bake at 450° or 475°. Makes 12 rolls.

title: golden biscuits
directions: Combine the flour, baking powder, salt and sugar in bowl.
Cut in shortening until the mixture looks like coarse corn meal.
Add milk and mix until the dough holds together.
Knead a few strokes on a lightly floured flat surface.
Roll and cut with biscuit cutter.
Place on an ungreased baking sheet and bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cheese cake pie
directions: Beat cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped cream, blending well. Spoon into crust; chill until set, at least 4 hours.
Serve with topping or glazed.

title: zucchini pickles
directions: Grate or chop (or use blender) zucchini and onions.
Put 5 tablespoons salt (canning) over this mixture and let set overnight. Drain and rinse.
Put all ingredients into a 5-quart cooker.
Bring to a boil, then simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Put in hot jars and seal.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix all together into a ball.
Roll in nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: texas pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in a pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix well with mixer. Pour into greased 2-quart baking dish.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Add sugar, oil, zucchini and vanilla; mix lightly but well.
Combine flour, salt, soda, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add dry ingredients to egg-zucchini mixture and stir until well blended.
Add nuts, if desired.
Pour into 2 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool on a rack.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Mix sugar and flour in large bowl.
Mix Coke, oil, margarine, cocoa and vanilla in saucepan.
Let come to boil.
Remove from heat and add marshmallows.
Pour over dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk, eggs and baking soda and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured oblong pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: stuffed potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Drain well.
Mix with hand mixer until creamy.
Add ingredients.
Bake for 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: joan's brown sugar cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Grease and flour 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Mix Veg-All, margarine, sour cream, chicken and soup.
Pour into pie shell.
Invert second pie shell on top.
Seal around edges; dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes, until golden brown.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage.
Drain and spread in a 9x13-inch casserole dish.
Combine eggs, onion, milk, salt, pepper and Bisquick, blending well.
Pour over sausage.
Sprinkle top with cheese.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain well; put potatoes in 2-quart casserole and put flour, salt, sausage and cheese in layers.
Pour milk over all; cover and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Uncover the last 10 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place beans in 1-inch salted water (1/4 teaspoon salt, if desired, to 1 cup water).
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Boil, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Cover and boil 4 to 6 minutes or until desired tenderness.
Drain.

title: corn dish
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve. Beat to let set for a few hours.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix well and let sit overnight before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken salad
directions: Squeeze juice from lemon over chicken and let stand for 10 minutes.
Mix
chicken,
celery, onions and cucumbers with mayonnaise,
salt
and pepper.
Refrigerate.
Add almonds just before serving.

title: annie hugh's punch
directions: Make a syrup of the sugar and water by boiling for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add tea and jello.
Add all fruit juice and let stand for 24 hours.
Add Hawaiian Punch and ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Melt chocolate almond bark; mix in Rice Krispies, nuts and marshmallows.
Pour into lightly buttered pizza pan.
Sprinkle with coconut and top with pieces of cherries.
Melt 2 to 3 squares of white almond bark with 1 tablespoon oil and drizzle over the top.
Refrigerate until set.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Cream butter; add sugar.
Blend in milk and flavorings.
Drain cherries.
Shape small amount of sugar mixture around each cherry. Chill at least 2 hours.
Melt chocolates and shortening and dip cherries.
Place on wax paper.
Store in airtight container in a cool place.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain all vegetables.
Mix everything else into the vegetables and refrigerate.

title: quick chili
directions: Fry hamburg and onion in Dutch oven.
Add cans of beans, soup and tomatoes and stir.
Simmer until hot.
Stir occasionally. Serves 9.

title: no cook peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix all ingredients together in large bowl. When combined and firm, place on pizza sheet or cookie sheet with sides.
Place in refrigerator until it hardens.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix shortening, 1 1/2 cups sugar and
eggs thoroughly.
Measure flour by dipping method.
Blend flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Stir in.
Shape dough in 1-inch balls. Roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons of sugar and cinnamon.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes. Cookies puff up at first, then flatten out.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Spoon into pie crust.
Cover with top crust.
Crimp edges to seal.
Slit top crust.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Easy and good.

title: fried fish
directions: Cut fish fillets into serving-size pieces. Combine flour, salt and pepper. Coat fish with flour mixture. Place fish in a frying pan containing about 1/8-inch hot (but not smoking) oil. Fry at moderate temperature for 4 to 5 minutes or until brown. Turn carefully and fry additional 4 to 5 minutes or until fish is brown and flaky and no longer translucent in the center. Drain on paper towels. Yield: 6 servings.

title: fruit cake
directions: Makes 2
large
cakes.
Mix well and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cake springs back when touched.

title: old fashioned ginger cookies(soft)
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Add egg.
Add molasses, then hot water with soda. Slowly add flour with spices.
Mix well and drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet 2-inches apart.
Bake in
a 400° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: tanny cake
directions: Beat eggs, vanilla, sugar and oil and mix well.
Add flour, powder, salt and milk; beat well.
Put in large cookie sheet, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and refrigerate.
Spread peanut butter on top when cool.
Melt chocolate and pour over peanut butter.

title: nine-day slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, celery, onions and green pepper.
Add 2 cups of sugar and blend well.

title: texas pecan cake
directions: Heat oven to 300°. Grease and flour 9 3/4-inch tube pan.

title: cucumber-chile granite
directions: Combine all ingredients except matchstick cucumber pieces, in a food processor or blender. Cover and process or blend until nearly smooth. Press mixture through a fine mesh strainer, 1/3 at a time, holding strainer over bowl to catch juices (you should have about 1 2/3 cups strained juices). Discard solids. Transfer strained juices to a 2-quart square baking dish. Cover and freeze for 3 to 4 hours or until firmly frozen. Break up frozen mixture. Transfer mixture to a chilled large bowl. Beat with an electric mixer until slushy, but not melted. Return to baking dish. Cover and freeze for 2 to 3 hours or until firm.

title: mustard-glazed pork chops
directions: In a small saucepan, whisk the brown sugar, Dijon mustard, vinegar, molasses and ground mustard until blended.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring frequently.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 2 to 3 minutes or until thickened.
Place pork chops in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish coated with nonstick cooking spray.
Top with sauce; turn to coat.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 18 to 22 minutes or until juices run clear, basting occasionally.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 1 hour. Seems better if frozen awhile.
M-mmm good!
Top with Banana Nut Bread Spread.

title: pineapple cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line bottom of Pyrex baking dish with pineapple. Mix flour and sugar.
Sprinkle mixture over pineapple. Cover with grated cheese.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top of cheese.
Pour melted margarine over crackers. Bake for 30 minutes.

title: fried chicken
directions: Wash and pat dry your favorite cuts of chicken.
Place, skin side down, in ungreased baking pan.
Sprinkle with Lawry's seasoning.
Cover pan with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Turn chicken and sprinkle with Lawry's again.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt in a mixing bowl.
Add corn meal, corn, diced onion, egg and beer.
Beat in oil.
Let set 5 minutes.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into 350° fat until brown.
Makes 42 small puppies.

title: french onion soup
directions: In saucepan cook onions in margarine until tender.
Add broth, water, worcestershire sauce.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat, simmer covered for 25 minutes.
Put bread into 4 oven proof bowls. Pour mixture over bread and sprinkle top of broth with mozzarella cheese.
Broil until cheese melts and is slightly brown. Serves 4.

title: freckle-faced taters
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix all ingredients together except cheese. Quarter hot potatoes lengthwise and place in a bake-and-serve dish.
Cover potatoes with mixture, then sprinkle grated cheese over them.

title: homemade cottage fries
directions: Leave skins on and wash potatoes thoroughly.
Slice potatoes in wedges or in rounds.
Layer in 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Chop carrots in rounds and slice onion; add to potatoes. Sprinkle on seasoning and bake at 400° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: apple crisp topping
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl and work together with hands, as heat from hands softens margarine.
Work until crumbly and small balls form.
Sprinkle over top of apples prepared as for a pie. Bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: basic cream sauce in vegetables
directions: Melt butter in a 2-quart measuring cup on High for 30 seconds to 1 minute.
Stir in flour and salt.
Microwave on High for 30 seconds.
Slowly stir in milk.
Microwave on High for 6 to 8 minutes, stirring several times.
Sauce should boil and thicken. Pour into 1-cup freezer-safe containers.
Seal, label and freeze. May be frozen up to 3 months.

title: souper potatoes
directions: Wash and scrub potatoes. With skin still on potatoes, cut into chunks and place in a casserole dish.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over potatoes. Melt butter and pour over potatoes.
Stir until all the potatoes are coated.
Bake in a 350° oven for approximately 45 minutes or until tender.
(I microwave mine on High for about 20 minutes or until tender.)
Be sure to stir potatoes every once in a while, while they are baking.

title: shrimp fettucine
directions: Cook pasta in 4 cups hot water for 8 minutes, then add shrimp and frozen vegetables.
Return to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer until shrimp turn pink and pasta is tender (about 1 to 3 minutes); drain and leave in saucepan.
Melt margarine or butter; stir in cornstarch, bouillon granules, garlic and lemon pepper seasoning. Add 3/4 cup milk.
Cook and stir over medium-high heat until thickened and bubbly, then stir 2 minutes more.
Stir in wine or milk.
Pour over pasta mixture and toss to combine.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese.
You may garnish with tomato and parsley if you desire.
Makes 3 servings.

title: joseph's trail mix
directions: Combine in plastic bag.
Shake and enjoy!

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve the yeast in the warm water.
Add the sugar, oil, egg, salt and flour.
If too soft, add more flour.
Pour on board and knead well.
Put in a large buttered bowl to rise. Turn in bowl to butter both sides and mash down even.
Let rise 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Work down and roll out.
Spread with soft butter.
Roll up like jelly roll and cut in 1 1/2-inch rolls.
Place together in pan and let rise.
Bake at 375° until brown.
Brush butter on tops before baking.

title: lazy day salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Cool Whip, by hand gently.
Do not use a mixer.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate about 2 hours.
Will keep at least a week or more (if it lasts that long).
Delicious and quick!

title: jewel fruit cake
directions: Line a loaf pan with heavy brown paper.
Grease paper well. (Use about a 4-inch deep pan and a brown paper sack.)
Chop pecans, dates, cherries and pineapple into medium-sized pieces. Place all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Mix until blended.
Turn into prepared loaf pan and press with spoon, or use your hand, to level the top.

title: glazed teriyaki chicken stir-fry
directions: In a large skillet, stir-fry chicken in 2 tablespoons oil for 6-8 minutes or until juices run clear. Remove chicken and set aside. In the same skillet, stir-fry carrots in remaining oil for 2 minutes. Add onion, stir-fry about 2-4 minutes longer or until vegetables are tender.
Combine soy sauce and brown sugar, add to skillet. Bring to a boil. Return chicken to skillet. Boil for 5 minutes or until sauce
is slightly thickened. Serve over rice. Sprinkle with sesame seed and green onions if desired.

title: apple cranberry crisp
directions: Peel apples and slice thin.
Arrange in square or 10 x 6 baking dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Spoon cranberry sauce over apple/cinnamon layer.

title: cream puffs
directions: Heat water and butter to boiling point.
Add flour and stir with wooden spoon until it forms a ball.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well until smooth.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet 3 inches apart.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce to 350° and bake for 30 minutes.

title: chicken tortillas
directions: Wrap chicken breasts in foil, 2 to a package.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour; save juice.
Debone breasts and cut into large pieces. Add remaining ingredients (except cheese and tortillas).
Shred cheese.
Butter tortillas and cut in fourths.
Layer like lasagna. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bread puff pudding
directions: Scald the milk and pour over the bread crumbs and butter. Separate the eggs; beat the yolks until thick and combine with the sugar, soda, salt and vanilla.
Add the bread; fold in the egg whites (whipped stiff).
Transfer to a well oiled pudding pan; set in a pan of warm water and bake in a slow oven for 30 minutes or until a knife comes out clean when inserted.
Serve warm.

title: toffee bars
directions: Beat butter for 30 seconds. Add brown sugar and beat until fluffy. Beat in egg yolk and vanilla. Gradually add flour and beat well. Press evenly in 13 x 9 x 2 baking pan and bake for 20 minutes in 350° oven. Immediately sprinkle chocolate pieces on top and let stand until softened (about 5 minutes) and spread evenly. Sprinkle with nuts. Cut into bars while warm.

title: marinated green beans and onions
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl; mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serving size 1/2 cup, calories 80, food exchanges 1 fat, 1 vegetable.

title: jam thumbprints
directions: Heat oven to 375°. In a mixing bowl, beat margarine or butter with an electric mixer on medium to high speed for 30 seconds. Add about half of the flour, the sugar, egg yolks and vanilla. Beat until thoroughly combined. Beat in remaining flour. Cover and chill about 1 hour or until easy to handle. Shape dough into 1-inch balls. Roll balls in egg whites, then in walnuts. Place 1-inch apart on a greased cookie sheet. Press centers with your thumb. Bake in a 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until edges are lightly browned. Cool cookies on a wire rack. Just before serving, fill centers with jam or preserves. Makes about 42.

title: wonderful casserole
directions: Make this the night before.
The poultry should be cooked and diced.
Place all ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Stir well, cover and refrigerate overnight. Uncover and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: apple crisp pudding
directions: Mix the crumbs, flour, nuts and sugars together.
Season with orange rind, salt and spices.
Moisten with butter.
Cover the bottom of a lightly buttered 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with a layer of apples.
Scatter some of crumb mixture over the top and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Repeat, ending with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes and serve warm with whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mocha-rum cheesecake
directions: Toss together cookies and butter.
Press into 9-inch spring-form pan.
Stir together rum and coffee.
Beat cream cheese, sugar, chocolate, flour and vanilla just until combined. Add eggs all at once.
Mix; do not overbeat.
Stir in rum.
Pour onto crust.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Serves 12.

title: triple-action multi-purpose cleaner
directions: We may live without friends, we may live without books,

title: peanut butter chex mix
directions: Melt peanut butter and margarine.
Pour over Chex mix and spread.
Bake at 200° for 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally; cool. Add raisins and chips.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Mix package of bread mix as directed, adding 1 teaspoon almond extract.
Pour into an 8 x 4-inch or 9 x 5-inch loaf pan (greased and floured bottom only).
Sprinkle with the sliced almonds.
Bake as directed; brush with warmed jelly just before serving.

title: buffalo chicken wings
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Coat wings with oil and sprinkle with black pepper.
Place wings in baking pan and bake for 20 minutes. Remove pan from oven.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: In a large bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat cream cheese and mayonnaise until smooth; gradually beat in sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time; beat in chocolate and vanilla until smooth. Pour into pie crust.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven 30 to 35 minutes or until set (when silver knife inserted in center comes out clean).
Chill 4 hours.
Serve with whipped topping if desired.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Crumble half of cake into bottom of punch bowl.
Start alternating ingredients:
1/2 cake, pudding, pie filling, fruit cocktail, pineapple, Cool Whip and coconut; repeat.
Crumble other half of cake on top.
Put layer of Cool Whip, coconut, nuts and cherries.

title: banana torte
directions: Mix well.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: new york deli style cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Have all above ingredients at room temperature.
Cream the cheese.
Add sugar slowly.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix well.
Add sour cream, bit by bit, followed by juice and vanilla.
Grease and line spring-form pan with graham cracker mixture.
(For crunchier crust, add 2 tablespoons melted butter.)
Bake for 10 minutes.
Cool, then add cheese mixture for baking.
Bake for 1 hour, then turn oven off.
Leave cake in oven for 1 1/2 hours with oven door cracked open.
Open door all the way and leave cake in for 1/2 hour longer.
(Slow cooling is the secret.)

title: salad supreme
directions: Empty Jell-O into blender.
Pour in water.
Blend together. Add cream cheese and pineapple, undrained.
Blend again.
Pour this mixture into a mold.
Stir in the pecans and chill overnight.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Whip in a blender until smooth.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas; combine with other ingredients and beat thoroughly.
(Mix soda and water together to add.)
Turn into 2 greased and floured loaf pans and bake for approximately 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: wild duck
directions: Salt and pepper duck.
Stuff with apple, onion, sausage (with casing removed) and celery leaves.
Add a little wine to the cavity.
Place in an iron pot.
Pour over rest of wine.
Place salt pork on breast of duck.
Cover.
Roast at 325° for about 3 hours. Serve with orange sauce.

title: strawberry charlotte
directions: Put the gelatine, 1/4 cup of the sugar and salt in the top of a double boiler.
(Add the following mixture to the double boiler, mix in a separate bowl.)
Beat egg yolks slightly and add water and 1 box of the strawberries.
Put over boiling water and cook, stirring constantly, until the gelatine is dissolved and the strawberries are melted.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Line 3-quart greased casserole with cooked broccoli. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Put cooked, boned chicken over broccoli and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
