Pour sauce over all and sprinkle again with Parmesan cheese.
Dot with butter and cook 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
I sometimes put this over egg noodles and it is delicious.

title: cheese and cracker bake
directions: Spread butter or margarine on crackers.
Place 9 in bottom of 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Arrange 4 slices of cheese over crackers. Top with another layer of 9 crackers.
Arrange 4 slices on top.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put sliced apples in greased baking dish; sprinkle with a little sugar.
Sift flour, salt, sugar and cinnamon.
Combine the butter with the flour mixture and spread this over the apples in baking dish.
Bake at 350° until apples are done, about 30 minutes.
Serve topped with whipping cream.
Serves 6.

title: ground turkey in onion gravy
directions: Mix ground turkey and garlic (reserve 1 teaspoon of garlic for gravy).
Chop 1/2 of 1 onion and bread crumbs.
Form 6 patties. Place in baking pan and bake in 375° oven for 15 minutes, then drain off fat.
Mix water, roux and garlic.
Pour over meat.
Slice rest of onions, cover and return to oven.
Cook 30 more minutes, covered.
Serve with rice or mashed potatoes.
Serves 6.

title: viv's chili
directions: Brown ground beef with onions, bell pepper, celery and garlic. Drain off fat.
Combine with the rest of the ingredients.
Simmer over low heat for 1 hour.
Add water as needed.
Serve with crackers.
This is really good on cold winter days.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Mix cornstarch and sugar in large skillet.
Stir in pineapple with juice, soy sauce and vinegar.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add green peppers; simmer 5 minutes.
Great with meatballs.

title: white chili
directions: Cut chicken breasts into 1/2-inch cubes.
Toss chicken with 4 teaspoons olive oil.
Saute cubed chicken until cooked (5 minutes).
Combine chicken, white chili mix, chicken broth and beans into 4-quart pot.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Garnish with a selection of Monterey Jack cheese, chopped red bell pepper, avocado and black olives.

title: party dip cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into two balls.
Roll in pecans.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: easy scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Brown the ground beef and green bell pepper; add the remaining ingredients. Cook for 10 minutes, then serve.

title: pizza dippers
directions: Brown sausage; crumble, drain and set aside.
Combine flour, cheese and salt.
Cut in shortening until mixture is the size of small peas.
Add sausage.
Add water, a little at a time, tossing and stirring with fork until dough is moist enough to hold together.
Shape into balls 1 inch in diameter.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Serve hot, dipped in cocktail or pizza sauce.
Serve on toothpicks.

title: beets and potato salad
directions: Step 1:
Melt Jell-O in 1/2 cup boiling water.

title: rich man's pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand and lemon juice until thick.
Add Cool Whip. Add remaining ingredients and pour into crust.
Refrigerate until cold.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Break cauliflower into small pieces and cook in small amount of water until tender; drain.
Add sliced, boiled eggs to cooked cauliflower.
Make white sauce of butter, flour, milk, salt and pepper.
Combine white sauce with cauliflower and eggs.

title: breakfast egg pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chewys
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 325 for 30 minutes in a large flat pan.

title: cheese cake
directions: Combine graham crackers and butter; press into bottom of spring-form pan.
Chill 10 minutes.

title: stuffed potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes; dry and prick with a fork.
Bake in a 425° oven 55 to 65 minutes until soft.
Reduce heat to 350°.
When potatoes are done, cut slice from top of each.
Carefully scoop out potato without breaking skin.
Set skins aside.
In medium mixing bowl, whip potatoes until smooth.
Add tomato sauce, butter, salt and cumin; beat until smooth.
Stir in corn, chilies and parsley. Spoon mixture into reserved potato skins.
Bake in a 350 degrees oven 20 to 30 minutes, until potatoes are heated through.
Yields 4 servings.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread softened cream cheese on the bottom of a 12 x 8-inch dish.
Spread chili on top of cream cheese.
Cover with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Microwave until cheese melts and dip is hot. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain all canned ingredients and mix together.
Use juice and add enough water to make 2 cups.
Add to instant pudding mix and beat for 2 minutes.
Add to fruit and sprinkle nuts on top.
Chill and serve.

title: oregon apple dapple
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Then add vanilla, apples and nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve warm with sauce.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Sift flour with spices and salt. Add this mixture to shortening mixture slowly.
Add raisins and nuts.
Mix water, soup and baking soda and add to batter.
Pour in greased 9-inch square cake pan.
Bake 375° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Bake chicken breasts in covered dish for 15 minutes at 425°; drain.
Layer spaghetti sauce, garlic, Mozzarella and Parmesan over chicken.
Top with lots of Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 30 minutes.

title: confetti corn bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt, pepper, sugar, thyme, sage and marjoram.
Add corn meal and stir to blend.
Saute onions, celery, green pepper and pimento in shortening.
To flour mixture, add sauteed vegetables with shortening, eggs and milk.
Stir until well blended.
Pour into well-greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake in hot 400° oven for 30 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix as for plain cake.
Add just enough milk to make the dough stiff enough to roll.
Chill dough.
Roll out in portions. Sprinkle on some sugar.
Cut into cookie shapes.
Bake 8 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: carmelitas
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Reserve 1 cup.
Press remaining mixture onto bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until light brown.
Cool 10 minutes.
Top with nuts and chocolate pieces.
Mix caramel topping and 1/4 cup flour until smooth.
Drizzle over chocolate pieces to within 1/4-inch of edges.
Sprinkle with reserved oat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 22 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely.

title: stuffing baked chicken
directions: Butter 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Place chicken side by side. Combine soup, milk and sour cream and mix well.
Pour over chicken.

title: fry bread
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking powder in a bowl. Make a hole in the center of the mixture and pour in buttermilk mixed with the baking soda. Knead the dough and roll it out on a lightly floured board. Cut it into rounds about 1/2-inch thick. Fry in medium oil.

title: greek cornbread
directions: Beat eggs; add rest of ingredients.
Put in 8 x 8-inch square greased Pyrex pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat and drain off grease.
Mix remaining ingredients together in a large pot.
Cook at medium heat for 1 hour.

title: italian sausage and peppers
directions: Remove cores, ribs and seeds from peppers.
Set aside.
Peel onions and slice into 1/8-inch slices.
Set aside.
Heat olive oil in large skillet.
Sear sausage for 5 minutes until well browned on all sides.
Remove from skillet and set aside.
Cook peppers and onions in sausage pan for 5 minutes over high heat.
Mix tomato paste with 1/4 cup of wine to dissolve.
Mix remaining wine and pour into skillet.
Bring to boil for 1 minuet.
Reduce heat to medium-low.
Sprinkle oregano over vegetables.
Place sausages in pan; cover and simmer for 40 minutes.
Cook noodles.
Serve over noodles.

title: bread pudding
directions: Toast bread and spread with butter.
Arrange toast in baking pan. Stir salt, sugar and cinnamon into eggs.
Add milk and lemon extract to egg mixture and stir well.
Pour over toast.
Press toast down so it will soak up milk.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Serve warm or cold.

title: rhubarb oat mixture
directions: Combine flour, oatmeal, brown sugar, walnuts, baking soda and salt. Mix. Cut in cold butter or margarine. Press 3 cups mixture in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Soak rhubarb in 1 cup cold water for 3 minutes. Drain.

title: apple cake
directions: Preheat oven
to 350°.	Grease and flour a 12-cup Bundt pan. Peel,
core and quarter apples.
Cut into 1/4-inch thick slices. Mix apples and sugar together.
Let stand 30 minutes. Add oil and eggs; mixing well.	Sift together flour, cinnamon, soda and salt. Stir into apple mixture.
Add vanilla, walnuts and coconut.
Pour into
Bundt
pan.
Bake
to 45 minutes until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat for 2 minutes.
Drop from teaspoon, 2 inches apart, on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 2 to 3 dozen.

title: stuffed french bread
directions: Brown ground beef, salt and pepper; set aside.
Saute onion, bell pepper, mushrooms and dry mustard in butter.
Combine with meat mixture and all remaining ingredients.
Stuff in bread and cook for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add Crisco and mix well.
Add buttermilk.
On a well-floured board, knead dough.
Roll out to desired height and cut with cutter.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Sift flour and measure.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt. Add sugar, oil, eggs, bananas, vanilla and pineapple.
Mix well with fork; do not beat.
Pour mixture into long prepared pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: stir-fry chicken
directions: Cut and skin (if not already) chicken in thin strips.
Set aside.
In small bowl, blend sauce mixture.
Set aside.
Add oil to wok.
Preheat.
Slice green pepper, carrots and onions into thin strips.
Cut broccoli into small pieces.
Stir-fry carrots and broccoli for 2 minutes.
Add onions and green pepper.
Add chicken to wok, stir-fry for 4 minutes.
Add sauce mixture. Cover and simmer on low for 2 minutes . Serve.

title: red pineapple punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve over ice.

title: white sauce(for potatoes or other vegetables)
directions: Melt oleo in saucepan over low heat.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring, until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.

title: rhubarb-strawberry jello jam
directions: Let rhubarb and sugar stand overnight in a bowl.
Bring to a boil; add jello.
Boil about 10 minutes.
Pour into hot glasses and seal with paraffin.

title: japanese fried rice
directions: Cook chicken breasts and shred.
Cook rice.
Saute carrots, celery and onions until tender.
Add rice, chicken and soy sauce (medium heat).
Keep tossing.
Add bamboo shoots, water chestnuts, bean sprouts, eggs, snow peas and more soy sauce.
Keep tossing and adding soy sauce as you add ingredients.
Remove from heat. Cover and let set a few minutes.

title: pumpkin crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix first 5 ingredients together and pour into 13 x 9 buttered (or sprayed with nonstick spray) pan. Sprinkle dry cake mix on top of mixture in pan.
Top with nuts and drizzle margarine on top of nuts.
Bake 1 hour.
Serve with whipped cream.
(Better when served warm.)

title: citrus mint cooler
directions: To Prepare Makeup:
In a small bowl, mix cornstarch and flour. Gradually stir in light corn syrup and water until smooth.
Pour about 1/4 cup into each of four bowls or paper cups.
Color three of the batches with desired liquid or paste food colors.
(Paste provides more intense color.) Leave one batch untinted.
For additional colors, prepare more makeup.

title: mushroom scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix mushroom soup, cheese, pimento and salt into milk and stir well.
Add sliced potatoes.
Put into a well-greased 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes are done.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Cook sugar, milk, butter and cocoa.
Let cook until boiling. Let boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla.
Drop cookies onto waxed paper and let cool or spread into greased pan until set, then cut into small pieces.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: In large skillet or Dutch oven, cook and stir ground beef and onion in butter until onion is tender.
Stir in flour, salt, garlic, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in soup; simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes. Stir in sour cream and heat through.
Serve over cooked noodles. Serves 4 to 6.

title: tomato casserole
directions: Boil tomatoes, onion, brown sugar and salt for 10 minutes. Toss bread crumbs in melted butter.
Combine tomatoes and most of bread crumbs.
Put remaining bread crumbs on top.
Garnish with parsley and bake in covered casserole for 30 minutes.
Bake at 325°.
Serves 5.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
It's best the next day.

title: ham and broccoli roll-ups
directions: Roll 2 pieces of broccoli (spears inside) on ham.
Take one biscuit, rolled slightly flat, and put broccoli and ham roll on biscuit.
Fold over all, pinch and place on a shallow baking pan, lightly greased.
Bake just long enough to get biscuits done, 10 to 12 minutes.
Serve Cheese Sauce over.

title: fresh apple cake(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Mix according to directions.

title: high as the sky strawberry pie
directions: Whip the whipping cream in a small bowl and put in fridge. Chill a medium mixing bowl (glass, not plastic) and beaters. Combine remaining ingredients and beat 15 minutes (by timer). Fold mixtures together and swirl.
Pour into pre-baked 8-inch pie crust.
Place, uncovered, in freezer.
Serve frozen.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 370° for approximately 1 hour in a 9 x 2 x 13-inch pan.

title: leaf lettuce dressing
directions: Mix together; cook until it comes to a boil (until the eggs are done), except for mayonnaise, keep to side until needed.
Remove from heat, then add mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Eat hot or cold.
Fold lettuce, then dip into dressing.

title: apple cake
directions: Add sugar to apples and let stand 10 minutes or longer. Sift flour and spices. Blend oil and eggs and pour into apples. Add flour all at once and blend with wooden spoon. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in 9 x 13 pan. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar when cool.

title: early american bean bake
directions: Combine pork and beans, celery, apple, water and brown gravy mix in casserole dish.
Top with Brown 'N Serve sausage links. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: spinach bake
directions: Mix well and pour into 10 x 6-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
When doubled, bake in 9 x 13-inch pan and add 15 minutes baking time.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in large cooking dish.
Add 1 cup water; bring to boil.
Add 1 cup instant rice; cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Add other ingredients.
Sprinkle top with grated cheese.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix altogether.
Three times the recipe fills a large Bundt pan.

title: lucinda's fruit cake cookies
directions: Cut fruit fine.
Mix in raisins and nuts.
Dredge with 1/2 cup flour.
Cream butter well and gradually add sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, and beat well.
Sift flour, adding in spices.
Add the soda to the creamed mixture, then add flour and liquid, blending well. Pour the batter over the floured fruit and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop by tablespoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar; mix until not grainy.
Beat eggs until lemon color.
Add sugar and butter.
Beat at high speed 10 minutes.
Sift flour and soda.
Add to eggs mixture small amounts at a time.
Grease a tube cake pan.
Pour batter in pan and bake at 250° until a straw inserted comes out clean.

title: cornbread pudding
directions: Melt margarine over low heat and let cool.
Combine cornbread mix, sour cream eggs and stir well.
Add both cans of corn and the cooled melted margarine and stir well.
Pour all into a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350 degrees until top is golden brown and toothpick comes out moist but clean (approx. 30 minutes in a 3 - 4 inch casserole).
This recipe is best in a deep dish, but can use a 9 x 13 pan (approx. 20 minutes).
This should be more moist than corn bread...do not overcook.

title: nut and raisin squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease shallow 9-inch square pan.
Sift flour, soda, salt and ginger together.
Stir in raisins and nuts. Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla and molasses.
Add flour and nut mixture; blend well.
Pour into prepared pan; bake about 30 minutes.
Mark into squares; let cool in pan before removing.
Yields 25.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar and oil and pour over vegetables.
Before serving, drain off and add salt and pepper.

title: tortellini salad
directions: Prepare tortellini and veggies as packages direct.
Drain and keep hot.
In large bowl, mix together mayonnaise or olive oil, Parmesan and/or Romano cheese, minced garlic, basil and black or white pepper.
Mix hot veggies and tortellini with sauce (cheese should melt, if not nuke it).
The olive oil version is "Heart Smart."

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in loaf pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli, raisins, pecans, onion and bacon.

title: zoey's favorite
directions: Bake at 350° to 400° for 50 to 60 minutes until bubbly. Serve warm. Refrigerate.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, beating until stiff peaks form.
Fold in pecans.
Pour butter into a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan. Spread pecan mixture over butter.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.
Cool and store in an airtight container.
Yields 4 cups.

title: sour cream candy(1960 recipe)
directions: Combine sugar and cream and cook at 240° or soft ball stage. Remove from heat.
Add pinch of salt and butter.
Beat until mixture begins to grain.
Stir in vanilla and nuts and pour into pan.

title: lasagna
directions: Saute ground beef in a skillet in butter until it loses its pinkness.
Transfer to a pot.
Peel and chop onions.
Saute until transparent.
Add to the meat.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, bouillon cube, minced garlic and seasonings.
Cook over medium low heat, covered, for about 20 minutes.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Mix and cook cake mix by directions on box.
Let cool.
Punch holes in the cake.
Pour caramel and Eagle Brand milk over cake. Cover with Cool Whip.
Crumble Butterfingers over the Cool Whip.

title: chicken metrazzini
directions: Make a white sauce with butter, flour, cream and broth.
Cook on medium heat until thickened. Add chicken, mushrooms and spaghetti.
Spoon into a large greased casserole.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top. Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes. Freezes well.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind the cranberries and add the cut up marshmallows. Mix and refrigerate overnight.

title: banana loaf
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in large bowl. Make a well in center of mixture. Combine remaining ingredients. Add to dry mixture, stirring until moistened. Pour batter into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pan 10 minutes. Remove from pan and let cool on wire rack. Makes 1 loaf.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Melt margarine and mix with the stuffing mix.
Put into baking dish, saving some
to
sprinkle
on top.
Spread cut up chicken on stuffing mix.
Mix	soup,
broth,
sour cream, salt and pepper; pour
over chicken.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: turkey pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to direction on package.
Drain and rinse.
Place in a 2 1/2 quart salad bowl.
Add turkey, celery, onion and green pepper.
Toss to mix.
Combine dressing mix, sour cream, salad dressing and garlic salt.
Add to pasta mixture and mix well.
Sprinkle with almond and paprika.
Garnish with pepper and tomato slices if desired.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken hot dish
directions: Cook carrots and celery in chicken broth until tender. Combine all ingredients.
Bake in a large casserole dish at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: very good soft white icing
directions: Combine milk and flour and cook to a smooth, thick paste. Beat remaining ingredients until creamy.
Add flour mixture and beat.
Very good!

title: cheese ball
directions: Cut dried beef into small pieces.
Mix cream cheese, dressing and dried beef together.
Make into log or ball and roll in pecans.
Chill overnight.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and remove from bone.
Add soups, peas and sour cream and mix well.
Mix melted margarine with crushed crackers.

title: skillet enchiladas
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, cook ground beef and onion until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Drain.
Stir in soup, enchilada sauce, milk and chilies.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together and make 8 patties shaped like hamburgers.
Spray a nonstick pan with Pam and fry until crisp.

title: spinach on the side
directions: Cook spinach according to directions; drain well.
Add next 4 ingredients, 1/4 cup bread crumbs and 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese.
Mix well.
Place mixture in a casserole dish.
Top with one layer of bread crumbs and one layer of Parmesan cheese. Drizzle 1 to 2 tablespoons melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Top should be lightly browned.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Add vegetable mixture to syrup and simmer for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Seal in sterilized jars.
Makes 3 to 4 quarts or 6 to 8 (1/2) pints.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine ingredients in a large bowl; stir.
Serve chilled.

title: clam dip
directions: In bowl, blend cream cheese and sour cream together well. Stir in lemon juice, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Fold minced clams into cream cheese mixture.
Chill and serve.

title: grandma's dried apple cake
directions: Soak apples overnight in cold water. Chop raisins fine and stew with syrup until soft but not pulpy. Cool. Mix with apple mixture. Add remaining ingredients for batter. Bake until it tests done.

title: raisin pie
directions: Prepare pastry.
Heat raisins and water to boiling; boil for 5 minutes.
Stir sugar and flour into raisin mixture.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in nuts, lemon peel and lemon juice.
Pour filling into pie crust.
Cover with top crust, which has slits cut in it.
Seal and flute.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes or until crust is brown and juice begins to bubble through slits.

title: striped grahams
directions: Mix jello packet with one cup of applesauce and mix contrasting jello with second cup of applesauce.
Do not separate graham crackers.
Place two sections of two lengthwise on dish.
Spread with jello/applesauce mixture.
Place two more sections on top and spread with contrasting jello-applesauce mix.
Continue layering crackers with alternating flavors (peach and raspberry are especially good).

title: sausage and kraut
directions: Cut sausage into bite size pieces.
In a roaster, put kraut and sausage.
Bake in oven at 325° for about 3 to 4 hours.
Stir frequently, so sausage does not burn.
If you wish, you can cook potatoes in with kraut.

title: caesar salad
directions: Rinse lettuce and let dry.
Refrigerate wrapped in paper towels for several hours to crisp leaves.
Whisk raw egg, garlic, lemon juice and oil together and pour into bottom of large salad bowl.
Add lettuce, anchovies and hard-cooked eggs.
Toss thoroughly with dressing.
Add cheese and toss again.
Sprinkle with croutons.
Serve immediately.
Pass the peppermill.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients.
Spoon into prepared pie crust.
Cover with top crust.
Crimp edges to seal.
Slit top crust and bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Cool about 10 minutes before serving.

title: chicken delight
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan or glass dish, place dried beef to accomodate the number of chicken breasts.
Wrap each breast with a slice of bacon.
Place wrapped chicken on each piece of dried beef.
Mix both soups and sour cream.
Spoon over the wrapped breast.
Cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: rhubarb muffins
directions: Combine rhubarb and 1/4 cup sugar.
Let stand 1 hour.
Mix together flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Beat together egg, buttermilk, oil and vanilla. Add to dry ingredients.
Mix just until moist.
Add rhubarb mixture.

title: corn and broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bacon, together.
Put in 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.
Place bacon on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or more until done.

title: asparagus with cream cheese soup
directions: Combine asparagus and broth in a pan; bring to a boil, uncovered.
Stir to break asparagus apart, then reduce heat and simmer, gently, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Add salt to taste. Cut the cream cheese into 1/2-inch cubes and place in soup tureen. Pour the hot asparagus soup in and serve at once.
If you choose to use sour cream, pour soup into individual bowls.
Add sour cream without stirring.

title: janet's pudding delight
directions: Mix together and press into bottom of 13X9 pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter chocolate fudge
directions: Melt cream cheese and peanut butter in microwave for approx 2 minutes (stopping and stirring at 1 minute intervals). Melt chocolate in separate bowl until creamy. Combine chocolate with cream cheese mixture and whisk in sweetener and cream. Pour into buttered (or Pam'ed) glass dish and chill at least 4 hours. Cut into 16 squares. 2.5 carbs per piece.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix in cream of celery soup and mushroom soup.
Pour in a casserole dish and place Tater Tots on top.
Bake at 350° until Tater Tots are done.

title: mulled cider
directions: Heat slowly and let stand for several hours before removing spices.
Serve in hot mugs.

title: good pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Melt 1 tablespoon of butter in skillet.
Pour into skillet 2 tablespoons of batter.
Fry until full of bubbles.
Flip and fry until golden brown.

title: fluffy oat pancakes
directions: Heat electric griddle to 370°.
In a bowl, combine all dry ingredients, buttermilk and vanilla.
In a mixer bowl, beat egg whites until soft peaks form. Fold egg whites into oat mixture. Spray griddle.

title: white chocolate mint sauce with raspberries
directions: Break up the chocolate and melt it in the top of a double boiler over hot water.
Meanwhile, bring the milk to a boil in a small saucepan and steep the mint in it for 5 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: In a buttered baking dish, combine apples, 1/3 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons butter.
Mix in medium bowl and blend remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: patio potato salad
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch in saucepan and add next 6 ingredients.
Heat until thick and bubbly.
Remove from heat and add salad dressing and onion.
Mix with cut up potatoes and eggs. Chill well and serve.

title: pace cream cheese dip
directions: Soften cream cheese in a bowl.
Stir in Pace picante sauce. Add lemon, salt and pepper to taste.
Blend well.
Serve with corn chips or potato chips.
Add more Pace picante sauce for a better taste.

title: baked chow suey
directions: Place rice in boiling water and set aside.
In separate pan, cook meat, onion and celery until browned.
Drain fat.
Strain rice.
In a 3-quart casserole dish, place rice, meat mixture and all other ingredients, except almonds.
Mix well.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with almonds and bake for 15 minutes more.

title: corn pudding(corn casserole)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix everything together in baking dish. Bake uncovered for 30 to 45 minutes until nicely brown.

title: hot pepper spread
directions: Put all ingredients in large pan and boil 15 minutes.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour, mixed into thin paste.
Cook entire mixture 5 more minutes.
Seal in hot, sterile jars.
Excellent on meat.

title: granola
directions: Measure oats, wheat flakes, nuts and coconut into bowl. Stir to	mix.
Add
oil,
honey,
vanilla and salt. Mix well. Spread 1/2-inch
deep
on	cookie	sheet.	Bake at 250° until toasted and
golden
brown,
about	40
to	60 minutes.
Stir occasionally as sides brown first. Let cool.
Store in jars.

title: recipe for a happy child
directions: Parents add the ingredients slowly and consistently, making sure to mix well.
Sprinkle with mistakes and mix until dissolved. Comes out perfect every time.

title: cabbage relish
directions: Mix all together and put in the refrigerator for 1 day. Then it is ready to eat.

title: creamy cheese ball
directions: In medium bowl combine cream cheese, 2 tablespoons almonds and sherry.
Shape into ball. Cover and refrigerate 3 hours.
Smooth surface with spatula and roll in toasted almonds to coat.
Serve with crackers.
Makes 1/2 cup.

title: whipped topping
directions: Chill bowl and beaters.
Combine milk powder and ice water. Beat until stiff.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Serve immediately.

title: coconut cake
directions: In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, cook cake according to directions on box.
Cool 10 minutes. Poke holes in cake with straw.
Mix Eagle Brand milk and cream of coconut together.
Pour over cake.
Let cool.
Mix Cool Whip and can of coconut and frost cake.

title: linda's venison stew
directions: Marinate venison in red wine vinegar for 3 to 4 hours; drain. Transfer venison to a large pot and cover with water.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add garlic and chili powder.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer for another 25 minutes.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Whip mayonnaise together with cream cheese.
Add garlic powder and mix well.
Rinse crab and drain.
Fold crab into mayonnaise mixture.
Place in a buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with crackers.

title: apple krisp
directions: Place apples in greased baking pan.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and egg.
Place over apples.
Pour melted butter over top and sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in 375° oven.
May double for 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: hawaiian fruit dip
directions: Combine sour cream, milk and pudding in bowl with whisk, mix until smooth.
Add pineapple and coconut.
Mix to combine. Refrigerate for 30 minutes before serving.
Yields 2 cups.

title: cheese meat loaf
directions: Chop onion.
Mix all ingredients well.	Shape in a loaf in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: grandma's cucumber koko
directions: Cut cucumbers into 2-inch wedges.
Mix sugar, salt and vinegar in a pot on low heat.
Add smashed, whole chili peppers to taste. Remove mixture and pour over cucumber wedges.
Let stand for about an hour, stirring occasionally.
Bottle and refrigerate.

title: okra and tomatoes
directions: Fry meat.
Add other ingredients in saucepan.
When meat is done, add vegetables.
Cover the saucepan.
Simmer over low heat for 25 minutes.
Do not add water.
The liquid from canned tomatoes should be enough.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Combine dry ingredients with milk to make thin batter. Melt margarine in a deep bowl in oven while it is preheating to 350°. Pour batter into middle of melted margarine. Do not stir. Carefully pour fruit which has been sweetened with 1/2 cup sugar and seasoned as you wish over batter. (Any canned fruit pie filling may be used, too.) Do not stir. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until crusted on top.
